text: This is the place for breakfast and brunch slash comfort food. Every week they have a unique flavor of potted bread which is offered as a side to most entrees.  I like the omelette selection.  The wait staff is attentive and very nice. At peak hours there's usually a short 15-30min wait for a table. I like to burn time at Dead Poets Used Bookstore also located in the same strip mall.

We came here for breakfast on a Vegas trip, my husband likes to find local mom and pop places rather than the usual tourist traps.

My son ordered the smores pancakes which are actually chocolate chip pancakes with caramel sauce and whip cream.  I tried a bite and they were delicious.  The pancakes were light, airy and chocolatey.  I was surprised they weren't overly sweet.

I ordered the french toast with strawberries.  It was very good with fresh strawberries instead of limp soggy thawed berries and they were plentiful.  The french toast is drudged in crushed cornflakes so they had a nice bite to them and no soggy bread.

My husband ordered the corn beef  hash, this is where they lost two stars.  What arrived looked like browned sliced pieces of lunchmeat.  He told me it was so salty he couldn't even taste anything else.  To make sure he wasn't being overly dramatic, I had a small taste.  OMG it was the saltiest thing I've ever eaten and I like salt.  I drank my entire drink after that small bite.  It literally tasted like someone spilled the entire salt container in the hash and fried my taste buds, glad I was done with my french toast.  

Bottom line, don't go anywhere near that hash if you have functional taste buds and anything but perfect blood pressure.  Get the french toast.

I really wasn't impressed. My husband and I stopped in on a Wednesday morning on a recent trip to Vegas, we were seated immediately by a friendly hostess. I was really excited to try it due to the great reviews, it's a way off the strip and wasn't worth the drive. 

I had the Breakfast Combo thing with eggs, ham, sausage, bacon, and pancakes. The pancakes were doughy and not cooked through, the eggs were a spongy egg-replacement, and the rest was average. 

My hubby had the Corned Beef Hash Eggs Benedict at the waiter's recommendation and it was really slimy and the English muffin basically drowned and dissolved in all of the sauce. His hashbrowns were greasy and left a lot to be desired. 

We ordered the S'mores pancake to try it and it was just a pancake with chocolate chips and marshmallows sprinkled on top, it was gross. Our waiter didn't take it off our tab or bring us the cinnamon raisin pot of bread we ordered. 

Not worth coming back, and no clue why it is so highly rated. Cost us $25+ so not cheap diner food either...

I never let the fact a restaurant in Vegas is in a strip mall bother me, because inevitably they wind up being great and Jamm's is no exception. We came based on the Yelp reviews and had to leave one for others.

The free pot of bread you get with a Yelp check-in is awesome, we had the cinnamon raisin variety and were pleasantly surprised at how much lighter and fluffier it was than your regular cinnamon roll. We had omelets with home fries and it was very filling.

Service was friendly and fast, good value.

Came here on a Sunday after working out at 24-hour.  Must have been early enough (around 1030AM), as we were seated right away.

Coffee was good, food was good.  We got a small stack of the grain pancakes, which was actually a pretty big stack.  They were good, but nothing to write home about.  Also got an omlete with cheese, bacon, and avocado.  Minimal avocado, tons of bacon and cheese.  After working out, would have preferred the reverse.  It was tasty though and came with a heaping side of cottage cheese and tomoatos.  Food tasted as expected.

Service was ok.  Not too spot on for a Sunday, which one would think would be the prime breakfast day.  Cost was around $20 for above mentioned food and 2 coffees.  Wish I would've ordered that cinnamon roll in a mug- looks divine!

The crowd must come around 11AM, as there were 4 or 5 parties waiting for a table.

Our new bfast hangout ..great pancakes and waffles selection and even greater lunch menu ! We had Eggs and pancakes with Nutella ..Its pancakes with Nutella topping ..I should have tried pumpkin pancakes ..French pressed coffee was a nice option ..chicken club sandwich was great ..we saw a lot of tables ordered waffles and chicken ..so must be their thing ? Oh..if u check in on Yelp and showed it to your server you get a free pot of bread ..we got the blueberry one super yummy  ..if u like the additional 10% off your bill, post of Facebook or Twitter too

The food is super good !!! My two favs are the corned beef hash and eggs !! The best in town ..no one comes close ... And the country skillet... if ur running on empty this will fill u up !!! The service is great !!! my favorite part is just hearing Shirley's laugh...makes my day !!! Well worth the wait... because this place gets busy ..
Loved the early morning atmosphere and the pot of bread. Coffee and company is awesome!
Great food and service! Place is small but comfortable. As soon as we sat down we had someone come to us for drinks. I will definitely go back to try some of the other menu choices.
I had the best omelet (the babalama - bacon, tomato, avocado, and cheddar) of my life here.

We are back for lunch.  We were not disappointed.  Beef dip and fries were great.  My wife had the Club with sweet potato fries.  She loved it.

Service is still great as is the food. Everyone is so friendly.  Nice way ti get out of the heat.

First time here and have determined it was a pretty good decision.   There was maybe a 10 to 15 minute wait (0900 on Saturday morning) but we'll worth it.  The staff was very friendly,  the food was quick,  hot,  and plenty.  They have PLENTY of great items on the menu but I went with the basic eggs and bacon with hashbrowns and toast.  Great start to my day.
Jamms is our favorite local breakfast joint in town. Great food and the best server's ever!

Long overdue. I stopped by with my husband on September 4th. We were in Las Vegas celebrating our first Anniversary, traveling from Sacramento, Ca.  The food here is amazing. I had the homemade Chicken Soup and a turkey sausage burrito. My husband tried their pot bread and the crunchy french toast. The food was perfectly prepped and seasoned.  The atmosphere was loud but we knew it was because it was busy. Must be because its popular. Certainly interested in coming back if ever I am in the area again!
I love the fresh bread and the chicken noodle soup in the breakfast a really good with the crunchy French toast
Such a great breakfast with excellent service! I got the Mediterranean omlette and it was supurb! Will definitely be coming back. Thank you!
I got the Irish skillet and my wife got the pancake combo.  Both meals were very delicious!   The pictures look great but the taste is even better.   The wait staff and atmosphere are great 5/5

This is a comfortable homey restaurant. Everything is great. The potted bread option can be a meal in itself but you won't want to pass up one of the great omelets. The southwest hamburger is a real treat. Friendly staff does whatever you need to enjoy your meal. Prices are very reasonable.
Very friendly staff, great service and good food a great place to have breakfast or lunch ! Bery affordable and great portion sizes for the price.

I have to start by thanking my good friend John, who introduced me to Jamms.


 Jamms specialises in breakfast and lunch. It is an unassuming place well away from the strip - so most of the traditional visitors to Vegas won't know about it.


 The service is extremely friendly and welcoming as soon as you enter the restaurant.


 The type of food served is typically diner-style food. However there are a few things that raise them up to a five-star rating:


 1. The service is genuinely friendly
2. The steak and eggs (for breakfast) is great - and arrives very quickly
3. Try the chicken-fried steak. It is to die for!
4. Instead of toast, have the pot of bread. You get an individual loaf that has been freshly baked in its own ramekin. Marvellous!


 Obviously when I was there, the waitress must have noticed my enthusiasm for the homemade bread because she brought me a second one (which I dispatched with equal enthusiasm).


 Vegas can be a mad place, but it is really nice to stumble across somewhere like Jamms every so often.

I wanted to love this place. The potted bread was good, but not tdf or anything. I might go back to try some kinda eggy or pancakey or waffley meal or maybe a sandwich...give them a chance to redeem themselves after the awful corned beef hash, which really was a dire salty pile of mush next to some flavor-free hash browns and perfectly cooked poached eggs. Hormel's cbh is miles better than that stuff was. In future when I want cbh, I'll either have it at home out of a can or pay a bit too much for it at Hash House A Go Go (for all that place's faults, they do know their namesake). 
I want to give them more stars as I always prefer to support local family-run places, but for now, it's just a Meh.

The staff is friendly.  Service was excellent had the corner beef hash one of the better ones I've had in awhile. Recommend getting the hash well done extra crispy. Pop over thing was excellent decent cup of joe

Excellent breakfast spot. Pot of breads are awesome (they are really just breads baked in cupcake size). Had an omelette, customized however you like. Huge portions, friendly service, and quality food!

Love their fat fries with a side of ranch! I usually get their jamms american breakfast sandwich or their BBQ chicken sandwich or their amazing Denver potato pancakes. Love this place. Definitely me and my husband's go to place for brunch!
Try the mini pot with the raisins and cinnamon , it's delicious.   This restaurant is to die for. We come here weekly with my clients and we all love it.
My idea of a perfect yummy brunch! Everything was wonderful and I plan to go back soon to try more!!
Great food. Love the Sandy omelet. Service is great. Really great menu choices. I live in Henderson and try specifically to come here to eat

Nothing bad to say. Have your group ready to be seated when you get there. Food choices are outstanding. Quality is superior, service quick and friendly. Portions great, hot, fresh. Priced RIGHT!!! Many regulars there each visit & they know all the friendly staff. Won't go anywhere else now for breakfast! Hostess Devyn is the best!
Hated The Griddle :-(
While off the beaten path, the warm atmosphere of Jamm's, their friendly staff, and great breakfast is a must if you're looking for a new spot!

The service is always wonderful. We were promptly greeted at the door and shown to our seats. Just as we were sitting they came to take our drink order. Our waitress Sandy came by not to long after we received our drinks to take our order. 

We were there early so it wasn't quite as packed as it usually is on a Sunday. I loved seeing those with their football jerseys on. The new paint on the door and Windows is fabulous I love Frankenstein. 

My husband had the California Benedict with home fries. It was beautiful to look at. He said it was glorious. It had a fresh taste but was also rich with their hollandaise sauce that he loves so much. The tomato and avocado were perfectly ripe. I had my usual French toast combo. The bacon was extra crisp exactly how I like it. They have a Jamms French toast or a traditional both are good options but I do prefer the traditional. My eggs were over medium, which is what I asked for. We also shared their weekly pot of bread this week it was pineapple pumpkin. My husband  greatly enjoyed the pot of bread, but it was my favorite but that's the joy of having a different flavors to try every week. 

We love that they offer discounts of you check in on social media or yelp. Our waitress was very attentive throughout the entire meal and we were very satisfied with our experience there as always.
Cant go wrong with this place, very creative menu and super delicious.

I was looking for a restaurant that had good corned beef hash and this place popped up. It's located in a strip mall and it's actually bigger on the inside than it appears. Total hole in the wall diner feel with booths. 

Ordered the corned beef hash that comes with 2 eggs, hash browns and their famous pot of bread. I got the lemon and blueberry, which was their flavor of the week and it came out piping hot with sweet butter cream. They also have plain and cinnamon raisin daily. Everything was great! Did not disappoint and it was a good size portion. My pot of bread wasn't quite ready with the rest of the order, so she gave me a complimentary cinnamon raisin also. 

Next time I'm going to order the home fries instead. It's not the typical diced potatoes, but they were sliced and looked almost like hash. Tasted hubby's and it was good. He ordered the Reuben omelet, my son had a made to order omelet and my other son had the steak and eggs. Everyone enjoyed their meals and said the restaurant was a good choice. Will definitely be back!
Fantastic service and great food! When you need comfort food and a place that gives you that feeling of meeting friends Jamms is the place. We love Ronnie.

The Jamm's French Toast was some of the best french toast I've had in my life, and the ham steak was half the size of an entire plate! Pot-o-bread is similar to Alton Brown's Popovers, poofy, soft, and flavorful bread in a little muffin tin. Service was friendly and overall the food was excellent. Will definitely be back many times!

I have been coming here for 10+ years and never a bad experience. Sandy is the best server, fast friendly and funny. If you want a delicious treat try their weekly pot a bread. Also I love the Erica small plates which allows for us Weightloss patients to order in small portions!!! I will always remain a loyal customer for the next 10+ years!!!
This is my 3rd time here. The food is always fresh and delicious and the service is more than excellent, everyone is super courteous and attentive.

We have been going to Jamms for years!  The food is amazing and the staff are even better.  Try the pot of bread, the omelets are fabulous.  MY favorite is the mushroom delight, cream cheese in a omelet, so good.   My husband's is the white castle omelets, ground beef, onions and cheese.  So Yummy.  Don't forget the biscuits and gravy!

Food was good as usual but service was not as great. The server was sweet but they brought out our food a couple of plates at a time. Mine was the last and about 15 minutes after everyone else's so they were pretty much done. We also ordered a small plate of French toast sticks that they never brought out and she didn't come back enough for us to say anything. 

Later, the waitress told us she realized she forgot and removed it from the check but never apologized or offered to get us any which I thought was a little rude. At that point, we were over it and didn't really want them. 

Other than that, food was good just maybe not in a big group.

C'est mon restaurant déjeuner favori à Las Vegas. C'est un espèce de Chez Cora. Beau, bon, pas cher, avec une ligne d'attente. ;-) Et comparativement aux buffets dans les hôtels, chez Jamms c'est excellent et pas dispendieux. Et la qualité des ingrédients est là. 

Petit truc, si la ligne d'attente est trop longue, le bar est une option rapide, sans besoin d'attendre.

This place can get super busy, and there's a reason why. Everything I've tried here is great. To the point where I had a friend come in from out of town and she loved it. The next time she was in town, the only thing from her last trip she insisted we repeat- Jamms. Any time a tourist wants to go to the same place twice, you know it's awesome. And the people working here are always super friendly. They treat you like family. And yum goes the food. Try the bread bowl! It's their little specialty.
Great environment amazing food and love the service. My always go to spot for great breakfast

I like jamms.  It is good, they have a great little thing called a pot of bread.  The regular pot of bread is good, but I tend to like there special one for the week.  They have really good pancakes, and decent burgers. The staff is friendly, but they really do get crowded on the weekends. Especially on Sunday morning. The staff is friendly, and the prices are okay.  I do love the smores pancakes, and the cornflaked French toast.  You should give it a try you will love the home kitchen feeling and friendly staff
Best breakfast in town. Jamms is a throwback to old Vegas. Great service,  great omelettes, and don't forget to order their famous pot of bread.
Awesome as always! We never miss coming here for breakfast when we visit Vegas. Great food, service, and prices.

What a great place to eat. I go about once a week and the place is always busy but the service is great. I always request to sit in Shays section. She is the sweetest girl and is super professional. Never leaves and empty plate or glass and has great recommendations of things new to eat.  Will always go back for the food and smiles.
You HAVE to come here when you visit Vegas. Old school decor, sweet waitresses.

Long time lover of this fabulous, down home diner. Haven't been back in quite awhile. Wish I had stayed away. The service and friendly atmosphere is still fully intact. Wonderful, quick service. One start for that alone. 

Unfortunately, I think, over the years, they have tried to become something they're not. The menu has exploded with ridiculous, monstrosities for new dishes. They couldn't just add chicken and waffles. They had to create anything and everything with waffles from a BLT on waffles to a waffle pizza. Yes, I said "waffle pizza."  They managed to get a bit of notoriety on the Travel Channel with a crazy breakfast sandwich consisting of a corned beef hash omelet with sauerkraut and Swiss cheese piled on a huge pretzel bun that has been egg battered with cinnamon and sugar then deep fried. Couldn't bring myself to try it. 

The last time I visited, Jamm's had been venturing into exotic coffees and cappuccinos. They were heading in the right direction. This visit, the coffee tasted like it had been brewed through the same grounds all day. I could t even finish one cup. 

We went with a couple classics that we remember being the best in town the Hash and Eggs and the Country Benedict. The hash would have been fine without the handful of chopped garlic that was clearly tossed in right at the end of cooking. I love garlic, but that much undercooked garlic ruined what was once a breakfast legend. Since they clearly switched their sausage to a poor quality, frozen patty, they must not have had the flavorful sausage drippings and fond leftover to make a decent country gravy.  They changed their home fried potatoes to hash browns with onions and peppers. Which would be fine, but then don't call them home fries. Call them hash browns O'Brien. Of course, that wouldn't be necessary as they still offer hash browns on the menu. 

I am not only disappointed, but saddened by the changes this place has undergone since I last visited. This used to be a place where we new the crew and they new what we wanted and you could not pick a bad thing off the menu. I think they just fell victim to chasing the "foody" trend and lost sight of what was working so well for them. 

I hope they find their way soon. Would love to return to the good 'ol Jamms I remember.

Excellent food & service, thank you Roni! First time in on a Tuesday, a medical professional came in and took a seat at the counter, "hellos" & "hi" came from the wait team and they called him by name! Like I said excellent service, my home away from home!
1st time here and what a great visit it was. Food is delicious, prices are affordable and best of all THE staff is super cool and friendly.

I wrote a review about a month and a half ago for this restaurant. We had a disappointing experience. The Owner of the restaurant read my review and wasn't happy, so she invited us back for complimentary lunch or breakfast to try and make up for the experience I had. That is excellent customer service and really shows they care about the experience of their customers. 

We came back and the experience was better. We both ordered something different this time. I had the Wild West Burger and she had the French Toast. The burger was cooked as I liked it at. The chili that came with it was good. I tried the french toast and it was cooked great!

Here's what I've found in my two experiences here: They have a wonderful staff who are friendly and seem dedicated to customer service. The food is cooked very well. Everything is cooked exactly how it should be. But my problem is the food does not wow me. There isn't any thing unique or special about it. The food isn't bad, it's just not something worth 4 or 5 stars.
We had breakfast at Jamm's and enjoyed the hearty food served by the great attentive staff.  I had the bacon burger w seasoned fries...very good.

The food was great ...once we sat down. Make sure your whole party is there when you request a table. If you say a table you better have 3 present or you have to wait until they get there before you get seated. 
Frenchtoast was perfect, the best I had in a while. Eggs cooked to perfection and huge fluffy pancakes. The country fried steak was reminiscent of that served in my school cafeteria, terrible. Biscuits were perfect and the gravy was pretty good. I would go back but never have the country fried steak again. 
Our waitress was great

Chose this restaurant for Sunday breakfast based on other Yelp reviews.  Was not disappointed.  Excellent, reasonably priced food.  Friendly, attentive service.  Sticks of gum at the register are a nice touch.

Wasn't bad service. The pot bread was delicious but they messed up on my order. I asked for no tomatoes in my breakfast burrito but it came with a lot and the egg Benedict was just basically a hard boiled egg.

I love the feel of a local neighborhood restaurant with yummy coffee and pot of bread. The food is plentiful and it is easy to get seating. Sometimes, I take it to-go to have brunch with friends at home. It's worth stopping by if in the neighborhood. A local gem!

Food is always great. 20 years and counting. Service is excellent, no better place to have breakfast or lunch.
Tellem Fred sent ya!
They also advertise 10% off bill if you check in with Yelp.

Our restaurant divining rod pointed us from the airport to Jamms this morning. We enjoyed plates of comfort food served to us by Shirley whose friendly expertise and infectious laughter are worth a visit to this local cafe.

Staff is awesome mostly there at least 7-8 years though 2 newer females in front were less than pleasant- if we weren't regulars since 2003 & these 2 were my first impression we would have walked. 
A pathetic attitude from the cashier like she's hot shit does not match the great service the waitstaff provides. 
The food is fast & consistent- a bit over priced but we obviously haven't stopped driving 20min to get there for a reason
Try any omelette (or red velvet pancakes my sister in-law got today)

This is the best breakfast restaurant in Vegas! We come here EVERY time we're here!  Everything is delicious! Good variety of dishes! Try their "pot of bread". Today's choice: s'mores waffles! Very friendly and efficient staff!
Breakfast always the bomb at Jamms with the family. Fast service, friendly service and reasonable prices. Sandy is awesome!!!!!

This was my second time at Jamms and both were excellent.  Pleasant service and great food.  Highly recommend the Jamms French toast and don't leave without a pot of bread.  I prefer the raisin and cinnamon one.  I just wish it opened just a bit earlier since I'm always there for work and have to start too early to go all the time.

My  adult daughter and niece, mother in law, wife and I ate here while in Vegas.  Well worth the drive away from the strip.  Excellent food And service, full of locals.  Try the bread bowls.  Everyone  left full and happy while saying only good things  about this gem
I had the smores pancakes they were great. The orange juice tasted like orange juice from the stor
Great tasting food. Great service. Definitely recommend to anyone visiting Las Vegas.

I've eaten here quite a bit with my dad as he likes it but I think it's just an alright breakfast spot. If you sign up for their e-mail list you can get coupons for 10-15 percent off your bill or a free pot of bread.  Anyway I recommend ordering the Irish skillet and a pot of bread.

I still haven't been able to find a great breakfast spot in Vegas, i've been to Cracked Egg, Egg & I, Hash House A Go Go, Babycakes, The Bagel Cafe, Blueberry Hill, Pancake House, etc. I like The Bagel Cafe, Blueberry Hill and Pancake House out of all of those but those are all pretty expensive and the Pancake Houses in other states are better than the ones here for some reason. Hash House is the worst out of all of those.

First off, they are not a chain and I LOVE that!!

You must try the blueberry pot of bread. It is amazing. It is a special, so you have to catch them on the right week. Their plain pot of bread is just as good though.They have the best ham around.They grill it perfect! The owner is always there to greet you when you walk in.The waitresses are always friendly. I have never had a bad meal here. They are known for their pot of bread, so make sure to order one when you stop in!  Also, I think it is a cute touch that they offer you gum, instead of those red and white mints everybody gives you on the way out.

The service is amazing, the food is delicious, and they keep up with the cleanliness 

I always leave with a smile (:
If you want to feel like family, then come here (:

Wow, what a gem we found today. Sandy took  care of us ...friendly and great at what she does. Excellent food ... yummy ! 
My new favorite food spot! !!!

I do not usually write reviews, but I just had to review this place. The food here is DELICIOUS.  Did not have to wait long at all. I have to say the employees at this place are awesome......Shirley our waitress is one of the best I've seen. Will definitely be coming back to this place.
This place was absolutely fantastic and the service was wonderful. Great on my short Vegas visit!

Checked in here yesterday for some good home style food.  At least that's what all the reviews say, right?  Let's just start off by saying that they truly do treat you like family.  Service was very warm and they're genuinely glad to see you there.  I ordered the corned beef hash and eggs.  Great flavor and I absolutely loved the texture of all the caramelized onions and crispy corned beef hash.  Very good.  I also was curious to see what all the hype was about the Pots of bread.  Meh, it was ok, but to me, nothing to write home about.
Jamms is one of the best breakfast restaurants in Las Vegas---always friendly service and lots of choices of delicious food.
Best breakfast ever!!  Shirley made us laugh and had great recommendations. If you're close, don't miss this little gem.

Duuuude this place is awesome. I've been in Vegas 6 years and had never heard of it until today. Service was phenomenal, atmosphere is charming, like comfy grandmas house. Plenty of items to choose from on the menu, so we pigged out and ordered for 6 people. There were two of us. If you like bomb ass food, good service, and fair prices, go to Jamms. French toast fries. Need I say more?
Food is consistent, hot, tasty, and filling. Be sure to have the pumpkin pancakes.....a classic
Reuben Benedict and Chicken Fried Steak! Free Pot of Bread offer redeemed! Lovely people and place!

This was my first time dining at Jamms and I was very impressed! My party and I came on a Saturday morning. The wait time was about 20 minutes, which we expected for a weekend. We were seated in less than 20 minutes. 

The menu is huge! There was a ton of options and you can try many different items, which made it easier to decide. The 1st server came to our table and took our drink order. The drinks were brought back promptly. The 2nd server took a while to take our order. I could see that the server was busy, but an acknowledgement from the server would have been appropriate. The server took around order after about 10-15 minutes.

We ordered our meals and the famous pot of bread. That was absolutely delicious! It was fresh, warm, and tasteful. Our food arrived a little erratically. Myself and 3 others received our food while the 4th person had to wait another 5 minutes for his meal. We dug right in when we got our food, but felt bad that the other person had to wait.

The servers were very attentive with drink refills and pre-bussing our table. We received our check quickly and got cashed out fast.

Overall, I will definitely dine here again. The 1 star deduction is for the small wait time for our order to be taken and the wait time for our friend's food.

I would always see a line out the door for this place, so decided that it must be good! I had asked my friends about it and they warned me about how dirty it was. I figured that it couldn't be THAT bad, so I thought I'd give it a try. Such a bad idea!!! I ordered French toast, pretty hard to mess up. I couldn't even finish it. Our waitress ignored us completely and kept taking forever at her other tables, talking and laughing with them. 
Later that night I was so incredibly sick and throwing up. I will never go again.

Love eating here. Food is fresh and delicious. Staff are pleasant and courteous. Looks as if they have done some decorating. I know they have added new menu items. I like the new "tapas" plates. Can select variety without eating a lot.

Great service, really good food. Can't decide which omelet you want? Get a couple different ones on the small plate menu for a reduced price. Ingenious and delicious. You have to experience the "pot of bread".

Stopped here after a quick search before starting the drive back home. Sat at the counter and was quickly greeted and set up w coffee and water. Menu choices looked good. I tried the Denver potato pancake. Also started w the little pot o bread. Excellent! The entree was presented quickly and was very tasty indeed. This will be my new go to for breakfast away from the Strip.

I love this place for breakfast! Nothing fancy. Just a good neighborhood joint that never lets you down. Super friendly staff, great service, excellent food. They only do breakfast and lunch. Haven't tried lunch here yet, but it's sure to happen.
Great breakfast and all around meals for great prices. The servers are kind and prompt. So come and try it out. Tell them you know Fred TabronYou all want to come to my sisters

I am a breakfast person! It is my favorite meal so I try breakfast places all the time. I stumbled upon this place when looking for Sundays breakfast. First I went to babystacks but they had a 45 minute wait. 

Me and my boyfriend came here and there was no wait. 

I ordered the mushroom omelete which had tons of cheese :) and a bagel with cream cheese

The service was perfect and very helpful our waitress was lenore. 
Their coffee is excellent and we ended up getting a pot of bread (the nutella peanut butter one) sooo goood!!!

My boss and I came to this restaurant on our lunch hour, and we were dang impressed! It is a super cute mom and pop restaurant, and has a traditional American feel with delicious food. The cinnamon raisin bread pot was delicious. We both got a breakfastRito and some waffles to share. All was delicious! We definitely plan to return to this restaurant again for lunch!
we are here and loving it.  great food and friendly service.  the top breakfsst restaurant on my list.

This is our second time here and the food is great so we came back for seconds. However this time a girl in a red shirt greeted our table, brought drinks and we sat for about 5 to 10min in an empty restaurant. We flagged the girl in the red shirt from across the room (signaling we would like some kind of service) she just pointed to the front of the restaurant at our server. She could have easily walked over and let her know. Such a rude way to carrying on business especially since she was just standing there.

Was really  looking forward to my usual Irish skillet but about broke a tooth on a rock or pit the size of a small pea.  Luckily tooth was ok but did sent it back for a new skillet.  The waitress was very apologetic and told the manger what happened.

The one star rating was not for the hard pit in my skillet but for not even a visit from the manager or an offer to give a discount.  This was totally unacceptable service in my opinion.  I didnt expect to get a free meal but I did expect the manager to at least come over and apologize, but NADA.

Won't be coming back for awhile, too many other good breakfast places around town.

The corned beef hash is the best in town!!!  Fresh, not canned.  Once you eat the cbh here you won't be able to have it anywhere else!!!  Also depending on the flavor of the pot of bread could be good or too much.  But anything with chocolate is so good!

If I were asked by my friends where is a good place  to eat, I would say Jamms. Nice attitudes, nice busyness and workers moving around, lots of good attention and service, great food. Made my day. Great waitress named Sandy.

Went there for a late breakfast with the family.  Place was "Jamming", but only had to wait about 15 minutes to be seated.  Service was friendly as always.  I had the Jamms Special, with a cinnamon raison pot of bread and it was devine.  The pot of bread was mouthwatering and the omelet was huge.  They have some the best house coffee in town.  Will be going back again.

If you are staying in Las Vegas I would highly recommend leaving the strip and driving to this restaurant. The service is excellent. The French Toast tastes great. Coffee was good. They do bring milk for cream so it you want the classic cream taste ask for the half and half. The server asked me if I want a fresh cup of coffee with the cream. I noticed a lot of regulars and locals coming in. The hostess was very polite and cheerful. She also wondered on how we found the place. It looks like positive reviews are bringing people in. On the way out I noticed all of the social network ratings including Foursquare, Yelp, and Trip Advisor. Google needs to advertise Places.
Nice place to grab breakfast.  Of couse got the pot of bread at it was good.  Eggs Benedict hit the spot. Will try this place again when I'm in the LV
Super friendly staff and a menu I look forward to continuing to explore!

If you are contemplating eating here, just do it! You won't be disappointed! The pot of bread is so flavorful and their omelettes are stuffed to the brim with deliciousness!  Service is outstanding and the atmosphere really feels like home. I highly recommend!

Nuh not impressed with this place. Wait was to long service was ok. Food? Oh well I have had better food at other places.
Their favorite pot of bread they say its so delicious was just meh. Weekly choice was cherry cream cheese, nothing to rave about to be honest.
Coffee was just normal cup of coffee. (Free refill) 
The portions are big sizes but I dont care about the size I rather have small portion but tasty instead of huge size but no taste.
Waitress was nice, front people were nice, but wont be going back.

The only reason I joined yelp was to tell everyone how horrible, crapy everything about that place was. I have actually been going there for years, and have noticed how service, and the food was going down hill. Everything is greasy. I mean everything. Today was crowded I will give them that. But the service sucked. And to top it all off I ordered a sandwich to take home with me. Now I know leaving it behind on the table in a doggie bag was my fault. I had returned no more than b a few minutes later to find out that they threw it away. I could deal with that.  But the way the they handled the situation with such a no care in the world to bad so sad attitude. Will guarantee that I will never go back to that hole in the wall sleazy place. You want a good clean classy place to have some breakfast. Go to the new York beagle cafe on buffalo.  You would never want to go back to jams agian.
Decent food at a decent price. Friendly staff who remember you is always a plus.

Had breakfast with my wife. Had Joe s omelet was grest
I hssd the breakfast burrito. 
Devyn was great!!!!!!!!

Feel Good Food Establishment:

Every now and again Life can you hit you with an upper-cut. Whether you took it on the chin like a champ or whether you saw stars and started bawling like a baby - There are places in the world you can go that will make you feel better about that punch to the face you just absorbed. 
-Mine is Jamms.

Friendly smiles as soon as you walk in the door and an atmosphere to match.
The menu items include Breakfast and Lunch options. I'm slowly working through them.

As of yet: French Toast: with the option of with or without crunchy cornflake topping. Additional options:  How bout Nutella French Toast, Apple Cinnamon French Toast, too name a few

You Like Waffles? Jamms like waffles too... so much they make a WAFFLE PIZZA!

Omelette anyone They have over 10 different types.  

A new item: Their breakfast burrito that will make you question all others.

This place is real a Gem.  
After a French Press coffee and Banana Fosters pancakes I always leave feeling much better than how I came in.  That is the magic of Jamms.

Don't believe me? 
Order their Pot' O Bread for the day and you too will be saying,"What Punch to the Face?"

They get busy, and rightfully so, but it is worth the short wait for the quality service and food you will experience.

Jamm On ;-)






.

So far the best breakfast we've had in Vegas! So many omelettes to choose from! I had the sandy omelette (bacon & avocado) with the cinnamon raisin pot of bread.  Crispy bacon, perfect amount of avocado. A healthy portion, I was Almost able to finish it.  My company had the spinach florentine, beautifully poached eggs.  And their coffee cups are BIG.  Made me wonder why all restaurants don't use big cups?
Staff here moves fast, tables turn quick and food flies out of the kitchen.  I never had to ask for a refill someone was constantly filling our coffees and waters. Glad we got here early a line started quickly but I can't imagine anyone waited more than 10 minutes. 
I was so satisfied with my meal but when I saw a waitress carrying some French toast covered in glazed apples I almost wanted to sit down and eat again!  And then I heard there was a chocolate caramel pot of bread.. So much more I want to try! We will definitely be back again during our stay here. Also, There was a 10% discount for posting on social media! Great place.

First visit today to this restaurant and it is awesome. I cannot believe we have not been there before.  My hubby wanted breakfast and I wanted lunch.  Hubby ordered corned beef hash and said it was homemade and delicious.  I had a tuna melt which was very yummy and so filling. Hugh portions and the service is excellent.  We will definitely be back as there was so much on the menu that i want to try.

What can I say! Well, to start off, Jamm's feels like home. I come from Northern California and so you can say that im spoiled with tasty and fufilling food with a very homemade touch. I feel that restaurants lack the "at home" type of feeling, Jamm's is definetely one of those establishments. As soon as you walk in your greeted with a huge smile and welcome. I waited less than 2 minutes for a seat. Right away we were asked what would we love to drink. Service right away! 

The waitress with an absolute contagious smile, was very sweet and helpful. We did not wait for our food no longer than 15 minutes! Awesome, because I get so anxious when it comes to food. I ordered the Sandy Omelette (which I reccomend), DELICIOUS! Goodness, it was GOOD, hey did not skim on the portions of bacon,avacado, cheese and tomatoes. 

I strongly reccomend this restaurant!
Jamms is da Bomb!!!  The food here is so Ono "good"  today we had Philly Cheese Steak and eggs Benedict.  Both very good Wonderful!!!

One of my favorite breakfast spots. My favorite waitress is Shirley...she's full of life, very friendly, happy and a great waitress. 
I'm a regular here :)

Food is decent but service was an epic failure. I've been here before & I've had to wait 20-30 mins for a table even when people were done eating & just chitchatting. I've never had an issue waiting because I'll have my turn. 

Today a friend and her daughter joined me for breakfast and before I finished my food they brought me a to go box.  They brought us the bill twice & started cleaning off our table before we were done. Then as my friend's daughter was still working on her pancakes they asked if we were going to order anything else if not then they needed our booth for someone else.  WTF? 

Mind you we were there for less than an hour & the people behind me were there before us & were still there after us. No one asked them to leave... such a discriminating feeling. I didn't know that this sit down establishment had a time limit on seating.  Rude service is putting it lightly.  We'll never return!

Me and the wife's favorite breakfast spot. There French toast is very good. But by far the best thing about jamm's is there weekly pots of bread. Each week a new kind. Chocolate coconut and salted caramel were my two favs. Would recommend to anyone who's hungry

We live on the other side of town and are willing to drive to Jamms because it's so tasty!  It's small, so be forewarned that a wait is always imminent! They're quick in turning people around though!  The pot o' bread is good, but their lunches are AMAZING!!!

Erika's small plates is the greatest thing ever for a breakfast restaurant. There are so many wonderful menu options this gives you the opportunity to try multiple omelets without the sides getting you full. Sandy is a great waitress and always friendly.

If you like omelettes, this is your place. If you like old-school genuine hustling service, then this is your place. Don't expect any bells and whistles, nothing "fu-fu" about Jamms, but the "Sandy" omelette was one of the best I've ever had. If you're in Vegas, go have an omelette at Jamms, you won't be disappointed!!

Went here on a Monday morning and the place was pretty busy, still lots of seating available, but a good first impression. I sat down and my drink order was taken immediately. I looked over the menu, knowing of course I was getting the pancakes!! My waitress came and took my order and asked what I was drinking. She came back with another diet soda and a caraf!! Scored some major points there cause I guzzle soda!! I ordered the home fries as well bc the pics looked sooo yummy!! I was dissapointed that they came out as little chopped up bits of seasoned potatoes with peppers and onions...did I order the wrong thing? I'm confused on what the potatoes are in the yelp review pics that look like they are super crispy on top, almost looked like a mound if mashed- are they the breakfast potatotes? The guy next to me had a dif style but they still looked shredded. Either way the pancakes were amazing, little crispy on the side and barely needed any syrup they were so tasty. They are def the buttery version as opposed to a dryer type like at maple tree, cracked egg and weiss deli. I will def be back to try and get those potatoes. Very friendly atmosphere....would have been 5 stars had I gotten the right homefries!

A - OK pretty much sums it up.  I had a grilled cheese so it wasn't too hard to mess up.  Service at our table was good, but the hostess seemed a little rude.  We called ahead and they said there was no line, when we arrived 5 minutes later there were probably 5 or 6 parties waiting.  Could it have been bad timing and all of us arrived at once?  Possible, but unlikely.  

We got a free pot of bread with our Yelp checkin but I wasn't too impressed with that either...  it's bread.  Am I missing why this is such a novel thing?

This place is my favorite breakfast spot in Vegas. I really like how they make you feel very welcome and at home. Ive never been disappointed here. The foods is always what i expect and the staff are very friendly. Most of the time there is about a 10-20 min wait but it's more then worth it. If looking for a great breakfast/lunch spot then this is for you. If you are just visiting or live locally you don't want to pad this special place up.

super delicious and huge portions. We checked in on yelp and got a free pot o bread (delicious) and posted a photo to social media with their tag and saved on our bill! Fast service, bomb food and discounts. Loved it

Break away from boring strip breakfast and come over here.  This place is an absolute gem. You must try the Jamms French Toast.  I do not even like French Toast that much and this is good.  Sandy is among the best servers I have had.  I had not been there in 4 months and she remembered our names.  I promise I am not just saying that because Sandy's omelette is the best egg on the menu.  Cannot say enough about the pot of bread.  Try whatever the special is.  I have never gone wrong.  Worth the wait, but if you avoid weekends from 9:30-noon you should be fine.

Trying something new off of yelp recommendations never fails! This place has excellent service, number one. And the food is an even tie. We all had something different, and every dish was delicious. Our waitress was so kind to tell us the specialties to help us decide. A little wait, but SO worth it!

Good breakfast. Sometimes a long wait and it's not soooo good that I would wait in that line again. But the pancakes were fluffy and the eggs were done the way I like. The waitress was attentive and pleasant. The price was fair.

One of my favorite breakfast/lunch restaurants!
The service is always excellent and I absolutely love the pots of bread with the cream cheese icing!!!!

My very first yelp review. Had to do it, because if you haven't tried jamms, you're missing out. 

It's located on rainbow and charleston by the albertsons. Blends in well, I've lived in vegas my whole life and just discovered this place recently. 

My girlfriend and I have only gone for breakfast a handful of times, and each time we were impressed with the price and quality of food. I got the bumper omlette; fluffy eggs, mushrooms, broccoli, cream cheese, and topped with hollandaise sauce. I added bacon to it. AMAZING!! The service was pretty good, especially considering how busy it was. My girlfriend had a pretty customized order, and they had no problem with it. 

I would recommend Jamm's to anyone who likes breakfast food, and is tired of Dennys and ihop. Be sure to go early though, as they are only open for breakfast and lunch and close at 2pm!

P.S. You have not lived until you get a "pot of bread" from these guys!!!

Best corned beef hash I've ever tasted! Even the English muffins were amazing! Also had the pumpkin cream cheese pot of bread which was also really good. Service was amazing! Definitely want to come back to try more dishes.

It is our first visit here and I have to say that the pot of bread is sooooo good, you can pretty much have it any time of the day  we were looking for some place near us for breakfast and came across Jamms, love the setting, it's very homely and old fashioned like, love it!

Great food & service! I am definitely returning!
Have eaten breakfast & lunch there. Both were delicious.

We went on the 8th, around 10am. Not to busy, waited about 5 minutes for a table. Thought we scored. Wrong! We were seated and the buser came over and took our drink order. And that was that! 20 minutes later without a server ever coming by our table, we paid for our drinks and left. So I can't review the food. Service sucked.  Doubt will go back there again, especially since we went out of our way to go there, only to be ingored.

We went to Jamm's for a late morning breakfast. Never having been there before, and new to the state, we didn't know what to expect. We were greeted by a very pleasant lady and seated at a booth. Immediately we were served our coffee. A very nice waitress came to take our order as soon as we got the coffee. After she answered some questions she put our order in. They have seasoned home fries, and sweet potato fries.i had the sweet potato fries. They sprinkle them with powdered sugar, they were yummy. They serve them in a little fryer basket. They also have the original bread bowl. It's bread made in a little muffin cup, the bowl. They have white, wheat, and cinnamon raisin. I loved the cinnamon raisin. They didn't keep my coffee cup full, but did give me a second cup before I left. Over all, the food was great,very original presentation, very pleasant ambiance, service was good with hardly any wait. It's a place you want to return to. Oh, they serve breakfast any time of day. Price for 2 breakfasts for us was $22.00, but you could spend more if you want. Great place to take friends.  I will be a regular.  Dan
This place is hands down the best place to go and have breakfast in Vegas. Everyone is so friendly and the food is extremely fresh!!
It's good food.... Service could be much better. I've been here for about 35 minutes.... And I'm extremely parched lol. Other than that.... Definitely stop by!!!

This was another pick based on good Yelp reviews and it did not disappoint.  Again coming in late I expected a delay, but we were seated within 10 minutes.  The service was prompt and the staff was polite and helpful.  I had a standard sausage and egg breakfast which isn't too exciting. But being gluten intolerant I don't have a lot of choices that aren't some combination of meat, eggs and potatoes.  Still, it was well done and the server let me make substitutions for the bread item.  My wife had the chicken fried steak and eggs, and a "Orange Creamcicle" bread pot.  I was jealous because the bread pot looked like it would be really good.  Additionally she said the entire meal was delicious.  If you don't have to pick and choose like I do, their menu has a huge variety of choices.  Since they were mostly bread items I didn't spend much time with it, but they had an insert menu that offered small portions for less money so you can sample a large variety of their offerings without ordering multiple meals or eating off someone else's plate.  For the sake of the review I should have paid more attention to exactly what they called it, but this would be a good place to go to sample a variety of breakfast offerings.

Great recommend on the potato cakes by our busboy (busman), Jose. The food was slow getting to us but good when we got to it. The waitress was slow in responding to anything we asked for, but Jose was Johnny on the spot, and has a great personality. He really should be moved up to waiter.
The home pot of bread is so delicious!!!  The service was great and everyone so super friendly!  We had a variety of breakfasts and everyone thought theirs was the best!

Great food! Wonderful service. The pot of bread is unique and delicious. A bit off the beaten path in LV but beyond worth it!  Denver omelette was scrumptious, filled generously. The beverages were flowing, your glass never empty. If you love breakfast, you will love Jamms.

Went to jams today and I've always enjoyed it, but today was different first off my chicken fried steak breakfast was not good it and when I told the waitress I did not like it she did not care didn't even try to rectify anything very disappointed on a good note my husbands burrito was good.

I've been going here since I was a little kid (I'm 21) and I introduced my boyfriend to Jamms, HE LOVES IT. This is more than just a place to eat, but more like a full on old school experience. Everyone is personable, so friendly, and the service is great. Fresh coffee refills. The food... MAGIC. This is the spot for home made yummy breakfast and lunch, and it never fails to disappoint. I'm a picky eater and they have something for everyone! Classic foods, as well as creative spins on things. Portions are hearty, and I never leave feeling hungry or over stuffed. The best part... it's not expensive. My boyfriend and I paid 20$ for the two of us to eat, which makes the experience even better. 10/10 would recommend!!

Classic and reliable breakfast food provided by friendly and responsive staff. The pot of bread is a fun diversion from the usual-usual. The Country Skillet was delicious and well balanced. There was a good amount of meat/egg/potato mixed together (some skillets at other places are 70% potato and few ingredients). The scrambled eggs were fresh and fluffy. Their omelets are also hefty. The Sandy Omelet packs in a lot of flavor and should satisfy your hunger.

All in all, an easy and pleasant experience.
This place is great. The people who work there are super sweet and the food is awesome! Defiantly try the pot of bread it delicious.
Cute place.  Plenty of food and plenty of choices.  Sandy is an excellent waitress.  Very efficient and friendly. Pots of bread a nice touch.

This is probably one of my favorite breakfast joints on the west side. Don't let the size of the restaurant fool you. As small as it is, they make up for it by serving generous portions! 

The service is top notch and even though it was pretty busy since it was a Sunday morning, our waitress was super attentive.

The food came out quickly and tasted amazing. I'll definitely be back for more breakfast food because their they have such a big breakfast menu.

Best local breakfast spot in Vegas. Massive portions, tasty pot-of-bread and limitless coffee. Son had the S'mores pancake, and it was ridiculous (in a good way). I come here at least once every time I'm in town, and that's at least 4-5 times a year.

We love Jamms!  Take mom there every morning after sleeping in the hospital for the last few weeks next to my dad and she loves it. Fresh coffee Fresh Hot Food every time without fail and they always have a smile. My 18month old loves Shay! & we do too! Excellent Friendly service and when there is a line it goes so fast the staff have it down to a science.
Great breakfast place.  Wide variety of omelets and entrees.  Good service, fast seating.

Jamm's was awesome! ! Our server was very friendly and our food was fresh, hot and very tasty!! I was surprised that there was a bit of a waiting list on a Wednesday around 11am; however,  now I know why. This place is worth it. We will be back soon and often!!!

The interior is very worn down. I felt a bit like being in an old bowling alley, but without the ambiance.  The floor was so dirty it's probably criminal, and needs new carpets badly. Outside on the window they proudly present themselves as "best of Vegas", but  not since 2006, and those 9 years show...

The 'thing' I ate was featured on a TV show, and was interesting, but poorly executed. It had almost no taste, just a lot of "meh". The fries were dusted with powdered sugar, which made no sense, and mostly made a mess. It needs spices, herbs, crunch, and more to salvage.

Price would have been OK, if the food had been OK. Service was fine, although there was some ruckus in the kitchen that was rather noisy. I had to ask for a refill, it wasn't offered, and I got it just before I left. 

In a couple of years, unless they get their act together, this will be on Restaurant Impossible...

I'm a sucker for breakfast food. If only the appropriate time for breakfast was like... you know, 4pm... I'd be great.

So on the rare occasion that I AM up early for breakfast, I kind of like to reward myself for it. And as I was driving from my bank, I see this little restaurant in the plaza, and it's been rated Best of the LVR-J for 4 years, and it's only open until 3. Well I have to try it, I thought.

Best discovery on the Westside in a long time. The atmosphere is cozy, like your mom's kitchen (if she had an industrial kitchen). Knick-knacks and country sayings adorn the walls, and the staff treats you like you're in their house. Try the Texas Omelette (with chili con carne and cheddar cheese) or if you're daring, the White Castle Omelette (with ground beef and grilled onions -- yes, like a Slider!). They're famous for their "pots of bread." It's soft and doughy, and if you order the Cinnamon Raisin pot of bread, it's like eating a cinnamon roll.

They also have lunch items, which I'm sure I'll try someday, when I can get past the breakfast pages without choosing something.

After 26 years in Vegas, I've eaten a lot of breakfasts at a lot of places at all hours of the day and night. Jamm's remains my all-time favorite. Coffee is always hot and strong, food is always delicious, and the service is always excellent. Toast schmoast...get the famous Pot of Bread!!

Really great.  The corned beef hash was delicious, my wife's fruit side was totally fresh, and the pot o' breads were soft and fresh. The POB is an individual baked bread the size of a large muffin. It comes plain white (what we had), or cinnamon raisin, or weekly special. I can't wait to try them. The restaurant is cute and homey and the staff is happy and friendly. I'll be back soon, especially to try "The Jamminator".

Seriously soooo good! Has a small diner feel with delicious and creative dishes, but without the pretentiousness or price of alot of brunch places. It's honestly my favorite breakfast place in Las Vegas.  Feels like a hidden gem.
The corn beef hash is tasty. Service is a little slow trying to get their attention. But other than that it's a basic breakfast.
Try their piña colada pot o' bread. It's a nice craving quencher if you want something sweet without having to eat pancakes drenched in syrup.

My family and I have eaten there several times now and have never had a bad meal.  Make sure you go when you're hungry because the portions will fill you up for sure.  Be prepared to wait in line on the weekends, especially Sunday.  The line does move pretty quickly though and it is worth the wait.  It is pretty small inside so it does get a bit noisy, not a huge deal for us.  The staff is always warm and friendly and makes you feel welcome.

Wow - just noticed the last time i reviewed this place was in 2008 !!! I'm guessing i've been to JAMMS at least 10 times since then.  I'm also guessing the exact same employees work there now since i first tried JAMMS in 2008.

As the gf and I walked in we debated whether or not the place was freshened up with new paint - i generally don't look at decor but given our upcoming move to a new house and being bombarded by all the design/decor ideas coming from the gf for the new house, i've suddenly taken a closer look.

As usual, the service is spot on - water and coffee at our table within a minute, Flo taking our order within minutes and the food served within minutes ... honest ! 

Gf standard breakfast - veggie omelet - no seasoning, no oil , packed with 4-6 veggies, and of course, egg whites - given the large number of veggies, her food usually costs between $12-$15 at the various breakfast places we visit.  Surprisingly, no extra charge for the garden of veggies that the gf requested - but a $1.50 upcharge for the fruit side.  I believe her omelet cost $10.  She proclaims JAMMS is the only breakfast spot that consistently prepares her omelet correctly.

My ham and cheese omelet ?  All good - i like that they put the cheese on top the omelet AND inside the omelet.  

IF we lived closer to JAMMS ( and with the upcoming move, we will ) I suspect this will be one of our top breakfast spots.

pics included
The food was very good! Loved the Pot of Bread and Sandy Omelet!! The coffee was a bit of a bummer, watered down. The service was fabulous and prices were reasonable. We will definitely go back!

My girlfriend and I have been here a few times and everything is great here. Last time I went I got the s'mores French toast and it was awesome. Also customer service here is excellent especially the busboy who gets u drinks, he was great.

I would have normally given a much better review but my father and I went by there just a bit ago today - I get that they close at 3 and I'm not trying to be one of "those people", it was a few minutes before 3pm when we arrived and I literally just wanted an order of biscuits and gravy (being 32 weeks pregnant I had my mind set on what I wanted). My father and I weren't looking for the whole sit down and be served experience, just the biscuits and gravy which we would have gladly taken to go if it had even been an option but the woman at the counter quickly snapped that they were closed/done for the day. 

Fortunately there was a knowledgeable patron just outside that noticed I was pregnant, even he was a little surprised they wouldn't allow us to order anything, not even to go. He suggested we try Hash House A Go-Go, that's where my father and I are right now and the baby and I got our biscuits and gravy so we're happy again.

Breakfast is my favorite meal and I have lived in Vegas a long time now and have yet to visit this spot until recently. The pot of bread is delicious. My omelette was stuff full with huge pieces of broccoli. Would have liked a lil less cheese in it but it's easy to eat around it. Coffee was good for a breakfast spot and the server was very attentive.

Fun, local place!
LOVE the french press coffee and the pot o' bread!
We had to wait a bit for a table - we knew that was a good sign!
I don't live far from this place and WILL be back.

This place has gone downhill. The first couple of times I went here, the food was great. So was the service. But my last couple of times eating here, the food was lackluster. The service is still good, but there 'pot of bread' was cold & bland when brought to me. Boyfriend ordered the chiliquiles & the chips were all soggy.

There's always a wait, with good reason. Delightful, home style breakfast in a divey little strip mall. Get the pot of bread; you won't regret it. Great French toast, hash browns, and pancakes. Good service, good prices.
Down home food and people here! No games just what you came for with a healthy sprinkle of hospitality, absolutely love this place.

Looked up local restaurants to eat at on visit. Saw jamms had great reviews. It's a small and cozy place. Friendly staff. I had french toast fries which were good to the taste buds.  And their pot of bread was fresh out the oven, hot and soft!

I will admit that I feel that my experience here was subpar because of my own choices. I should have stuck with ordering a breakfast dish. 

I will say that this is the setting of a real diner. The restaurant isn't fancy or really decorated. The staff are warm. The food options are what you would expect at a diner. 

Our server was wonderful. She was attentive but never rushed us, which I really appreciated. 

I ordered the chicken panini. I'm not convinced the chicken was cooked all the way, so I pretty much peeled it out of the sandwich. The bread was far too crisp, and I am pretty certain there was not any pesto on it. I was severely disappointed. The potato wedges were good, but they're like any you can buy frozen. 

Overall, I won't be back. Sorry, Jamms.

So...after the servers stopped kissing all the regulars, I was able to nom on some very delicious food. 

Prices reasonable. Food delicious! Servers VERY friendly. 

On a side note, I would highly suggest that the owners expand into the vacant space next door. I would also get rid of the booths and replace them with small tables. It didn't make sense to me that two people sit in a 6-8 person booth when the restaurant is busy.
Best breakfast around town!  Shirley was such a joy!!  If your an outta towner head this way!
Solid experience, a mom and pop style breakfast place. Not the best breakfast I've ever had but also not the worst, everything was good, friendly staff as well.

I live in the Dallas area but have family in Las Vegas so I'm here several times a year. No visit is complete without a visit to Jamms! Everything I've ever ordered is fantastic and the service is fast and friendly. What more could you ask for?
Excellent alternative to Vegas buffets.  The service is friendly and professional.  The food is delicious.  Worth the time to find it.

I plan on coming here for almost every special breakfast meal. The food is always good, the service is always good, and I haven't been here and become disappointed. It's an old fashioned little joint where their main interest is being the best service possible. I ordered the French Toast sandwich and was amazed at the quality of the Jamm's signature french toast! On top of that, I never had to ask for coffee. And the best thing about this entire place is that it's relatively the same price as Ihop or Denny's.

Nice little place for breakfast. The place was packed Saturday morning but it only took about 15 to seat 5 people. The menu is huge. It took us awhile to make our decisions because it all sounded good. We went with omelets, pot of bread....of course, a breakfast burrito & apple stuffed French toast. The only minor complaint was the French toast was a little too sweet. The pot of bread is worth every calorie!
Really delicious food, good service and clean atmosphere, highly recommended. Pot of bread was awesome

I have been coming to this place for a few years now and always send family and friends that come and visit from out of town as my favorite local spot. Their pot of bread is amazing! However, lately the service has not been the same, not as friendly as usual and very slow. They don't offer the pot of bread or even mention it unless you ask for it.  Definitely going to stop referring people over here because it is not quite the same.

so hard to decided what to order since everything looks good!   We shared a mini Sandy omelet and smores waffles.  Both were awesome but the omelet was to die for.... lots of bacon.  And we each had a pot of bread...I had the cinnamon apple....yum!!!

Go try it no matter where you're staying - best on your first day so you can come here every day after that.
LOVE the pot of bread. Also they have nutella!
The earl grey tea was not so good, but the rest makes up for it.
On the weekends (we went on friday and saturday - had to wait only on saturday) you might have to wait but it's worth it.

6/20 just had breakfast here Veggie Omelet was tasty. Ham and Cheese Omelet was ok. Server and cook did a fine job pretty speedy.. We will be back for more because Im happy... I approve this message J K KUHL...

One of my favorite places for breakfast.

One house special is the "Eggs Benedict" - of which there are several varieties (including one that is served with a waffle rather than with an English muffin). They are all good.

The house coffee is Illy brand, which is an awesome way to start the day.

Prices are fair for what you get. The food is delicious.
Do not miss the "Pot of Bread" - fresh, hot white bread served in ... a pot ... what else?

Also, it is just a few steps away from the Dead Poet Bookstore - Vegas'  largest and best used book emporium. Plan on spending the rest of your morning there.

This place can rival Babystacks, and they are just as busy as Babystacks!  While Babystacks has their red velvet pancakes, Jamms has their pot bread!  Not only in plain but you can choose from cinnamon raisin and the special of the week.  And this week was Spice and More...which I will not disclose the detail of it but all I will say is, you must head on over there and try it!

I ended up ordering the ordering Babalama omelet instead of the Sandy omelet, as there was there was the  SOUR CREAM in the Sandy's omelet.  But the rest same, loaded with bacon, avocado, tomatoes, and melted Cheddar cheese.  OMG, it was so delish!  I ate so fast that  I ate so fast my tummy was telling me to slow down!  Pot bread comes with pot bread already and your choice of potato fries or hash-browns.  I choice the hash-browns.  

The rest of my part choose the chicken fried steak with three eggs, your choice how preparation, and a Provencal Cheese omelet with fresh diced tomatoes, spinach and provolone cheese.  

This is definitely a place worth trying and repeating all over again!  Great staff and your coffee is always full!  CAUGHT'CHA READING!!!
Signature omelet and Sandy omelet.  Comparable to Black Bear Diner.

I left my hotel at the Wynn Encore (awesome hotel) and all of the splendors of the adult "bathing pool" because I had seen this place with Corn Flake french toast on the Food Network and had to try it (I make this at home). I took a surprisingly lengthy (twss) and expensive round trip cab ride way out on Rainbow rd where you could still kinda see the strip but it was still $30 away. Anyway, after passing the strip mall where this place sits a few times, cabbie found it and I settled up to the counter in a surprisingly empty restaurant (well it was about 3pm on a weekday). A very friendly waitress greeted me and the french toast I ordered was well worth the journey. If you haven't had corn flake french toast before, this is a good place to try it. Perfectly cooked on some good bread and quite tasty. The corn flakey crunch adds so much to the french toast experience, you may never make french toast the same again. Awesome.

Pretty good service they were nice I didn't have to bother her for our beverages to be refilled our meal was made in a reasonable amount of time and the food was very good also well worth visiting when u want a nice breakfast or brunch dates or arrangements
Hanging out at Jann's with my favorite girl and glad we made the choice to hang because we were greeted by our beautiful friend Kim who is always the hostess with the mostess!!!
An amazing experience.. we drove from southern highlands just to eat at this place and so far I'm not disappointed
Food came out in 10 mins, nothing was fresh. Bread is cold & stale. VERY disappointing.
Great service always nice the pot bread is great and love the cream cheese spread so good

This is a great place for a person who wants to have some of all the breakfast foods, they have these great little "tapas" red plates where you can order a small amount of each thing you want. They also have specialty homemade breads every day.  Very good and very short wait.

This is a great place for Breakfast! The decor is ho-hum but the food makes up for it, as does the great service and friendly staff. The omelets are huge! And come with choice of potatoes and pot bread ( super yummy ) or English muffin or toast for around 9 bucks! I went there with my husband daughter brother and dad. For all of us with drinks and coffee was about 56 bucks...a bargain if you ask me =) We left happy and full. I suggest the pot bread french toast...mmm.
Great service, food and atmosphere! If you like French toast get the Jamms French toast it has little bits of cornflakes on them, it's amazing

Jamms is always a great choice! Weekends are busy so expect a line but worth the wait! My favorite it the Jamms signature omelette other goodies are country Benedict and Corn Beef Hash is out of this world! Good fresh OJ!

I like the atmosphere. It's sort a place you would want to walk to in your neighborhood, grab breakfast, and read the newspaper. 
Jamm's has been a voted favorite for awhile and I can see why. But there is always room for improvement. 
On the first trip, I ordered the Provencal omelet. It came with spinach, tomatoes, and cheese. The omelet was very soggy probably because of the main ingredients, but it should never be presented to the customer in the way that it was. It looked more like soup. I have to add, I never appreciate places that put a slap of cheese on top to melt. It tastes better when inside the blanket of egg. 

The pot of bread, which this place is known for is a cool idea. However, if they want to make a pot of gold serving the carb in a cup, they need to perfect the recipe. It's dry. 

Second trip, I ordered the turkey melt on texas toast. It was good. Just make sure you ask for dry toast if you don't like it to be buttered up. 

This place is one of the better breaksfast joints in town. With a few quick improvements it could be even better. 

3 1/2 stars.
Didn't care too particularly for the food. Pot of bread isn't what I thought, too much hype.
I've been coming here for over 18 years. Love it, best breakfast ever. People are always nice there

I love this place.  I have been here for breakfast and lunch.  However, no matter when I come in I rarely deviate from the delicious homemade biscuits and gravy.  Absolutely to die for!  I highly recommend!

Jamms has the best chicken soup in the world!  : )  The owners are extremely friendly and so are the waitresses.  They always remember that i drink ice tea with extra lemon and always go the extra mile!

It's delicious! It feels like a diner that cares. TRY anything with corned beef in it (Reuben, amazing! Or the Hash).. Chicken BLT waffle sandwich was a treasure as well. Shirley was our waitress and she was attentive and friendly. The atmosphere is very comfortable and welcoming. Food came out fast and hot. Overall a great experience. Definitely coming back
Great food. (Not so much for veggies). Recommend having the tapas style to try all as the portions are massive and yummy.
I love this place their bacon is to die for, and their jams French toast is amazing. You can't forget about the sausage it was fantastic.

This is a wonderful country style cafe where you can get a good meal.  The staff is friendly and helpful.  My son and I went here because of the reviews and we have noticed the long lines on the weekends.  The decor is what you would expect from a country style cafe.  The food was good.  The french toast sticks were great.  My son really enjoyed them.  I had a healthly omlet which was good, not amazing, but good enough to go back again.
Great "home-cooking" restaurant with enough unique dishes to keep you interested.  Staff is always friendly and helpful.  Love it.
Pina Colada French Toast was delicious! Rueben Omelet was delicious! Staff was so customer friendly. Loved it!
One of my favorite places for a great breakfast! Great service great food. Potbread is the bomb.com!

No words can describe how much I love this place!! Went here on a recent trip to the area, I was only in town for 4 days and had to go back twice! Growing up in a small town I always miss the breakfast place where everyone knows everyone and the servers know your order as soon as you walk in. This is that place!! The food is simple and classic.... except for the POT O BREAD!! Such a simple idea, and yet so good!!

I can't believe in the years I've been coming here I have never reviewed Jamm's. This spot has been voted Best of LV numerous times and for great reason. I have never had anything here except breakfast, regardless of the time of day. Their Irish Skillet is to die for, potatoes, corn beef, bell peppers, eggs and cheese. It's definitely my go to meal. I've also had the Jamm's French toast (coated in crunched corn flakes) and a few of their breakfast sandwiches. I have never been disappointed and will always come back!!

I want to go back to Vegas NOW!
There are ways to tell if I'm having a good meal. One of them being is that I will moan a la Meg Ryan Sleepless in Seattle. I met up here with a woman who I consider to be a second mother. It had been more than 15 years since I had seen her and this is where she chose to eat. Thank you mama Cheryl!!

The place is small, but what it lacks in size it makes up for in great service and food. Our waitress was a sweetheart! I ordered the cinnamon pot of bread and the corned beef hash breakfast. My hubby ordered the French Toast breakfast.

DELICIOUS. 
ORGASMIC even.

I need to go back to Vegas, nao!
Not bad for a breakfast place. Very friendly staff.

Very good! We had breakfast everything hot and yummy, even the syrup, For my french toast that was nice with vanilla and just the right amount of pieces (4). Bacon thin sliced and not over cooked, perfect~
   Coffee is in a generous mug and they are asking for refills promptly.
   All servers and staff quite friendly. The pot of bread a nice option and 1 is definatly  enough for 2 people.
   We live in Henderson so this was a bit far for us, but it was with the drive and if we are on the area would surly return.

Went in for their well-known omelets, but ended up with the french toast...and absolutely no regrets! My friend had one of the skillets, and that was a lot of food!  The lunch menu looks just as good, will have to try it. 

The place was busy, but we got seated quickly, and the service was good. Basic ambiance, but plenty of parking (strip mall) and easy to find. Will definitely put it in the rotation.

Come for breakfast or stop in for lunch. The food will be just as delicious no matter when you stop in for a bite. If you love sweets, this place is perfect. The pots of bread change in flavor weekly, but my absolute favorite is the cinnamon raisin! My husband can't make up his mind whether he like the Irish skillet or the steak omelet. Little to no waiting for a seat, and the food is nice and hot when it comes out.
4 stars for service. It's a little slow.

The only reason I gave then 4 instead of 5 is because sometimes you have to wait more than 30 minutes, outside. Tough w a baby in arms!
Food is great, staff are wonderful including the bus boys.

A good friend who lives around the area recommended this place and I'm glad we did come to this place. The food was really good and tasty and filled us up with the right amount of food. The service was good and fast. I would definitely come to this place for a quick bite when I visit. It gets pretty busy as well but we didn't wait too long.
BEST BREAKFAST WE HAVE HAD IN VEGAS! This includes Monte Carlo and Bellagio! Plus got a free pot of bread! Service was excellent and our server Staci was top notch!
Went to grab a nice breakfast with friends. Food was delicious, customer service was great and the prices were reasonable. I'd go back to try another food item.
We loved this place!  Everything on our table was hot, tasty, and exactly as ordered.   We loved Shirley too!

Disappointing change in attitude by management. We've been coming to Jamms for years. They have always been accommodating to my celiac spouse. Today he ordered his usual skillet and mentioned that he was gluten intolerant. The server screwed up her face and told us that none of them including the chefs had been trained to handle allergens. She acted like she wanted us to leave. What the heck???

There are three possible explanations for this change. 
1. The server isn't willing or able to deal with allergies.
2. Management has had a change of heart and is no longer willing to deal with dietary restrictions.
3. The chefs really haven't been trained to handle allergies.

All of these options are disturbing.

We saw Jamms on television when the chef Guy was checking out different restaurants in vegas. So we decided to try them out, we are so happy we did. The service has that family owned feel where you feel welcomed the whole time your there. Their pot o bread is the best i have had in vegas, i love the variety of flavors and there is always a different special flavor when we dine.
