So far the nutella banana and the pineapple cream cheese ones are my 2 favorites. My husbands favorite breakfast to order no matter where we dine is the Corned beef and hash with potato and eggs. He says hands down they make it the best in the city. I normally pick an omelet and they are always light and fluffy and taste fresh. The prices are affordable and you get a discount for checking in on social media and you show them at the register. We love this place and it's our new breakfast place when we decide to eat out. I can see why they have so many great reviews and repeat customers.

I'm not a big fan of breakfast but Jamms turns me into a maniac. The service, the old school feel and best of all the  yummy food. One of my favorite places to eat and my only breakfast joint. Highly recommend!!

My brother and I stopped here for a late brunch after hiking at Red Rock, it was exactly what we wanted. It was Sunday around 2pm and they were still serving breakfast so I ordered the bacon, avacado omlette, it was delicious! Nice home cooking and generous portions. It seems like a family-run restaurant with a classic diner feel and the staff we encountered were friendly. It may not be in the most exciting location (in a strip mall) but if you're after a filling breakfast/brunch and in the area it definitely does the trick!

I always enjoy having a great breakfast with the whole family when it's possible. Though I wish it was an every day thing, but that's not the case. So in those times where we can a few times a month we enjoy trying different spots, but since the first week tried this place over a year ago we knew we'd be back again and again. 

    With all the different choices and every which delicious and we'll priced I was already satisfied. The service is just as good really making you feel at home I recommend this to anyone looking for a great breakfast experience.

While we were told the wait at 11am on a Sunday would be 15-20 minutes, I was pleasantly surprised when we sat after only about 8 or 9 minutes. They do indeed turn tables quickly, but at no time did we feel rushed. The staff hustles, our waitress was efficient and cheerful, the coffee was hot and eye-opening.

My daughter had Jamm's French Toast which is battered then encrusted with corn flakes before frying. She says I will have to make mine this way from now on. I had Jamm's Speciality Omelet which has steak, grilled onions and mushrooms and lots of mild cheddar. Guests get their choice of hash browns or home fries and a bread selection - English muffin, toast, their signature pot o'bread. I chose the home fries and the special of the day pot o'bread with cream cheese frosting. 

The long and short of it is that we both left stuffed and happy, several wait staff wished us a good day and that we'd be back soon. We don't get to Vegas very often (about every 2-3 years) but we will certainly come back to Jamm's again.

Saw this place on the Travel Channel and had to try it out. When you first walk in your greeted with a smile and the place is all a chatter. No wait and I'm at my seat. Looking around its clean and everyone is smiling. Ordered my food( Texas Omelette) and was here with in 10 min. The food was great and the waitress was nice. This is a place that I can return to no questions asked.

Excellent!  We were staying on the Strip...wanted a great breakfast and found the friendly and delicious Jamms.  we did get to see more of the real Las Vegas driving there, but the food was worth the trip!  Do it!

Good food, reasonable prices, a friendly staff and homey decor.  It's NOT a chain which gives it extra stars in my opinion.  Service times were good and the menu choices were numerous.  Will definitely return.  Other reviewers have stated they had a wait time and that is certainly a personal choice, but the fact that they are not a multinational company makes the short wait worthwhile.  Buy local!!

For a Saturday morning, there was only a 5 minute wait. 
The first thing that caught my eye was the French Press coffee. This was a first for me and it was so incredibly good. They even offered a to go cup for what we didn't drink.
The corn beef hash is hands down the BEST EVER!!!!!! It was what my husband had, along with the carmelized onion, bacon, cream cheese pot of bread. Dayyyyum!!!
My next trip I'll be trying the S'mores pancakes. Sounds like a little piece of heaven. 
The servers were on point with everything!!
Check it out!

Saw this place at just the right time. We were craving some breakfast and Jamms was just in sight. First time here and you get what you pay for. I ordered the sandy omelette with home fries and the hubby got the Denver omelette with hash browns. We ordered their original pot of bread and the cinnamon raisin pot of bread. Neither of us could finish. Nice, hearty potions if home cooked breakfast food. Good for a quick bite in an old fashioned setting. Service was quick, friendly and at tentative. Both omelettes were jammed;) with ingredients. No cheaping on bacon, cheese, avocado or anything. Friendly, homey joint with good food

I have been to jamms quite a few times and this time particularly rubbed me the wrong way. The food was great and amazing I give the chef a 8/10. It was well prepared and delicious. Why I am giving this visit a 3 star is because the customer service provided today. The associates were very  and seemed irritable because it took longer than usual to go through the menu of great options. I witnessed my server speaking to other associates about our table and kept getting eyes from the associates she would speak to about the table. My server asked the drink provider to give us more water and he displayed an action of not wanting to do it. I get that it is a job but the people eating should not feel in easy or insecure while waiting for their food. In addition all of the staring eyes as we were sitting here did not make jamms to feel like the homey vibe I am used to. Customer service is my number one priority. I can eat anywhere it is the workers that make this experience and it was not a great customer service experience. I felt singled out and the center of their work gossip. We did speak with the manager about it and she made it more comfortable. So I thank the manager for doing a great job. I will highly recommend this place it has amazing food! I will go again maybe at a different time to have a different set of workers.

First time eating here and overall, very impressed.  Had the bumper omelet, which is mushrooms, broccoli, cream cheese and topped with hollandaise sauce. Although I wish the broccoli had been cooked a little more, it was delicious. The pot of bread was different and scrumptious. Parking is convenient and plentiful, since there is a grocery store a couple doors down. Decor was OK, but very clean,  booths looked a little circa 1980's. Honestly the only thing I wish they'd change is the kids menu prices, they seemed a bit high. Will definitely go back again.

I have been holding this in for sometime now, and I feel it is important information to share. A few weeks ago my husband went to eat breakfast at Jamm's here in Las Vegas. He ordered and ate his breakfast, and then asked if he could order some bacon to go.. With one request, that it be made in a separate pan so that I would be able to eat it and not have to worry about cross contamination. The server said it shouldn't be a problem. However, when she brought it to him she informed him that in the future if he were to order the bacon this way it wouldn't be possible if they were busy. He was floored. He is making sure that his wife doesn't potentially die and apparently this "special" request was just to much for the kitchen to handle. Seriously?! So he speaks with the manager and her attitude was so non-chalant that clearly life saving practices are not important. So he gets home, tells me this, and now I am questioning if I should even eat this bacon. I open the container and find not only my bacon but hash brown bits as well. Clearly our request was completely ignored. So I decided to call Jamm's and the manager gets on the phone, and when I inform her that I could die if I ate that bacon her response was, well then just don't eat it. I went off on her. Clearly no concern for their patrons is evident. I want everyone in Vegas to know that if you have a "special" request in order to ensure your life isn't jeopardized, won't be taken seriously. It starts at the top people. If management doesn't care then no one else will. I just hope the death of someone doesn't happen due to their carelessness and negligence. I am not asking because I am picky, I am asking because I don't want to die. So please make sure that before you eat there you evaluate their practices. Oh and just so you know no military discount is given, but if you post you are there on social media you get 15% off your bill. Really? I think priorities need to be shifted.

I felt ignored by my server, stopped by for a quick meal before work they were pretty speedy with getting the food out. Me and my family will not be returning anytime soon. Good food, didn't feel like they had good service.

I thoroughly enjoyed the great good and huge portions at this great breakfast restaurant.  The omelets are large with a lot of different varieties, as well as the pancakes and French toast.  The Jamms French toast was good, but also not as flavorful as I would have liked.  But I would come back several more times to try all of the other types of pancakes and French toast they have on the menu.

We were greeted quickly and the waitstaff was nice. We had whole grain pancakes with whole grain crunch. It was yummy. I ordered Eggs Benedict, again great.  If you mention yelp, you get a free bread. Price was under 22 bucks with coffe and a coke for two :). We left satisfied.

The food was amazing!!! Literally 20seconds away from my mom in laws house can't beat that! I must say the Jamms French toast crusted with corn flakes bomb.com got it with a side of bacon and my bf had the California beni and mom Inlaw had the sandy omelette with sweet potato fries with the cinnamon bread super delicious!!!, staff super nice and attentive it was a first timer for me and my bf and we must say we will be back definitely very cute lil breakfast/lunch spot must check while in the area! Aloha from Hawaii!:)
Best corned beef hash on the damn planet. Seriously.

What a great place to have breakfast or lunch! The staff is so friendly and the food is great at a reasonable prices. Definitely a nice place to sit and chat for a bit. If you get the chance, ask for Shirley, she's amazing!

Had the sandy omelet and let me tell you that thing did the disappearing act.  Pot of bread was the holiday cranberry flavor.  I can't give Jamms enough love, I want to skip the silverware entirely and use my fingers next time.  Old fashioned homey atmosphere, huge portions, great service, family owned.

They also will do platter portions for carry out for you to supplement your next party!
Great breakfast at the right price! Definitely want to come back and I live in north Las Vegas!

Amazing had the sandys omelette, french press coffee, and sweet potato fries. Friendly great service and delicious food...large servings at a reasonable price.
Definitely will return!
Truly a hidden jamm! If you're seeking a truly local breakfast shop, make sure to stop in. They have a fantastic menu with constantly changing specials. Love it, wish I found this place sooner!!

I love breakfast food and I must admit, its hard to find a really good breakfast place. I came here with the bfriend and we ordered:

*Matty's Country Benedict:
 2 biscuits at the bottom with 2 sausages and 2 perfectly poached eggs on top, covered with creamy light yummy gravy!  Also came with a choice of hash browns or fries.
*Country Skillet:
fluffy scrambled eggs with sausage pieces, diced sweet onions, shredded hams, sliced mushrooms, diced potatoes.. covered with their creamy gravy on top.

The service is two thumbs up-- quick and friendly. The waitress came back several times to ask if we needed anything and if everything was okay. I really enjoyed their breakfast and the gravy topped off everything perfectly. Loved it!!

The "Tie Dye" Tony and crew wanted to leave a review

We love Jamms and we visit at least a month, if not more.

The food is always delicious and always large portions, I've never had anything bad here and we always bring friends, family, out of town visitors, ect because this is our go to breakfast place! 

We always appreciate how fast and friendly the staff are to us and how quickly the food is delivered! We appreciate how the food is always amazing and we are always taken care of here!
Pot O'bread, nuff said. Excellent. Also had the reuben omelette. Unreal.  Highly recommended. The corned beef hash is also the best around

On Fathers Day I simply looked up "breakfast restaurants" + my zip code. Wanted to find someplace a little different from where we normally go for family breakfast. Jamm's was absolutely amazing! Every review was spot on, even when they tell you it's well worth the wait. Our waitress was funny and courteous, the food was absolutely outstanding and their signature POT OF BREAD was out of this world!!! I will definitely frequent this place many times over!

The first time i went here the food was awesome. Today it was horrible..hair cooked in my fries..and my daughters panini had next to nothing in it compared to the last time we were there. After telling the waitress about it she apologized by saying..hair flies around..we all have it and she would rather have a bug in it than a hair. Enough was enough but then she proceeded to tell us they found a frog in the spinach once. Not sure what her motive was but in the end she took 2.00 off for the fries. After finding hair i had only ate 1/4 of my wrap. My stomach turned at this point and made me sick. I dont go to a restaurant to order hair in the food and this should of been entirely written off the bill. What a disappointment!

Service is great and a cute mom and pop eatery indeed.  There popover bread is why we come here occasionally.  It was served in a ceramic pot before but now in a tin cup which seems to get the popover bread out quicker.

We have tried their Sandy burrito, eggs benedict, and pancakes. All good. 

They have a $5 small plates menu, which I love and allows for you to sample a few choices. 

Expect a wait over the weekend and definitely try their popover bread, they have seasonal ones and original which is my favorite.   I am not sure why they are called Jams, but if I were to guess without asking I would think they are known for their homemade jams which unfortunately I have not experienced here, only the typical packets of Smuckers
I don't even like breakfast foods but I come here at least twice a week! It's so good and they have the option to do small plates so the portions are perfect. The bread pots are my favorite!
First time here, we're from out of town. I looked up on my Google maps top rated restaurant and found Jamms. The food was good.

Jamms was a great surprise. Everything was great- the atmosphere, the menu options, the workers. I love their pot of bread. It's so adorable and warm and delicious. We usually get all three flavors when we go.

First time here
Their complimentary Pot Raisin Cinnamon Bread with Cream Cheese spread a great way to start off a meal.
Simply said one of the best breakfast places in all Las Vegas.
And for you coffeeholics their coffee is Excellent.
Thank you for the great food, great service, great experience.
I am a big fan!! after just one visit.
Best breakfast in town! Best bread too! I had the Denver omelet and the creamy strawberry pot of bread, which was the special weekly flavor. So good can't wait to go back
This is my favorite breakfast spot! I live in San Diego but EVERY TIME we are in town we have to stop in!

Perfect breakfast. I am a huge fan of breakfast, coffee, and sausage gravy and all of these items were spot on. We will be back. Erin got the tuna melt and it was truly perfect. The tuna was grilled also as it should be. Why haven't I heard of this place? Go try it now!!
We have come here for years and years.  You really can't beat the place and the service is over the top.  What a great place to have, we are lucky.
Our favorite goto place for breakfast.  Excellent food...Excellent staff.  The pot bread is an excellent addition to the meal

Went with the hubby today- we both ordered corned beef hash based on these glowing, stellar recommendations of fellow yelpers!! ...and we were not disappointed!!! He loved his plain pot of bread and my cin raisin one was awesome. Fresh coffee, great service. Really glad this business has survived the sucky economy. Will definitely re-visit! :)

After having dined here multiple times over the year (2013) I was recently shown my previous review, which was a two liner and felt ashamed I have not updated my pathetic first review.

JR is always a front runner in any Friday "where are we going to breakfast" discussion.  The reasons being you are always going to get a great breakfast, happy service and great coffee.

The omelets are a group favorite and I seem to focus on the Jamms Signature Omelet.  
It consists of pieces of sliced tender steak, onions, mushrooms, cheese.  All covered with a wonderful béarnaise sauce.

JR is known for their pots of bread, which is FREE when you check-in on yelp.  The benefit  has yet to expire because every time I check-in.....there it is.  CHECK-IN!

ON my most recent visit some ordered the grits.  Now I can take or leave grits.  But I would kiss these grits all damn day until I died of a heart attack.  Heart attack?  YES!  the are covered in cheese and comes with butter! You can get the LARGE or you can get a "monkey size" which dials down you cholesterol a tad.

Be sure to grab a stick of Juicy Fruit at the counter when you settle up the bill.

Be sure to add this to your list of breaking the fast spots!
Nice place to get breakfast away from the strip. Great pancakes and eggs. Although, I thought the coffee was a bit watery and weak. Would like to go back and try the french toast.

My first time at Jamm's was pretty delicious, as far as I remember. When a friend suggested we meet there for breakfast, I was excited to eat some delicious French toast again! That's about as good as it got. I ordered the Jamm's French toast, which was pretty good. I also ordered scrambled eggs, sausage and hash browns. My eggs tasted like they had been prepared with dishwater, and the hash browns has a foul odor to them, that I couldn't even get past to taste. The sausage was average and a bit room temperature. I was pretty disappointed in the food this visit. If I were to come back, I would stick to French toast and avoid side dishes.

This is definitely one of my "go to" restaurants all the time.  I normally get the steak and eggs or corned beef hash.  For lunch I get the tuna sandwich.   But this time I went out of my comfort zone and went with their signature omelet with  slices steak with onions, mushrooms and cheese topped with our homemade béarnaise sauce.  Delish!   And of course I always get the Cinnamon raisin pot of bread.  Can't wait to go back!
Food is amazing! Large portions for a reasonable price! Staff is extremely fast, attentive,& sweet

Boyfriend and I love this place! Even though it's far from where we live in the east side of town, we chose to go because of the great food and service. We always build our own omelette because they have a great variety to chose from! The servers and bussers are always nice and attentive, there's one server in particular that is great! I don't know her name but she's awesome! The cinnamon pot bread is delicious as well. Looking forward to my next visit to Jamms!

What can I say?? Jamms is the best.  Expect to wait on the weekends,  the place is packed.  Try the pot of bread.. The service is always great.  Been going here for about 17 years,  and the same waitresses are working there.  That tells me that they are treated well and are happy. Our order is always correct,  the coffee is good and they always have a smile on their faces for us. Best place for breakfast in town.

Trying out a new breakfast spot in town was a good choice. Although this is in a shady neighborhood, don't judge a book by it's cover. What's inside is what counts. There was a short wait but as we were there I notice the wait got longer and there was a steady flow of customers coming in. I also noticed waitresses that spoke to customers by name, telling me there are regulars here. Those were all good signs to start. 

I got the veggie omelette which is my go to breakfast item of choice. This omelette really impressed me with large chunks of vegetables. They also cooked the onion and bell pepper prior to putting it in the omelette. I really liked this extra step and appreciated it. Having ordered this at many different restaurants, I can say that this was above the rest when it comes to giving me some actual veggies I can see in my omelette. Other places it is just tiny chopped pieces of veggies with no veggie taste. I also really enjoyed the hash browns. The bread that came with it I was not that impressed with. It was kind of dry and bland. We had the cinnamon. 

We also ordered red velvet pancakes to compare to others we have had, and these were different. They were huge, really thick and fluffy, and a little on the "less sweet" side which is a good or bad thing, depending on what you want. 

Service was good and quick. I think this is a good choice for a simple all American breakfast.

One of the best mom and pop breakfast spots! Love the pot of breads they serve with a meal! Would like more parking for the restaurant but it's in a plaza so can't do nothing about that. You won't regret having breakfast here

I LOVE THIS PLACE!! I have been there several times.  The food is great and the service is excellent.  I love getting the pot o' bread and they know how to make an omelette (which most places just mix it all together)!!!  I highly recommend this place because it's not over-priced and I love that I have never had a bad breakfast there!!!!

Not exactly sure what all the hype about...or maybe these people have just been breakfast deprived...but this place was just OK. I have had a lot better elsewhere and was kind of disappointed. The pot of bread (that everyone raved about) wasnt that great..and no one in our group of 12 really liked it. 
I got the corned beef benedict. It was alright. I think there was some kind of skillet that was the only thing everyone actually liked. 

However, the Service was great though
Always a great breakfast spot. Pot of bread is delicious and the flavors are different every visit. Super nice service and friendly faces.

Wow  no good no gluten free items. For starters....the floor was so dirty from days ago who knows how long the ham was there because when I put my foot down it was crusty and it was on my new shoes :-(  I ordered a side hamburger  patty with a fried egg on top... with a side of COLE slaw clearly the cook top was dirty with old grease my fried egg had old particles on it .. yuk...the COLE slaw was soggy like you could smell it was old and not crispy like it should be and no flavor needed a hint of salt...oh yes ordered side sweet potato fries like it was eating cardboard not that I know what cardboard tastes like. Lol But not even salted that would of helped. Needless to say we did not complain left and will never go back!!!!!

Was it good? Sure. Was it great? Nope. We decided to come here since it's been on my bookmark list for a while now and from what I heard it's supposed to be very good. It was kind of a check in the box for me, so if nothing else I'm glad to knock another one off the list. 

Came here on a Sunday and the line was out the door, which is usually a good indication the food is worth the wait. And surprisingly, the line moved rather quickly. And thank goodness because we were all in desperate need of nourishment after the night out we had. (Note to self: lots of sake, sushi & shots are a recipe for disaster, ugh!) Lol! 

Anyways...first impression: it's a very small busy diner that could use some major updating. Lots of noise and hustle & bustle. Sitting near the kitchen I got a good glimpse of the waitresses & cooks frantically trying to get food out. Even so, our food took a bit longer than expected to make it's way to our table but in all fairness it was a Sunday not to mention, Mother's Day. We should feel lucky we were able to get seated so quickly. 

On to the food. The pot-o-bread was good, free with your Yelp check-in. I guess that's what they're known for. Nothing here that really stood out to me. The guys seemed to be pleased with their meals. My omelet was just okay. The cheese on top wasn't melted. And the bacon inside seemed a bit over cooked, as were the side of potatoes which made it difficult to eat. (See my photo and you'll understand). 

All in all, it wasn't terrible, it also wasn't the best. Great prices so that's a plus. But there are better options for breakfast around town.

Literally my go to place for breakfast. Everything is always cooked to perfection & served with a smile. The place is so down to earth & relaxing which is pretty surprising for a small restaurant. It's cozy in a great way (:

Coffee and pot of bread great....service is bad!!! Breakfast took 2 hours!!  Food was just ok. Had to ask for to go box twice and then it was thrown on table! Our bus person Jose was the nicest person there! Probably won't go back.

Still loving this place. This time, we brought relatives from Hawaii who just arrived on the red-eye, so we skated right in on an early Sunday morning. Jamms delivered as usual, hot pots of strawberry-coconut bread (flavor of the week), with multiple refills of good hot coffee.  We appreciate a good cup of coffee--nothing pretentious, just a decent complement to the food. Again, the breakfast selections are varied and it does take time to settle on something from the menu. Orders included the grilled corned beef hash & eggs, which was savory with a nice crunchy exterior; the iconic Joe's Omelet with fresh spinach and plenty of beef and mushrooms; fluffy pancakes and eggs cooked exactly as requested. 

Our visitors were happy with being brought to this local spot to have a very satisfying breakfast. 

By the time we left, there was a line of people waiting to get in. The usual Sunday morning scene. But it's worth the wait.

Fantastic place and worth the drive! I was greeted as I came in and everyone was very friendly despite how busy they were. I had the corn beef hash and eggs, bread pot, hash browns, and toast. The CB Hash is the real deal made from scratch with bit pieces of CB throughout. Eggs were poached and exactly to specification, bread pot was delish!

I was told to pay up front when I was done with my meal and they kept the coffee topped off and offer a stronger blend if you desire.

Yelpers that did not rate this establishment higher need to try it again, because it seems they have listened to your suggestions/complaints and have acted upon those making the needed corrections.

I will return!

Have been going here for...  hmm probably 10 years.  I live around the corner and I love this breakfast spot.  Service is good, prices are reasonable, food is tasty.  They also deal REALLY well with specialty orders to the point where they know..  eggs benedict, dry english muffin, sauce on the side, fruit instead of potatoes lol.

Great tasty food, too bad you can only have breakfast or lunch here. Asked for steak and eggs, and it was awesome. Coffee was delicious too. It'd been better if they would've taken the order quicker, almost 10 min later after sitting, and still the lady took the order from someone who sat after we had been assign a table...

Great place! Cozy and friendly. 
Great food and great service and really nice and big selection! There is an option to taste in small portion everything that's on the menu. 
Highly recommend:)
The food was really good but it was so stuffy and hot in the restaurant. Burnt toast smell got a bit noxious.

My husband and I went here for breakfast and the service was great. He had chicken and waffles which were delicious. I had a breakfast burrito that was not so great, it was very bland and not at all what I was expecting. I will say that I enjoyed their puff pastry that comes in a mug.
Some of the best breakfast in town! Has a very homey family vibe to it! Friendly staff, good food. Sometimes there is a wait, but definitely worth it!
Yummy food!  Homemade chicken soup and bread bowls!  Great local place for breakfast or lunch!

I had french toast the first time. It was gud. They put cornflakes on it cuz that's the best way to do it. 2nd time I wasn't feeling gud and so the server said to have the soup and it was gud and made me feel better. so have the french toast if you're feeling gud or have the soup.  Pot of bread is not a literal pot of bread.

Can't disagree more with this overall yelp rating!   Strike 1: coffee was served in a dirty mug with lip smudge marks still on it.                Strike 2: I order jams French toast and got waffles instead. I read it off the menu to the waitress . She argued with me when the wrong dish came out and said "are you ok " as though I am crazy.                           Strike3: the waffle was baaad , it was grainy and tasted like it was never mixed.The worst waffle that I ever ate. The bacon was cheap buffet quality . My bill was $17 with tax and tip. It was $16.99 too much. Keep away from Jamms, go to the omlet house or original pancake instead.

When You  have company come into to town, you discover many new places to eat. Googled best breakfast and this was #2 on the list. We  went on a Sunday morning..VERY BUSY.. but VERY friendly and accommodating..Superb food & service..I Loved my pot o bread which they are known for...Next time I will go on a day other than Sunday.. but no complaints..
Very slow, poor service. Out of party of 5, 2 had issues with order. Hair in a BLT and tuna that tasted as if it was out for a week. To their credit they did try to fix things.
Delicious breakfast!! Love the cinnamon pot bread !! Omg to die for  & the waitress was so kind & her laugh was soo contagious 10/10

They're an okay place to go, they have some pretty nice omelettes but other than that it's a pretty average place. 

The French toast tastes more burnt than anything, you'll have to drown it in syrup to be edible. The orange juice taste synthetic and watered down. The pricing is cheap compared to other places and it's pretty cute old fashioned inside.

We jammin! The cornbeef hash is the bomb, boom!
The staff is very attentive. I love the irish skillet with my eggs over medium. Tony really knows how to cook an egg to perfection. The egg white omletes are awsm too. The coffee is strong, and the french press is even stronger. If you like that classic cream taste in your coffee ask for half and half, or they will bring you milk. All around great breakfast joint. Try it a couple times, then a couple more. Shirley,Maria,Kathy,John, and Albert were great all the times we went. cheers!
The service is awesome. The people are friendly. The food was very fresh, tasty and presentation was great.Lenore is wonderful and she brought us their specialty Pan bread just like a cinabun.
This is one of my favorites for breakfast.  Try the corned beef, if you haven't already.

I really enjoyed eating here. Cute decor, warm and friendly wait staff, and great food. The only thing is that I wish my breakfast had a little less salt, but I have to give them props for using FRESH CORNED BEEF for their corned beef hash! Their Cinnamon Raisin pot of bread was excellent and it was enough for us to take back to our room and heat up for the next day! :) YUM!!!

Visited here on my first time in Vegas. I am still so grateful my friend showed me this gem. 

You really feel the love in this place! I still dream of pots of bread. Just like having a home cooked meal with your grandparents. :)

Best Breakfast by far in Las Vegas! Been coming for years to Las Vegas and decide to trust my YELPERS. Once again, they have not failed me. I'm from San Diego and wish we could have a Jamms restaurant down here! Till next time! Highly recommend the breakfast! Service was awesome, friendly and quick!

Not sure what the draw is here. If Las Vegans think this is the ultimate breakfast hotspot, then they have never been to an ultimate breakfast hotspot.  When we arrived the place was crowded and there was about a 10 minute wait. no problem.

When we were finally seated, it took the server nearly 10 minutes just to get to the coffee. Now I know the place is busy but it's never too busy to serve coffee in a timely manner. But in all honesty, I have to say that once the ball was rolling, we did not have to wait for refills. Maybe there was a little redemption there.

The location. What is up with that? It was a big ugly strip mall which I think is a weird place for a restaurant but Las Vegas is so full of big ugly strip malls, there's just no place else to put a restaurant. It's bizarre.

The food is nothing beyond mediocre. I had a veggie omelet that was so loaded with cheddar that it just became a big greasy mess and worse by association, death on a plate. I tried to push as much of it to the side as I could and by the time I was finished, it was quite a pile.

The next time I'm in Vegas, I'm going to do some research and come up with my own breakfast spot

Tried two items from Erica's small plates. This was a great option to try more in one sitting without breaking the bank or having a bunch of left overs. The omelet was hearty and the perfect size. The waffles had fresh fruit toppings, a generous side of syrup and delicious whip cream, but the texture was more of a beignet. 
The servers were polite and attentive, specially with coffee refills.

Will return again!
Delicious food every time I go! Love the variety, so there is something for everyone. Large portions, which allows for leftovers. Very friendly staff. Go early, as there is usually a wait.

I've been coming here since it opened! Great and friendly staff. Best breakfast in town. My go to items are the waffle Benedict and the Jamms signature omelette with steak mushrooms and onions and cheese, the Pot of bread is a must!
Great savory and sweet breakfast items and awesome service. Tried the Nutella pancakes, Reuben omelet. Also got the free pot of bread! This will definitely be my new go to breakfast place. :)

Burnt hash browns, steak was 1/2 an inch thick and smaller then a steak from south point. Pot of bread is just bread in a tin cup.... Ok? Zagat rated their food at a 25..... How is that even possible? I think they need to reassess their decision. They might have been good in 2014, but not now.
Good food but overpriced for what you get.  I think the competition out there for breakfast food is fierce.

Wasn't as impressed as I thought I would be. Omelet was VERY good! The pot bread I should of stuck to the original vs the one they had that day (it was awful) the sandwich they are known for is a grilled cheese Ruben - it was anything but! I'm willing to try again and maybe stick to something more common. The staff is very attentive and kind
I'm giving this place 4 stars because the atmosphere was old school diner. And the service good. However the food was not that great it was horrible but it was just meh...
I really loved the tapas breakfast. I had a small eggs Benedict florentine and two pumpkin pancakes. Super yum!!!!

Drove across town to fulfill my corned beef hash craving at this place. Because of all those remarkable "Yelp" comments on their corned beef hash, I could not get this place off my mind! Not only that, corned beef hash is my #1 preferred breakfast dish!!!

Corned Beef Hash and Eggs: NO Question, the Best Corned Beef Hash I've ever had to date!! They crisp up the top and bottom of the corned beef hash serving which added a very nice subtle touch of texture and the meat inside stayed juicy, tender and tasty as can be! The portion was also Generous! The accompanied fried potatoes were far from dry, simple and delicious!

French Toast - "Jamms Style" = corn flake breaded/crusted: 4 Thick half slices of toast that were a little crunchy, a little sweet and had a nicely executed spongy consistency. Add some of their softened butter and drizzle some maple syrup over the bits of powdered sugar.. Yummm!!

Pot of Bread: Thanks Yelp for the complimentary/special offer!  Extra Fresh, Extra Soft and Plainly Divine Roll of Bread!! 

Worth the Drive, Server was Very Nice and Enthusiastic, Prices were Fair and the atmosphere felt like how it should be!! APPROVED!!

Always great service with a smile & amazing fresh cooked food. Got my favorite, the Irish Skillet, delicious & filling with home made corned beef hash. I highly recommend! 

(Different day) We come here often because it's always great. Not super happy with the corned beef hash today, it was mushy & had too much garlic. I'll still be back

My brother and I were both up at 8am and wanted some breakfast.  He found this place online and wanted to try it due to some awards they received from Best of Vegas.  I then looked it up on here and read about the special offer for a free pot of bread.  I love bread and was excited to find out what it was exactly and to try it.  After our waitress took our orders I mentioned Yelp and asked about the pot of bread.  She didn't seem familiar with the offer, but didn't question it at all and brought me one.  In case you're wondering, it's a personal sized piece of bread that comes in a little round bowl and resembles a large cupcake.  I got the cinnamon-raisin one and it was definitely the best part of my dining experience.  The top was just a little toasted and the middle was soft and chewy.  If that were all I ate I'd have given them 5 stars, but sadly it went downhill from there.    
I ordered an omelet with avocado, bacon, and cheddar and it was a big disappointment.  There was quite a bit of bacon inside, but it was all way overcooked and a little thick, so it was rock hard.  The avocado was good but it was all on one side, so I had to open it up and spread it out.  Also, the only cheddar I found was a few shredded pieces on top.  Like I said, very disappointing.  In hindsight I should have sent it back and either gotten something else or had them remake it.
They give a choice of hash browns or home fries and I had the latter.  They were good and had bits of onion and bell pepper mixed in.  Overall, I can see how this place could be good, but my experience wasn't the best.  I'd give 'em a mulligan tho.

I didn't do the review while in the restaurant  because I want to give readers an accurate review without feeling pressured to give a great review because of the ten percent discount so I skipped doing the check in on yelp and taking the discount so that I can give you guys an accurate review which is, 
the staff is friendly and the food is OK it could use more seasoning and flavor on his own without you having to put ketchup Hot sauce or A1 sauce on it. I wouldn't recommend ordering the steak because it was not tender and it's very poor choice cut of meat the little bread pots are good the eggs were just loaded with cheese with no flavor  no salt or pepper and I had to send it back the crunchy French toast is OK we did however like the orange juice

Outside of the place being freezing, the staff was nice enough and the food was good. The Cuban sandwich was excellent and the French dip was just okay. The pot of bread is a good signature appetizer. We would go back if we are in that part of town.

Pleasantly surprised! There isn't an overwhelming abundance of breakfast places around here, and diners can be pretty hit or miss- but this one knocks it out of the park! Menu has about ten different omelets, in addition to skillets, benedicts, and the usual waffles, pancakes, etc. along with lunch options: sandwiches, burgers, soups, and salads.

BF and I started with coffee and OJ, then opted for different omelets: the Jamm's signature omelet for me  (béarnaise sauce on the side, I never used it), Joe's omelet for my guy. Each omelet is about $10, and includes your bread of choice (I opted for the plain pot bread, BF had the special: walnut brownie) as well as an additional side (wedge fries for me, cottage cheese for the dude).
Good portion sizes for the price, both with the variety of sides and the sizes of individual items.

Omelets were both cooked perfectly: others have said they are drowning in cheese, which is not entirely true. Mine had a good amount, but the Joe's omelet was a little lighter. Both had good amounts of meat and veggies. 
The fries are tasty and seasoned, served in a cute little individual fryer basket container (cute!), cottage cheese is standard. The pot bread was a delightful surprise! Preferred the plain flavor: reminded me of slightly-sweet biscuits with dinner, growing up with homestyle country meals. The walnut brownie pot bread was sweet, but no overwhelmingly chocolatey or nutty- the name had made me expect more of a dessert on the table, but it wasn't overkill.

Service, as others have said, rocks. Attentive and polite, not overbearing or annoying.
Will be returning to try the benedicts and perhaps a lunch one of these days. And the featured pot bread, of course!

Great local hole-in-the-wall with a friendly diner atmosphere.  We ate breakfast there.  I had a meaty omelet and my wife had the eggs Benedict.   Both were tasty and reasonably priced.  We were headed out of Vegas going North, and it was an easy stop before getting out of town.  

They are apparently famous for their bread bowl, wish we would have gotten that.  We didn't notice it until we exited.  I had whole wheat bread with my omelet and it was amazing.  Pretty sure it was homemade.  The texture was soft yet chewy and buttery... man that was some good bread.

Jamms is always the place to go for breakfast.  There is not a thing in the menu that you can go wrong with.  Service is always excellent and attentive.  My wife and I come here as often as we can because they make you feel at home.
Great food and service! If you can't make up your mind, try the "Red Plate" selections. A little of a lot of different flavors. I have come here for years and never have had a disappointing meal!

Sorry! Wasn't a fan. Went here with my gf and her family and so my hopes were high especially since I recommended this place based on reviews here. 3 out of 4 of us ordered the "hungry lion" which consists of eggs, sausage, bacon, ham steak and pancakes. Eggs and pancakes were pretty good, nothing special, ham steak ok, bacon and sausage bad! Bacon chewy like rubber and the sausage was unlike any other I've ordered in a restaurant. They were the kind you get at the cheap breakfast buffets that are snappy and are kind of gross without much flavor. So, to sum up, not too impressed. Service was nice though :)

Went here today for the first time got sausage egg and cheese sandwich and Home made fries. I did not like none of it, it seemed rushed no seasonings no nothing the potatoes was barley cooked. I paid $19 and I can say it was a waste of my money and am highly disappointed. I picked here because of the high ratings, but those rating did not add up to the food I had today. Would I go back again? Maybe to try something else but I highly doubt I would ugh   what a waste of money.
A welcoming environment! Food was good  service was great. A menu full of good  food choices .
Had breakfast at Jamm's this morning while visiting Vegas for work.  Great food!  Hungry Lion breakfast left me stuffed!  Will definitely be back next time I'm in town.

Very good diner.  Corn beef hash was not the best I have had but was solid.  I did not have one of their famous bread rolls but they looked good.  Coffee was plentiful and strong which is essential for any breakfast place in my book.  I live in SW Vegas but will return next time I am around Charlston and Rainbow.

I had the sandy omelet with hash browns and the raisin pot of bread. I also tried the French toast sticks. Everything was delicious!! The waitress was attentive and my drink stayed filled. This restaurant served one of the best breakfasts I've ever had. Absolutely loved it!!

Delicious!!! We were in vegas and Friends that live there took us here for breakfast I want sure about it by it's looks but I loved it the ham was delicious and the pancakes everything I will definetly go back
I always love Jam's  Just make sure they r opened before u arrive :) Thanks guys!!! Their biscuits and gravy remind me of my small town childhood like Dorothy,

This has been my regular breakfast spot for years. 

Sometimes it's a bit long of a wait to get in but normally the wait is worth it. My only real complaint about this place is the grits (way too watery) and the fact that many minor issues will come up if you have a special prep on your order (like simple substitutions or asking to leave items off) if they are busy. Don't think this is an waitress issue as its pretty consistent so maybe the kitchen is just willing to take the recourse. They really are minor but then again, I don't have allergies. That may be an issue for someone else.
Jamm's breakfast was vey affordable and WOW is the food great!

I was not impressed with this place at all today. First we get there around 12:30 and they say 15 minute wait. No problem. We wander over to the vape shop next door. I go back about ten mins later and our table is ready, but they won't seat me as my whole party is not there. Whole party??? It's just me and my boyfriend. I tell them he's right next door and will be back in a minute but they still refuse to seat me. I guess that is just their policy, but it put a bad taste in my mouth and everything got worse from there. 

Our server while nice, messed up our order. I wanted to try the weekly pot O bread, which was strawberry almond, but she brought me out cinnamon raisin. Womp womp. I ended up just eating it, because I don't like to complain. It was pretty good though. Boyfriend ordered a Philly with no mushrooms, and it came out with shrooms. She admitted that was her mistake and offered to correct his sandwich, but he decided to order something else instead. He chose a chili burger. This was the smallest burger ever and you could tell the chili came from a can. I ordered the eggs benedict with home fries. I got about 2oz of home fries, which are potatoes with bell pepper and onions. They were good, but I had two bites and they were gone. The hollandaise on my eggs did not have much flavor, so the whole dish suffered. 

I paid just about $30 including tax and tip which is wayyyyy too much for just an ok meal. I probably won't be back.
First time here and I LOVED it!!! Our server was hilarious and made suggestions that were on target. My favorite was the pot of bread!!! Will definitely come back even though it's off the strip!!

Good tasting breakfast for a good price. The food alone is worth leaving the strip for to have breakfast. And the staff are good and attentive. Reminds me of that good home style kitchen cooked breakfast.

My son and I are huge fans of biscuits and gravy. We have been on a mission to find "edible" B&G in Vegas. Loved Black Bear Dinner but the last 2x we ate there we found black hairs in our food...twice!! So never going back there again!!!
Now for Jamms...waited 30 mins not too bad. Service was incredible!!!! Never had an empty glass and she brought my son their famous pot of bread at no charge. Food was very good...still haven't found B&G like they make in the south but Jamms is pretty close. Will definitely be back!!

Great food: Love the corn beef hash for breakfast. Always as for extra buttery hash browns and they come out delicious. Service is quick and friendly. Tip: wait after 1pm to eat here as the big breakfast rush is over and I get seated very quickly.

Jamm's is a breakfast/lunch jem of the Vegas valley.  The food is excellent and the staff is friendly.  My 2 year old loves the potted bread and does my wife and I.  Our only wish is that there was more than one location but being they are a mom and pop restaurant, we completely understand.

Shay was my server and she was friendly and helpful. Tim, the server assistant I think,  was great and quick on the refills. Food was outstanding, and I'm a vegetarian, if that helps anyone. Their veggie omelet and veggie breakfast burritos are top notch. I'm stuffed because I just had to finish that huge burrito. Time for a nap. =)
Coffee & food is always great! Weekdays you should be good on waiting time but weekends get here early.

Worht seeking out for sure.
Eggs benedicts if really good.
Service is fast and friendy.
Make the drive from the stip you wont be sorry.
Great brunch menu. The pot of bread so good. My club sandwich was a little over toasted but the lettuce sauce meat ratio awesome.
Very friendly and attentive staff. Had French toast combo that was great! Pot of bread was tasty!

Rounding up for Jamms since I really had a nice experience there getting breakfast. Crispy bacon in the omlette was key and you got a lot of avocado too - no skimping here!  Service was prompt and I would say I like Jamms more than Mr Mamas where I've been to a lot.  It's a bit further out from the Strip if you are a visitor to Vegas (as I frequently am) but worth it!

Jamm's is the absolute best breakfast restaurant in all of Las Vegas. The staff is wonderful, impeccable service. The food is always perfect and I have tried all sorts of items on the menu. I highly recommend the Hungry Lion and the pot of bread  is amazing. They also have great lunches. If you are in the area of Rainbow and Charleston look no further.... go eat at Jamm;s.

Went in on a Saturday around noon. We were seated immediately. Waitress was great. Food was great. Very casual atmosphere. Not for the snooty. Overall a great place to bring the family to breakfast. Will definately be back!!

What a great place. There weren't any recent reviews that we could find so we thought we would try it out. I am here to report that it is amazingly good food and lots of it.

In the land of all you can eat, and Feng Shue less is more, they serve you well and you leave having eaten all you can.  both my wife's and my omelettes were filled to bursting. Her bacon and avocado were more than sufficient in the omelette. It was so big she ended up having to open it up to eat the insides and then still left food behind. The hashbrowns were done perfectly, crispy and flavorful and a good-sized portion. The homemade chips are perfectly sliced and served in their own little french fry basket. The bread pots are amazing. That special of the week was the pumpkin and cream cheese glaze bread pot and it was delicious.
If you're thinking about coming, do it! This is a fantastic place for breakfast.

I didn't think our meal here was fantastic or terrible. It was just okay. My hubby thought the sausage gravy was a bit flat.  Other than that, it was just your standard diner breakfast. The pot of bread was probably the best thing about it.  Service was good.
Loooooove Jamms!! The food is always amazing :) highly recommend! It's definitely always busy for a reason!

A place that hits the right spot! My crew rolled up at 11am and was seated in 10 minutes. The restaurant was packed but the service was good. I had the Waffle Benedict it was delicious and different from the regular muffin. I also ordered a side of bacon that was cooked to perfection. Everyone in my crew liked their meal as well. The portions are big but they offer tapas style for smaller portions. This was genius and will try next time I go. If you want a old fashion diner feel that hauls out great food stop by Jamms!!!

I was a bit disappointed when I ate at this establishment. I've a huge breakfast fan, and am always looking to try new places. 

It was pretty packed when I got there, and so I had high hopes. Busy places usually mean good food. 

Service itself was just bad. We were seated and given our menus, but no one came around after that for at least seven minutes. And when our waitress finally did come around, she had a very snide attitude.

I ordered the chicken fried steak. The steak was good and flavorful, and not the least bit dry. The gravy however, which was put on heavy handed, was disappointing. It had no flavor and added nothing to the dish. The scrambled eggs I ordered with it, were very dry. Which is a big pet peeve of mine. Scrambled eggs are probably my favorite thing to eat, and ruined eggs just ruin my meal. 

The Sandy omelet was ordered by a couple others that I was eating with. Both of which said their omelets were dried out as well. And that it was just disgustingly full of bacon. 

The Cinnamon raisin pot of bread was probably the best thing that was served to us. 

I definitely don't see myself going back to this establishment.

Great food, awesome service. Perfect place for breakfast. No reservations and nowhere to really sit inside. And everybody must know it's good because we waited outside for 30min for a table. But it was worth it.

This was the best breakfast I have had in a very long time. The service was very fast and nice. The cheese grits were awesome and the corn beef hash was just to die for. Reminds me of the way my grandma would make hers. The cinnamon raisin bread alone will keep me coming back again & again:)

A great place for breakfast!

I've had a couple different things on the menu and it was all great. 

The restaurant is pretty outdated and really needs a renovation, but that won't keep me from coming here.

If you are looking for southern comfort breakfast food, this is the place. We usually order the Rueben Benedict and the Chicken and Waffle BLT. Try the pot of bread as well! The servers are super friendly.  If you come on the weekend, be prepared to wait. Don't worry, it's worth it. Also,  they give 10% off for checking in on Yelp!
If you're looking for some homemade style breakfast, then definitely come here! I loved the breakfast burrito, and their house style potatoes made it 10 times better. Highly recommended!

So Jeromy and I thought we'd try somewhere new for breakfast. This place came up so we gave it a try. Breakfast was ok. Didn't care to much for there country gravy (had way better). Jeromy said there home fried potatoes were delicious. Service was good. Have to say the place was very busy. We'll probably give it another try just order something different.

After a long day of traveling we wound up in Vegas hungry for a good breakfast. We found Jamms to be all that we wanted and more.  Friendly service, great food And the bread bowls were delicious and innovative.  I like their menu that has classics and creative dishes for all the "Foodies" out there.  We'll be back!

We went over the weekend with my extended family hoping to get some yummy breakfast, but were very disappointed. We called ahead to make reservations since we had quite a few people and were told the wait was 15 minutes. We got there and the wait was 20 minutes, but we waited over 30 minutes before we went in and asked for an update. There was a large empty booth that we requested, but they said they would not allow us to use it since they didn't think we would fit. They didn't even let us try, and the majority of our party was small children, so we would have fit. They then told us the only way to let us eat was to put us at two tables at opposite sides of the restaurant. It was very frustrating. By that time we had been there about 40 minutes and everyone was getting very hangry. We ended up having to just go somewhere else. We wish they would have just told us they didn't have room for that many people when we originally called so we didn't waste our time. None of us will be going back after the horrible service we received.
I've been coming here for at least 10 years. Always excellent service and the food is amazing. Get the pot of bread every single time. It is soooo good.
I love to go here, I got water and orange juice and I got the babalama omelette and I got the pot of bread and thanks for the food I got good breakfast there and that's the review .

I'm the type of person that once I find a dish I love; I never really try anything else. And at Jamms, the Irish skillet is my favorite! Potatoes, corned beef, onions, and smothered in cheese... yummy! It's a lot of food (can't possibly finish it) and at $10, not overly priced.  Today I tried the pumpkin spice pot of bread and it was alright. Not too bad.  

I really like this place. The service is always good and they always give you gum on the way out. LOL
I love this place!  A little ma & pop place & Sandy was my server again.  Super sweet & always packed.  Had an inlet with home style potatoes & a honey bacon bun

I wish this was closer to me because I really enjoyed their food. I went there a few months ago with my husband and his brother and sister in law, and I wish I can go more often if it wasn't for the distance. I ordered the corned beef egg Benedict, and it was great! I've had quite a few egg Benedicts, and I would say this one is definitely the best. We went there on a Sunday, and there wasn't a long wait to get seated. Maybe we just got lucky? I don't know, but I definitely approve.
Always great get try something new every time .Today it Calif eggs Benedict with turkey and avocado..  pot of cheddar cheese and jalapeño bread so good

This was our last day in Vegas and after we checked out of hotel we decided to grab some breakfast. My wife looked online and found the top 10 breakfast places in Vegas. We were on our way to jamms. I didn't expect much but when we came it the place was packed but we were seated within 10 minutes. Great menu with great prices. I got the hungry lion breakfast. 2 eggs 2 bacon 2 sausage and ham 2 pancakes.  It was amazing. Best pancakes ever.  Also the potted bread it out of this world good.  So if you're looking for s place away from the strip for breakfast I would highly recommend Jamms

This is probably the best place to eat if you are feeling for something homey. Sandy omelette brings joy to your taste buds and the corn beef hash is simple but it won't taste the same anywhere else. The coffee is freshly brewed served in great looking jamms mugs that you can purchase while checking out. The staff is very friendly and attentive giving it the feeling of small town dinner.

The pot of bread! So. Good. 
The portions are huge and the food is good. Came with 5 other picky eaters and everyone was content. The garbage salad was bustling over. The pancakes were delicious and fluffy. The omelets (Sandy & Denver) were delicious. Yes I sampled everyone's food. The service was great. Mom was pleased with herself for finding this place on yelp off the strip. Well worth the trip!

Every time I have been here the food has been good - not great - but good. Not so today. I ordered eggs benedict and my wife got steak and eggs. Both were marginal. One of my eggs was hard boiled and the other was perfect. The Hollandaise sauce was basically tasteless. I didn't finish my meal and left the one hard boiled egg - no comment from the waitress. My wife's steak was overcooked (supposed to be medium) and had a strange taste. She ate less than half of her meal. At the check out counter the lady asked how our meals were. I said fair. No comment. I asked about purchasing another cup that I had purchased the last time we were here. I told her that the wording had come off in the dish washer and I wanted one like my coffee was served in - raised printing not just painted on. I was then presumed to be a complainer and she copped an attitude. Her tone changed and I gave up, figuring I wouldn't get anywhere here. Too bad really. You can get a marginal meal anywhere and any time,so it is a shame that she got huffy with me. Oh well !!
Nothing fancy or pretentious, which is exactly what they seem to want. Just good food, reasonably priced, and friendly attentive service. If you're looking for more then that, go to the Strip

Service was a little scarce, seems to be only one server for our half of the restaurant. Biscuits and gravy are bland, bacon is good though. This is my first time here, so I'm sure they should have other menu items that should be good to constitute a 4 out of 5 star rating.
Good breakfast. The service was good,  the little muffin the give you for checking in was delicious.

I've been coming to this place for years they have an amazing breakfast with a price that is very reasonable I recommend this place to anybody that wants to sit down and have a good time with their family
This was an amazing stop on our Vegas adventure. Love off the path finds. The pot of bread is amazing, so worth the trip. It's also a great atmosphere

With its homey atmosphere and tasty selection of breakfast favorites, Jamms Restaurant comes out to a respectable 4 star rating.

Service: 5/5
Our servers were polite and helpful when it came to selecting drinks and foods from the menu.  The food came out very quickly even though the restaurant was at full capacity, and the coffee was also given to us nice and hot.  We received a free pot of bread for checking in on Yelp!

Food: 4/5
Our main dishes were on our table less than 10 mins after we ordered it.  Somewhere before it came, we received our pots of bread.  I've had better, but it wasn't too bad.  It was just tad heavier and drier than what I personally prefer.  The food was decent.  I'd say its a tier above a typical Denny's or IHOP for sure.

Location: 4/5
The atmosphere of the place has an early 80's late 70's breakfast diner sort of feel to it.  Very warm with some character.  It pairs nicely with their breakfast selection, and I could see this place being a regular breakfast joint for people to go to and start their mornings in.

Overall: 4/5

Very good service from start to finish. I got the chicken and waffles, which were great the waffle was kinda regular but the chicken was above average. The hot tea my gf ordered came in a cute tea pot with honey packets. I can also add the side of hash browns were very good and one of the best I've had outside my house.  All in all a very warm feeling restaurant and great food, you won't be disappointed at all, will defently recommend this place to anyone!
Always busy cos the food is always good! Waffles, pancakes, skillet breakfasts and grits with their large cups of coffee!

Had been hearing about this place and decided to stop by yesterday. Had the chicken fried steak, scrambled eggs, hash browns & cinnamon pot of bread. The best thing was the bread. Steak size was kinda small & gravy was bland. Small amount of hash browns. Not worth $12

I am one of those lovely ladies who is unusually obsessed with carbs. I say unusual, but in reality I believe there must be a lot of people like me in the world because restaurants like this keep using the bread to draw us in! Their little bread pots are everything I need in life! They always serve the plain and cinnamon and then have a special bread of the day. I never normally like the bread of the days as much, so I stick to the plain. I hate to say this, but the rest of their food is probably a three star total. It's delicious breakfast food but nothing spectacular or different. Come for the bread, get fat for the bread, die for the bread. I just made them a new slogan! 

A lot of older people go here, it seems to be their customer base. This is fine, except for sometimes I feel like I don't get good service because of my age. They aren't rude, they just aren't super accommodating. I'm not a teenager or anything but I try to go with my mom to make sure we are taken care of right. Still, love this place!!

We initially ordered food to dine in but unfortunately had to take it to go due to an appointment I had. Our waitress was kind and understanding about our sudden change. 

Jamms reminds me of home cooked breakfast comfort food. Their omelets are generous and those hash browns are so good. They are known for something called a pot-of-bread, which looks a little bit like a tiny Yorkshire pudding married to a dinner roll. We tried the plain and the cinnamon raisin, and honestly you can't go wrong with either. The prices are reasonable and the interior has quite a bit of seating. Service is very friendly as well. 

Cute little breakfast spot with good food!

Dang, are they busy. I shouldn't be surprised though since it was a sat morning. Wasn't too long of a wait considering we have six people in our group. Ten minutes maybe? 

Checked in and received my free pot of bread. Pretty cool. I love free items. The cream cheese frosting isn't too sweet and I tried the new chocolate chip cinnamon raisin bread.

We all were starving so I only got a few pictures in. I will talk about the food I did try.

The Belgium waffle is large and tasty. Actually, all the plates are huge, so come with a huge appetite, or expect to take food home. Apple cinnamon French toast is ridiculously big and sweet. Too sweet for my liking but it might just hit the spot for those of you with a huge sweet tooth. Large enough for two or three people to share. I got the biscuits and gravy, which were delicious. I practically had to lick the plate clean. If it weren't for the biscuits and gravy this probably would have been a. Three star review. 

Everyone else loved their items, but I didn't get to try them. Next time, I say!

Waitress was great at constantly topping off our coffee and bringing more creamer too. Considering how busy they were I would have never known considering how often she visited out able. Great!

For a good, home cooked, large portioned, home type feeling restaurant this is your place to eat.
Large menu with great selections. Customer service was great out waitress was very attentive. I ordered Eggs Benedict, Very yummy and there signature "Pot of Bread" is delish.. I will be returning...
I wasn't too impressed. The eggs didn't seem to be scrambled fresh. Likely bladder eggs. We went to Mr. Mama's the day before it was excellent. Highly recommend there instead.

Best time to go eat here is during the week. Saturday and Sunday you will be waiting a while. All their staff is so kind. The pot o bread is always delicious. I had salted caramel today and it did not disappoint. I always get the same thing, eggs Benedict, and it's always as good as the last time. Love how their food is consistent and delicious every time.

The greeting at the front door is warm and inviting.  I love how they change the window paintings periodically.  The wait can be long, so come a bit earlier.  The decor is greasy-spponish, but everything seems clean.  

There's so much on the menu, that you can find something you like.  Avoid the steak and eggs.  Chicken and waffles are very good.  Egg white omelettes excellent...in fact everything here is pretty solid.  Kids love the strawberry waffles, the s'mores pancakes (seriously, which kid wouldn't).  The regular coffee is good, but the coffee press is worth looking like a nouveau french pretentious wannabe intellectual.  Yep, it's that good.  

Again, a good place to start the day.

Jamm's was smart to offer the Yelp deal of free bread.Those are DELICOUS. I am not even a big bread fan. I liked the cinnamon one the best. It wasnt heavily drenched in sugar, but just enough. The portion is a good amount. I had Joes omelet which was actually a little heavy on the mushroom but not enough meat, but overall it was still great. Not to mention the  hash browns were pretty tasty. The coffee is OK but not the best. I would definitely recommend it again.

Love this place for brunch... they are often busy and they need a bigger location as its always pretty crowded inside. We love their bread bowls,  breakfast burritos and chicken and waffle sandwich. I recommend this place to everybody wish their hours were longer though :)

The staff is always friendly and usually very quick to help you. We eat here once a week and the food is alway delicious and delivered in a timely manner. I would recommend this place to anyone who is looking for a new breakfast spot. The wait is usually about 30 minutes on the weekends but it is well worth it. Their food is reasonably priced and superb.

homefries and corn beef hash are one of the best i have had 
specially bread was excellent 
worth the trip off the strip for breakfast
Great hole in the wall eatery. The food is good staff is really nice and attentive. Sat thru morning rush on a Friday. Tables stayed full.
Oh my god! Their food is amazing! Homemade goodness!! Service was great an friendly. Place was busy but we still got out food quick!! On our honeymoon an so far this place was the best
The best home style restaurant you'll find anywhere! Amazing food, great portions. The best country fried steak in Nevada and the best place to find grits!

One of the most delicious breakfast of my life. I was there a few months ago and I still remember the wonderful taste... 
the service is incredible, they're fast, friendly and know the menu like their first name! Although the place is small, it never feels too crowded.
The portions are HUGE & were served nice and Hot. 
I cannot wait to be back!

I admit that I definitely prejudged this place to probably have mediocre food just because of the shopping center. I was definitely wrong and the food here is phenomenal. The Reuben and corned beef hash dishes are all delicious here.

Good just got better. We've been going to Jamms for years, as we love their large selection of yummy omelettes and their pot of bread. We went a couple of months ago and learned they now have cinnamon raisin pot of bread. Yum!

How could i have not written this review already - I thought i had! This place was SUPERB. OMG. The food was a plenty, the server was so sweet; not too attentive, but checked to make sure we were ok and happy with our food. The prices were also great for all the food you get!

I had chicken and waffles and it was amazing. Many places try to make their chicken and waffles confusing/adding too many other ingredients. Simple is best, and Jamms did that. yum! friend had a mix of stuff; grits, bacon, eggs, hash browns, and we got a free pot of bread, i think it's called, from my check-in on yelp.

If you go here, be ready to eat a lot, and be ready to take a nap after. The prices are great, and it is so worth your money!
We will be coming back my 4 hungry picky kids loved it.  All of our food was made fresh.  Love this plAce

How is this place getting so many great reviews.  The food was so bland and lifeless.  My wife thought it was 2 stars at best, but I guess I am a sucker for any breakfast.  We both got menu items that had a specialty star next to it even.  Service was prompt and friendly so I guess 3 stars is about right.
Breakfast joints tend to disappoint me, but not Jamms. The service was great. I felt like i was being served by clones of my mom. You know how that is. Food was good and reasonably priced.

One of the best breakfast places I've been to in Vegas. There was a long wait but it was totally worth it.  There's a reason places like this get packed. Their signature item, the Pot Bread, was just ok. We head the cinnamon raisin and it was good but nothing really special.  My husband had the meat lovers omelet and OMG meat.  I had the reuben benedict, the English muffin was nice and crispy, eggs well cooked, hollandaise was missing a bit of bite and the whole thing was a little under salted but most things are for me. The coffee cups are huge for a diner and they have great coffee.  Great service and pricing is on par with larger breakfast chains like IHOP. Overall great experience, will definitely be back.

Awful awful awful service and food!
What a waste!!!!!!! We will never return to this place that we fell in love with not too long ago. This is my 5th visit here and it was so awful that I do NOT want to ever return! First off we saw our food sitting in the window for a long time and of course it was COLD! My friend didn't even eat her entree and when the awful waitress picked up a full plate of food she didn't even ask if there was anything wrong! We ended up paying that entire bill and because my friends are waitresses they believe in karma and still left that lazy no good waitress a $5 tip! 
Our Irish skillet was so awful I only ate a few bites. The pot o bread was doughy and not fully baked! Even the hot water to the hot tea was warm! Really?!?!?! 
AWFUL AWFUL AWFUL!!!!!!!!!!!! 
Never again!!!!!!

We're visiting from out of town.  We didn't want to eat breakfast on the strip,  so we decided to try Jamms based on the reviews. The outside isn't much to look at but don't let that fool you.  Amazing customer service.  Friendly staff and even better food! My kids got some specialty pancakes and waffles.  I got the California eggs Benedict.  Everything was delicious.  Great prices too.  I highly recommend.

I'm not usually disappointed with restaurants, but after continuous rave reviews and legends of the Pot of Bread, I think I expected a little more than meh. 

I went into Jamms with an open mind and was immediately struck by the prices. Over $2 for hollandaise? $2.75 for coffee? Almost all entrees at least $10? Jamms at least makes it up to you by providing a large portion for every full size meal you order. However, on a light wallet, I decided to stick to their small plates menu, which was actually quite a good value. 

For $4, I got half of a Smores waffle, complete with honey, chocolate chips, and marshmallows. The toppings were great: it's hard to screw up chocolate and marshmallows, after all. However, the waffle was shockingly stale. Every bite I took, it seemed as if it was getting harder and harder to chew, until eventually, I was having a hard time even cutting the waffle into pieces. Luckily, the chocolate and honey masked the almost tasteless and stale waffle. Still: not a good sign.

Next, for $5, I chose the option of the Reuben Benedict, a supposed fan favorite take on the typical eggs benedict. It was your typical benedict, with an english muffin, an egg, and hollandaise. This version, however, replaced the Canadian bacon with some corned beef. (Thank god: I eventually tried the normal egg benedict, and the ham was chewy and cold.) For a signature menu item, it fell flat. The english muffin had a strange rancid taste, and the corned beef was lacking in both amount and flavor. While the Canadian bacon might have a worse taste, it at least was a better value!

My girlfriend had the Bananas Foster pancakes, and while I personally didn't try them, she commented on the poor quality bananas and insisted that the IHOP version was superior.

Finally, my ultimate disappointment was in the $1.95 Pot of Bread. This is the thing Jamms is known for. It's the thing I was excited for, and the thing I had heard so much about from my companions. And, unfortunately, it was the thing that sucked the most. I ended up with the cinnamon raisin pot, but the expanded bread on top was stale and difficult to eat. For such a small pot, I was amazed at the struggle. It simply tasted old, and I wondered how long it had been sitting in the kitchen. The only "soft" part was at the very bottom, and there surely wasn't much to go around. The cinnamon doesn't add much, but I shudder to think of how it tasted without it. I also tried some of the peppermint Pot of Bread, and while it was remarkably better, it may have been because of the outlandish amount of frosting coated on the bread. The Pot of Bread may have been the worst $2 I've spent all month, and, quite frankly, the free bread at Outback has far more flavor and is actually consumable. 

Jamms was a fun attempt at trying something new, but breakfast foods can be hard to get right, especially with such a limited menu. The service was great, but I had hoped for a bit more. Instead, I left wishing I had gone to Denny's.

I don't even have the words to express how great this place is. Sandy was our waitress and was excellent despite the packed restaurant. We decided to sit at the bar to avoid the wait and the staff was quite exceptional. Not only was the service remarkable, the food was fantastic! Thank goodness there is a "tapas" menu because I wanted to try everything! I ordered three different tapas and loved every single one of them. My boyfriend ordered the corned beef hash and that was delicious as well! We will most definitely be returning to this restaurant!
Great Cuban sandwich and sweet potato fries. Would eat here's often when I worked at the H&R Block around the corner.

we've been to Jamms twice in the last 2 weeks. they are right by our house and perfect for our "lazy Mondays" when we don't feel like cooking. they present themselves with a Paris-cafe-esque feel. its cozy & comfortable.
my hubby & i have plant-based diets, and although the vegan-options are few, we still love enjoying a vegetarian meal here. their bread-pots are delicious and we've enjoyed all food items we've ordered. the waitresses seem to commit to the Jamms claim "enter as strangers, leave as friends". we've had great servers & all great interactions w/ the staff. we always feel welcome and valued.
My boyfriend and I came here for our first time to try it out and it was amazing!! Loved the environment and of course the food. The service was great. Wil be coming back for sure.
The chicken fried steak is awesome! My favorite though is the potato pancakes!!

One of my favorite places for breakfast. Servers hostess bussers are always very nice and attentive. 
Food is perfect. Nothing fancy, just a great breakfast. Coffee mug is large enough and never gets cold.

My husband and I came here because of seeing the Man finds food episode in vegas. The Jamminator sounded too good to be true!!: French toast fried brioche bun, pastrami, sauerkraut, cheese, omelette patty! The result was something that I don't think was made with any love. The meat was skimpy and so was the sauerkraut. I was very underwhelmed.

Everyone is raving about the pot of bread, which I got for free for checkin in, it was good but not amazing. Should've been served warm, ours was cold.

Our service was good, the waitress was fast and attentive. 

I don't see myself coming back but it was worth a try!

Solid breakfast food at reasonable prices. I got a "reuben omelet" and enjoyed it very much. The portions are large, the service is friendly, and they keep the coffee cups filled. What more can you ask for from a simple place like this? Great job, Jamm's. I'll come back whenever I'm in Vegas....

This place was amazing. The staff was friendly and cheerful. They were efficient and energetic. They checked on us frequently and when my order wasn't to my liking even took it off my tab because I don't eat eggs and didn't know eggs were in what I ordered. Shirley is amazing! We will be back there for sure, food is great for sure but the staff is definitely top notch!

Stopped in to get some breakfast before a long day of running errands.  I had scrambled eggs with sausage and home fries.  I love the pot of bread, it was delicious.  I'm not a fan of onions and peppers in my home fries, so I didn't eat them.  Everything else tasted good, but I would love for them to have an option of no onions and peppers.  Great service, very friendly staff and priced reasonably.
