Such a fun breakfast place, amazing down-home favorites with some new twists. Popover bread is delicious. Coffee and hot chocolate are perfect! Only problem is it's a small space so there's always a wait

Jamm's is a great breakfast/lunch option tucked in a shopping plaza on the corner of Charleston and Rainbow. Although there are a lot of options for this type of fare, Jamm's remains one of my favorites for a simple, but well prepared breakfast.

I have a couple of criterium for an acceptable breakfast restaurant, those including good coffee, has waffles, and offers crispy, shredded hash browns as a potato option.  Jamm's offers all of
these (although I wish they had thinner waffles as well as Belgian).  They do; however, serve their coffee in a nice large mug and are somewhat known for their pots of bread (a sweet yeast roll marbled with different flavors).   My favorite order is the waffle with a side of their bacon. It's always served perfectly crisp. Although I do not eat eggs, the other half loves their omelets and always has a cinnamon raisin pot of bread. 

Jamm's remains one of my go-to breakfast spots in Vegas because of their traditional menu, good service, and easy location. It does get very busy on the weekends, but it's easy to figure out when the wait will be the most manageable and try them... I'm sure it won't be your list visit!

We came in on a Tuesday morning around 11 and the place was already hoppin'. We waited for a few minutes by the counter - they have a couple benches there and it's a quick turnaround. 

Shannon (Shay) was our server, she was incredibly nice and very attentive. I ordered the corned beef hash ($6 side, $2.75 coffee) and loved both - 5 stars. I mixed the seasoned salt and mild Tabasco together (both on the tables) and had the saltiest, corned beefiest, hashiest breakfast ever. So good, and so unassuming of a menu item. The omelettes get much more play.

My bf ordered an omelette, and I thought the steak was pretty dry (losing a star), but it had a ton of cheddar on it. The hash browns are definitely made in-house and are delicious - I recommend pairing them with the hash. :-)

 Very cozy atmosphere that gets busy, but is an excellent spot for families. I also like that they give out free gum at the counter. I saw a lot of grandmas today, and they all looked pretty stoked. 

Free "Pot of Bread" with check-in. Give em' a try!

Just had to write a review because it is very rare that from the time you walk in to the time you leave the staff was so friendly food was fabulous the bread in the pot YUMMY  they are only open for Breakfast and lunch but if you get a chance stop by you wont be disappointed

I just licked my plate clean. I am not ashamed. 

Got to donate to three square, have endless mugs of diner coffee, and try the "Reuben BreakfastRito"... Which was from the first bite insanely delicious. I had it w the hollandaise. My god. 

Ran me 9.99 and they gave me 10% for three square donation. Shay was sweet... On it... And gone when she wasn't needed. I really recommend bringing a family member or someone you love and just relaxing like it's Sunday morning. 

12:30pm on a Thursday and got a seat right away, but it was busy. Good was fast and atomically hot. Lots of love.

So good. So glad I just happened to see this place out of the corner of my eye. It's the perfect place for a breakfast spot. Provides many great signature options, and there bread in a cup is amazing. I got the blue berry it was so good.
One of the best breakfast restaurants to go to! Fast service and most importantly fast food comes out!! Biscuits and gravy is a must try

We're so happy when We find a new place like this 
The food was so good and the flavor really fresh the service was very nice. my server was devyn she looked very joyful while taking our order. 
Of course we  will be back.

Hello deliciousness! I've heard great things about this place and was eager to try it out and I'm so glad I did! The food was great and the service was great! The reason I give it four stars is that the place is a little out of date. Also, Seating is limited so if you have a big party you're not able to sit at one table. Besides that I am now a regular customer. :)
One of the best places to eat when I come home to Vegas! The staff and owners always show lots of love !!!! #lovethisplace
Our server is Sherlie and I am so grateful for her service waiting us. We didn't have to keep asking for anything, she is amazing, kind and thinks ahead! Deserves a raise

Met my buddy here for breakfast, recommended by him. I have to say I was very impressed.  He said anyrhing I order will be good. So I go for the country fried steak. It was simply scrumptious.  Then the hash browns. Oh my, cooked perfect. It's one of my indicators to knowing a good cook in the kitchen. Also hanb the bread in the pan. This is one of their specialties. Great stuff. Needless to say this will be another one of my must stop places while in Las Vegas and will be bringing all who come.

Brought the kids in for a weekend breakfast.  They were pretty busy but we were seated quickly.  I ordered the Reuben Benedict and the kids all got the Lumberjack Jr's.  My benedict was nothing special.  The corned beef being the only thing making it somewhat like a Reuben.  I love eggs benedict.  I guess I just expected more.  Another element or two of the Reuben would have improved it.  The kids were happy with their meals.  Service was ok.  They were busy so I don't really fault them for that.  Overall I would give them another try if I was in the area.  

They don't take Discover.

Excellent food! Our waitress Staci was genuine and funny, also knowledgable and gave great recommendations. We had the French toast, breakfast burrito, Belgian waffle, and Reuben eggs Benedict....all was amazing! What a cool hole in the wall breakfast spot. Less than 10 minute wait on a Saturday morning. Will be back next time we're in Vegas.

Another great breakfast find in the Vegas area!

Well, it wasn't necessarily a 'find' considering we attempted to roll through during a prior LV trip and the line was out the door. This time, we walked right in and found a seat without a problem.  

To share, we ordered French toast sticks and our Yelp check-in came with a free order of 'pot' bread. Who knew Vegas could consistently dish out amazing pieces of breaded sweetness!? The French toast sticks were a crisp golden brown, doused with cinnamon & powdered sugar, buttered and came with a side of good ol' fashioned syrup. The pot bread was truly a surprising delight. Scratch that, the NUTELLA PEANUT BUTTER it came with was truly the surprising delight. Sooo rich, so sugary.. *Sweats profusely* I actually don't like sugar rushes. I triggered one here and don't plan on having another one anytime soon.

I grabbed the chicken fried steak in country gravy with eggs over easy and home fries. I feel like I say this every time I eat this meal at a new location, but easily one of the best chicken fried steaks I've had in awhile. HUGE portion size that could easily feed two; Breaded with seasons that tickle the senses, a milky / creamy chicken gravy, moist insides and packed with a crunch. The gravy wasn't slopped all over the plate either. Right down the center of the steak with the ends just sticking out - you know it's the real deal when you subtract the gravy and have the steak bare.. if it's good without the gravy, then you have yourself a winner. In this case it was a complete winner.. The home fries were up to par too - with caramelized onions, bell peppers, crisp edges and just enough salt.  But really, I can't believe I wasted stomach space on the sweet stuff. I was relatively upset when I realized I was already full just about halfway through.. So, I unbuckled my pants and let the button go. We were finishing this off no matter what. Every bite was savored, and not forgotten. 

Our service was great, from hostess, to waitress, to the busser who rolled through and took plates not being used as well as various staff members giving the complimentary coffee / water refill here and there. Nothing weird happened, everyone was smiling, the prices were low and my stomach was appreciative.

I drove far and wide to try this place. The reviews everywhere I looked seemed to be on fire and to be honest, breakfast is my jam. I feel like I ordered almost every breakfast item on the menu. I'm a small girl with a Man vs Food appetite when it comes to brunching. As expected everything was beyond delicious. They serve their homemade bread in it's own little dish, have you ever heard of anything so cute?  Everything was fresh, comfy seating, friendly staff and top notch delicious fluffy pancakes. If you don't love a good fluffy pancake then you must be a monster. Go to Jamms now. Go on. Calories don't count there, or at least that's what I tell myself.

Great place to stop in for some solid food.  Places like this is what I love that you dont have to eat on the strip or anything.  I had the cuban panini and my wife had a sub.  So good and they tasted well.  We also had a pot of bread and it was good as well.  Staff was friendly and this is a nice little place to come eat and relax.  Good food and Good Service.

Oy vey! There was a ninety-minute wait at the Hash House a Go Go and not even a bench to sit around and wait. Damn that Rachael Ray. Alas, I went to the Yelp app on my iPhone and found a nearby breakfast eatery that was also averaging around four stars. It literally took us about three minutes to get to Jamm's and big surprise...it's in a strip mall, our third off-the-Strip place that was in a strip mall. We noticed the place was abuzz with customers but not nearly to the level of the Hash House. There was a fifteen-minute wait here, and the diners were not nearly as fashionably attired. 

It's a modest operation, the type that has a cheery hostess and cartoon murals on the walls. The menu is pretty robust, but unlike the nearby Egg & I, there was a lot more thought and care in the execution of the dishes. Jamie W. ordered the $8.45 Reuben Omelet, which was full of strands of corned beef and mounds of sauerkraut. There was also a generous slab of Swiss cheese melted on top and a side of crispy hashed browns (see photo). I went for a similar dish, the $8.50 Irish Skillet, which had the same corned beef accompanied by diced onions, green peppers and potatoes, all mixed into scrambled eggs and melted cheddar cheese (see photo). It was a mess of high-cholesterol goodness well put together. Tasty too. 

Jamie, in a moment of insanity laced with homesickness for his Midwestern roots, also ordered the $5.25 full order of Biscuits and Country Gravy, which was a gloppy pool on a plate (see photo). I won't deny it wasn't good in a deep Southern kitchen kind of way with the biscuits sopping up all that gravy, though I attempted to re-purpose it as an extra topping for my skillet breakfast. Bloated was the way we both felt afterward but also sated. Needless to say, I also noticed they decorated the restroom stall with the same cartoon murals. Somebody must have had time on their hands. By the way, the waitress was also cheery, chatty and about nineteen. She was refilling my coffee cup with unadulterated pleasure. 

FOOD - 4 stars...country breakfasts with deli twists, well executed with simple ingredients 
AMBIANCE - 3 stars...kitchen cozy with Fingerhut touches 
SERVICE - 4 stars...cheery thy name is Jamm 
TOTAL - 4 stars...good diner-style eats can be found in a strip mall
I've been coming here for years. Great place for breakfast and lunch. Highly recommend.
Pot of bread is great and the pot of bread french toast is amazing! They are busy but efficient. Wait time on a busy Sunday was only 10 minutes.

Service 5/5 Real friendly host, servers, bus boys.  Top notch.  very friendly.  They flip the tables pretty quick.  so there was a wait when we got there but we only waited 10 minutes on a holiday with a party of 8.

Corned Beef Hash (4/5)  Real corned beef (not the canned stuff).  Tasty
Country fried steak (4/5)  Ellis Island is way better but it's good here.
Pot O Bread (1/5)  Too small.  So you don't get much and because it's so small there isn't enough chewy inside to combat the crisp outside.
Pancake combo (4/5)  Tasty pancakes.
Hash browns are perfect here.

I'd expect when you go over $10 that your portions would be a bit bigger for being off-strip.

It's pretty pricey here for being so far from the strip.

We went here on the way up to Red Rock canyon (half way from the 15 to red rock)

You get 10% off for social media but that just offsets the higher prices.

This is a classic breakfast diner! The food and staff are amazing. This was our first visit, so needless to say we couldn't decide what to get because there are so many options. The portions are large and delicious. Can't wait to come back!

For me as a Dutch girl, I see this as a typical American restaurant. The people in there were very friendly!
We came here for breakfast and ordered provance and jamms specialty omelet with toasted wheat bread only, coffee and water. 
The omelets were nice! But I've tasted them better somewhere else. The toast was very very fat, but I guess that is normal in America. The waitress checked on us several times, which is a good thing! Overall an nice breakfast for American standards.

My good friend and Muse said we were doing to Jamms. 

Jamms?  Okay...it's a cool name. I had no idea what to expect.  "Just please don't take me to any hoodrat establishments, bet?"

I've NEVER done much of anything off the strip in Vegas..and so with me now having a good friend who lives there...anyway...

She took me to Jamms and it was the funk!

I had the Signature (steak) omelet, and french toast made with CORN FLAKE BATTER. Whaaaat???

She had the Country Skillett and an order of the Pot-O-Bread. (She was sweet enough to get me one to go). GOOD STUFF.!!! It's like a little..pot..of...sweet bread (blueberry, cinnamon)...

If you're ever in Vegas, you'll have plenty of nice buffet eating (Bellagiio, MGM Grand...)...but if you wanna venture off the strip...go to Jamms.

Jamms is the funk!

This place is amazing! First off, YOU MUST ORDER A POT OF BREAD! If you don't, you're doing yourself a disservice (its amazing). I got the California eggs Benedict and it was fantastic. But what was the best was my dad got the Jamminator, which I highly recommend! The pretzel bun is crazy good and the crispy fries are fried to perfection.

I was excited to try this place after a coworker kept telling me how great it was. I went on a Saturday afternoon and waited about 30 minutes to be seated. People kept getting in line so I figured the wait must be worth it. 

While in line, I couldn't help noticing that there were 3 hostesses/cashiers just chit chatting about their drunken shenanigans from the night before. Not very professional but I wasn't there for them... I was there for the food!

When we were finally seated, a lovely gentleman came by and got our drink order. The server took about 10 minutes to come to our table. Longer than I would have liked, but again I wanted to try this food. 

My companion and I ordered two separate dishes with the intention of sharing. I ordered the Sandi Omelet (bacon, cheddar cheese, green pepper, and sour cream) with homefries. My companion ordered the steak and eggs. We both ordered the cinnamon raisin pot of bread. 

The gentleman that took our drink order brought us our coffee and checked on us more than our server.  His service was perhaps the best part of our visit. 


Cinnamon Raisin Pot of Bread- was disappointing. It was dry and had no raisins on the inside which leads me to believe it's the same dough as the pot of bread that's been brushed with butter and sprinkled with cinnamon sugar and a few raisins before baking. 

Sandi Omelet- it's an Omelet that's folded over and has full size bacon strips tucked into the center. Not what I was expecting. It was an average omelet. It's saving grace was the salsa although I'm still not sure how salsa fits into the Irish theme of the restaurant. The homefries tasted as if they had been made in a large batch and were reheated. 

Steak and Eggs- had high hopes when I saw that they had a grill to cook their steaks. Big let down. The meat tasted as if it had been in the fridge for far too long. Otherwise cooked fine, but flavor was off. 

Overall, I don't think this restaurant lives up to the hype.

I love this restaurant. Their cute decor makes it a home-y feel. We came for weekend brunch and the place was packed. My party of 4 and I had to wait about 5 minutes for a table.

In my opinion, Their breakfast is almost, if not better, than the Egg and I. Service was awesome, food tasted great...everything came out pippin hot and fresh and the prices are on point. 

Also, anybody who loves biscuits and gravy would loveeeee it here. Their gravy had chunks of meat in it. Yummy!! =)

Just moved to las Vegas and went here for the first time with my dad that was visiting, our server Devin was awesome! I ordered the chicken and waffle BLT with skinny fries and she recommended ranch with them.  The whole meal was delicious. And the service was fast and accurate.  Thank you!

So happy we gave this place a shot.  My boyfriend and I are from the east coast and found out this place was opened by a couple from there.  The service was good and the food was better.  The atmosphere is very diner oriented.  I got the breakfast burrito and it was awesome.  The portion was a good size, I was very surprised I was able to eat the whole thing.  I will be going back.

Food was great. Came out quick. Waiter was ok, had to ask to place my order and my check at the end because she took a while coming back to the table. Maybe because it was Saturday morning and busy. Overall, great experience, friendly, and great food with affordable prices!
Great spot for breakfast. The service was fantastic. Definitely worth the short drive from the Strip.

James is the best breakfast place in Vegas!  Their pots of bread are amazing and every single time we come here the food and service are spot on!!! If you feel like lunch their burgers and sandwiches are always great!

Had the Texas chili omelet and the smores waffle.
The chili had great flavor and combined well with the omelet, very good and have never had shutting like it.
Can't really go wing with a smores waffle! The chocolate part of the smores were chocolate chips that weren't melted and that was a little weird, probably would have been better if they were.
The potatoes or home fries served with the omelet were better than most.
The lemonade was delicious, no minute maid here!
The service was fast and friendly. The atmosphere was cozy like grandma's house:)

Strange a place called jamms only had the little Welch's packets of jelly!

Check it out, it's worth it:)

This place is my favorite restaurant for breakfast! I love this place. My wife and I have been coming here for about 8 years. The menu has a lot of choices and everything is made fresh every day. Yummmmmm

Since Jamms is right across the street from where I live it is my go to weekend breakfast treat. I can always get a seat at the counter no matter how long of a wait it is for a table.  Jamms has illi coffee from Italy and you have the option of the little creamers in the plastic cups or milk served in a mini glass container. The also have a different flavor of their pot of bread weekly. I usually get something off of the breakfast menu but they have great soups and sandwiches too!
Great customer service and you also get 10% off when you check in on social media. Great food.

It is my first visit here and the first thing that pleased me was their excellent buser named Victor. Great customer service is very hard to come by especially during busier times of the day.  Immediately greeted my party and I with a genuine smile and catered to us the entire time we were here.  Their food is good and comforting. But what made the visit great was Victor and his hard work.  I watched him take care of other parties with the same passion and care & you can tell her truly loves his job here.  Great asset to the establishment, our food server was also great and courteous. I didn't catch her name however but she greeted normal customers by their names.  Very welcoming atmosphere.  From start to finish. The hostess was also very nice and welcoming. Thank you for a great first visit I will be back in the future for sure.

first time coming here , me and my boyfriend , and our waitress (Shay) was amazing and super sweet !! great energy , made my experience here perfect . definitely recommend this place to anyone ! food is awesome !!! ((:

This is my breakfast place of choice.  I love the food.  They have these French toast stick fries and they are awesome.  The service has always been good and never been disappointed any time I have ever been here.   A few times it has been busy but the staff seamed to get everyone fed and happy in no time.  I would recommend this place to anyone who likes good food.

Jamms is one of the best breakfast/lunch restaurants that I have been to here in Vegas. From their larger than life pancakes, to their soups and sandwiches; this is the place to be! Whenever you check into yelp you receive a free pot of bread. The pot of breads are really tasty as well. The waitresses are professional and have a great demeanor. Make sure to come early because this place fills up quick. I suggest ordering their chicken noodle soup which has thick noodles and large chucks of chicken as well as soft carrots and celery. Jamms is the place to be for a great meal, affordable, and perfect for groups.
This place does not disappoint on the breakfast. Even the long wait is worth it. Only 4 stars this time around because the kept getting my mom's drink order wrong.

I love this place. The decor reminds me of the mom and pop restaurants back home. Recently tried the Irish Skillet. It was awesome. My wife doesn't even like hash and she liked this item. I haven't tried anything on the lunch menu yet because I am always in the mood for eggs and bacon. If you go on the weekends prepare to wait. It is a bit small and always busy.
Got the individual tapas items for breakfast. Had the Reuben eggs benedict very good. Great service too.

I came here last week when I was on my road trip. I wanted to stop and see Las Vegas for a bit, even though it was so hot. I decided to find a local place to eat. Jamms Restaurant was on the top of the recommended lists on various websites. I definitely do not regret my decision to come here... The service was very good, even though the waitress accidentally forgot my honey mustard, but she apologized for it and still did a good job otherwise. I ordered an omelet with home potatoes, along with the plain flavor for the pot of the bread. It was a good experience. I will stop by the next time I come to Las Vegas. It'd definitely be a good hangover breakfast for those who choose to party and gamble at the night.

Best Brunch restaurant in Las Vegas!
Highly recommend the eggs Benedict and Chinese Chicken Salad 
Enough to take home for later

We are just in town for the weekend and was looking for a little restaurant away from the strip and typical tourist areas. I have to say after finding this place on yelp, I couldn't be any more satisfied that we decided to come here. All staff is extremely friendly and welcoming, the coffee is amazing and the food as well. We were seated quick and the food was out to us quickly too. If you are visiting and want a good friendly small little local restaurant, you should get an uber or taxi and check it out.

My husband and I decided to have a late breakfast.  I ordered a typical breakfast; pancakes, eggs, and bacon. My husband ordered a bacon, tomato, avocado, green onion omelette with breakfast potatoes. We also ordered something called a pot of bread. The pot of bread was homemade bread that was baked in a muffin ten. You could tell that this bread was  homemade and freshly made. It was very good. The service was excellent and we would definitely come back to Jamm's restaurant.
This has been, hands down, the best breakfast we have had in Vegas.  We make it a point to try different restaurants around town.  Jamms will NOT disappoint!!
The food was decent, but the customer service was off the chain. Super nice people. That is why I gave this place 5 stars!
Great food and service! We live right around the corner and go here regularly. My husband always gets the Reuben Benedict and I love the French toast. Biscuits and gravy are really good too.

Surprisingly we got seated right as soon as we walked in. I ordered the Jamms breakfast sandwich which had cheese egg and ham. It was very yummy but I did expect it to be a bit bigger. Instead of hash browns I ordered the home style fries which looked like mashed potatoes with bits of tomatoes and other stuff; didn't really like them. Over all the service was great and food was good for a quick breakfast stop. Super affordable too!

We discovered this place through yelp on a recent trip to vegas. We were getting a little sick of over priced buffets and dinging slot machines, so we strolled on over to Jamm's and have made it our go to breakfast trip whenever we're visiting Vegas. 

I'm a coffee fiend, I strongly judge places by their coffee, and Jamm's has some damn good coffee. It's got a good flavor and it's brewed strong.

Don't be dismayed by a long wait, it's worth it.

My go to is the stuffed French toast, but if you don't have a super sweet tooth like me, I'd suggest the the Chicken BLT with Green Waffles. 

Also make a point to try out their pot of bread.

We had a fantastic time at Jamm's! The food was excellent (we had breakfast) and the service was very attentive without being overbearing. I recommend you go for a small portion if you eat the smores pancakes- our friend, who can eat - could barely eat 1.5 pancakes. We also enjoyed the "pot" of bread which was very fluffy and light; we had the cinnamon raisin version.

I have been to this hole in the wall several times now and I am always pleased and satisfied with what I choose. First let me mention there are a ton of options so it may take you awhile to choose. Also the portions are large-size so come with an appetite or be prepared to take leftovers. I was please to find they added tapas portions, smaller plate styles at half the cost.
     This particular time I got the Rueben omelette (corned beef,sauerkraut, and Swiss cheese.) The tender corned beef really went well with the tangy sweetness of the sauerkraut. Also I got the pot of bread (cinnamon and raisin with side of cream cheese icing) yummy! They did come out with a pistachio pot of bread I'm dieing to try. When you check in on yelp they give you a free pot of bread but they said they were out of pistachio which is odd because they offered it to the table next to us so I don't know. Nonetheless my meal was great.
    Now my boyfriend ordered the steak and eggs. I warned him about ordering steak at a place that doesn't really specialize in that bc you can't expect much from a small breakfast joint but he took the risk lol. Of course I was right the steak looked like a chewed up oversized piece of bacon. He said it was tough, chewey, and tasted kind of like an old belt. However the scrambled eggs were plain and to be expected. The pancakes were really good and fluffy.
    Overall everything was great on my behalf and you cant beat the cost we spent under $30. Word of advice stick with breakfast it's what they are known for and don't order the steak.....obviously.
I love Jamms... they have one of the best breakfast restaurants in Vegas.  Their pot of bread is a must!!

I go here maybe twice a week now. One of my favorite places. I absolutely love the atmosphere. Really homey and inviting. I love when Devin is my server she's always funny and sweet. I had Shirley too.she reminds me of talking to my grandma. She is absolutely adorable. The food is always great. Whenever I take someone new there I tell them you eyes will be bigger then your stomach. And it's true. All in all you will love it

Food was okay, but service was great! Really friendly and chill environment. I got the signature omelet with a side of potatoes. It just didn't taste as good as it looked honestly. It wasn't terrible, but I just don't think I'll be back!
Love this place for breakfast! The food is amazing and I'm never disappointed! The staff is also super friendly! Highly recommend!!!

I love this place!  It's always busy, which is a good sign.  The service is always quick and no-nonsense, which I also like.  

I would have given 4 stars, but some of their food is not consistent.  I've had their Cuban sandwich, which ended up being super dry pork.  It felt like the sandwich was just dry pork and bread, when a Cuban sandwich typically has pork, ham, swiss, pickles and mustard.  Maybe they were having an off day that day, because their menu states the sandwich ingredients as such.

Their signature salad - the Jamms salad is cabbage, almonds, green onions, and sesame dressing is absolutely amazing!  It's light, crunchy and not over-dressed.  Very very good.

The corned beef hash and eggs is fatty fantasticness.

Their chilaquiles special sounded amazing, but was far from it.  It was under-seasoned, and loaded with tons of cheese.  Some may think that's a good quality, but this time it wasn't.  I wanted to taste the chips, eggs, and sauce, and the gobs of cheese made that difficult.  The beans that accompanied the dish looked as if they had gone way past their hold time, with the crunchy, crusty bits that form on the pan when they've sat there too long. 

Their pot of bread is their signature, and they do that perfectly!  It's got that fresh-out-of-the-oven temperature and smell, and when you pull it apart, it reveals light, pillowy, steamy deliciousness.    

All of these dishes were had over a couple visits.  I'll definitely go back to Jamms, but I'll get something different every time to figure out what's good and what isn't.  Right now their signature items (salad, and pot of bread) are the front-runners.

The ambience is homey, but clean.  Service is very attentive, and there's free gum at the checkout stand!

Man I had a hard time deciding how many stars to give this place.  We actually found this place by accident.  I wanted to try a place in the same strip mall and I won't give the name because that's another review.  Let's just say they sell poultry cooked different ways.  I let you do the math.  As I was bummed out driving I see a window blasted with "Best of Vegas" stickers.  I was about to eat my foot so we decided to stop in to the breakfast/lunch establishment.  As we were walking in I noted the best of stickers were kind of old.  I figured well it can't be that bad.  

We walked in  and were immediately greeted.  If I were to base the review only on the service and how friendly the employees are, then I would give it more stars.  The waitress was friendly and the guy who was filling our drinks was even more friendly.  Our 1 year old was a little fussy because she was probably hungry too.  They noticed this and brought us some crackers.  This was great!  If you are a waiter or waitress and notice a fussy kid and you know the little things that help parents then you instantly max out your tip.  Just a little piece of advise, go ahead and write that down.  

Let's take a look at the food.  I ordered the Jamm's omelet.  It had steak in it covered with a sauce.  When I looked at the steak and keep in mind I am not expecting fillet Mignon here it looked like the steak um's meat you get in your freezer aisle.  I didn't like it at all.  I think I really didn't like it because the omelet was about $10.  I guess I was just expecting more.  I did get the pot bread and it was really good.  My wife ordered the french toast and she thought it was tasty.  My daughters just at eggs and toast.  We emerged from the restaurant paying $30 for breakfast.  Ouch!  Overall I am sure at one time this place was great but as new restaurants opened it probably took away from this place.  There are a lot better breakfast places out there. Cheers!

Thinking of an omelet?  This place has them ALL!  http://www.jammsrestaurant.com/
I ordered the White Castle Omelet which was stuffed with crumbled burger!  It was huge--all of their omelets are huge!  Wilson Y. was correct when he said "The Pot of Bread is tasty and soft."  In fact, I'd try it you get to visit because the only other place I know that makes it like this is a place called the Summy House located in Manheim, PA.

Jamms is located in a strip mall along Rainbow.  Inside, it beams with natural sunlight.  The decor is upbeat with a lot of personal touches.  The staff are friendly and fast.
Awesome great corn beef hash . Tres Leche pot of bread amazing. Will stop by again if in Vegas ;-)
I love jamms been coming here for years now!! Its a great place for breakfast and i love the home like atmospbere!!
Love this place . Came here for brunch and was seated quickly and food was served in no time at all .

I wanted a different breakfast experience than another restaurant with the word 'egg' in their name so based on Yelp reviews, my husband and I decided to try this place. 
We drove a little ways from our side of town and would do it again to come back here!

It's a cute little place in a strip mall off of Rainbow & Charleston. Upon entering, we were immediately greeted and seated. Our drink orders were taken, literally the second we sat down.
Our very cheerful and friendly server asked to take our orders very soon after our drink orders were taken. Being this was our first time here, we needed a couple of minutes.

I ordered the veggie omelet and my cute husband had bacon and eggs. I really liked that the food was NOT greasy! The omelet was huge and stuffed with perfectly sauteed veggies. I had home fries that were seasoned just right, AND I really liked the fact that they didn't drench my toast with butter! My toast had just the right, even spread of butter, which is rare.

All in all, the service was great, the food was very good, and the prices were pretty much average to most other places. I would definitely make the trek to have breakfast here again.

Well this used to be our every sunday breakfast  spot.  We stopped coming for awhile due to the quality of food we felt was slipping. Today we wanted to give it another try. Service was a little slow and the food came out cold. Staff is always friendly

French Dip was very good
They got a good breakfast too
This is our favorite Breakfast place!! We love the great food and personalized service! I'd recommend it highly.
We had great time and our waitress Shirley was outstanding. Thank you guys and we will back soon!!

We had the Margie omelette and jam's French toast. Everything was super yummy! The only thing that wasn't amazing was the coffee lol. There was a looooong line to get seated but the food was worth the wait

Awful.  

The wait was about an hour on a Sunday - which is actually perfectly fine with me.  Why?

1. You know that a breakfast place is good when there's a line and full tables
2. I'll wait for a good meal, no problem

Problem was - the service was horrendous -- and so was the food.  It took the waitress 15 minutes to get to our table after being seated to ask us for drinks.  After we put in our drink order, it took another 10 minutes for us to actually get our drinks.  We spent so much time looking around trying to flag someone down (just with looks as I despise the whole hand waving thing that people do).  

When our drinks finally came, the waitress asked if we were ready to order.  As I ordered, she rushed me through any questions that I had.  For example, her question -- "wouldyoulikebreakfastpotatoeshashbrownsortoast"  She ran that sentence so quickly, I automatically "uhh....-ed" my reply.  When I said "breakfast pota----" she cut me off with a huff and replied, "it has onions and peppers and is stir fried."  

Anyhow, she continued on being rude, abrasive and hasty.  But enough about the ordering fiasco.

When I got my "signature" omelet - the "signature" sauce was dabbled on.  I mean, it literally looked like the cook took a teaspoon of the sauce and drizzled it over the omelet and left it be.  I asked for extra sauce.  The extra sauce arrived.  It was disgusting.  It tasted like clumpy flour boiled in egg yolk.  The omelet itself was dry and overcooked.  The steak inside of it was bland, chewy and grey.

My fiance's eggs benedict.  Disgusting as well.  No other way to put it.  

My niece ordered mac & cheese.  She said it was really dry and wanted to pour her milk in it.  Serious?

After our "meal" was over we paid our bill and walked on out.  The hostess tried to give us a discount of 15% for a future visit.  I politely told her she could keep it.

A great place to get classic American food. Simple prepared well comfort food. The pot o bread is light and fluffy and very tasty. They offer a la carte smaller portions of entrées which is really great for lighter eaters. The staff is friendly and always accommodating. If you check in on fb yelp or trip advisor you get 10% off your bill.

We stopped here because of the high reviews, and everything, from food to service, was 5 stars all the way. 

The small plate option is awesome. For someone like me who doesn't always eat so much for breakfast, I was able to get an omelet that was just the right size! The small plate omelet is about half the size of a regular omelet and also half the price. 

We also got their famous "pot of bread" (got a free one for checking in on Yelp!). The weekly special was jalapeño mozzarella and the classic cinnamon raisin. Both were super yummy!

Sandy was our server and she was great- very friendly and efficient with bringing our food, refilling coffee, and checking on us. I wish more places were like Jamms!

This is where you have Sunday breakfast if you're an old Jewish couple, or a non-old Jewish couple who happens to want some kick ass breakfast for a pretty reasonable price.  I've been here a few times over the years and it's always busy, but consistently good service.  The menu is what you'd expect:  pancakes, waffles, french toast and a bunch of egg-based platters, salads and the usual sandwiches such as the Club; point is, it's all good.  Most menu items can be ordered small, if you're watching your weight. Don't forget about the free pot of bread with Yelp checkin!

I honestly wasn't impressed.  The man who seated us was very unfriendly he grabbed menues and followed with "Come On" and walked off. I hesitated because I wasn't sure if he said "hold on" but then he looked back at me and my kids impatiently so that cleared things up. 

On to the food- well let's just say two orders of French toast fries and the pot of bread we ordered was not very impressive. I didn't order food but my 7 and 8 year old did. The French toast came with out powdered sugar (which was a selling point for my children when pictured on the menu) and so we had to wait for the waitress to come back to ask for it bc my daughter wouldn't touch it with out it. End result- I nibbled at it and I not my kids were impressed. Burger King had better French toast sticks... And well the pot of bread... YUCK. 

30 dollars to feed my 7 and 8 year old sub par food with moody service?... I didn't even order food... Nah I'll pass. Won't be back.

Little places like this make me LOVE Las Vegas even more!
From the outside, in the midst of the shopping plaza, a tasty little breakfast gem hidden amongst the other stores.

Let me tell you! - This is what locals look for in LV!!

First and foremost....Pot Of Bread! Say it with me..."Pot of Bread"
assorted daily flavors, freshly backed tiny single serving of delicious little mini loafs of bready, muffinish,  pop-over type things. Hell YES!!!!

Everything else was really good. Yes, we did have to salt and pepper our breakfast. In my opinion, the seasoning could be turned up a bit...ok maybe a more than a bit.
But still all the ingredients tasted fresh and made to order.

Jamms is like dining at Grams. 

Top to bottom with that old school look, closed-in booths and seating areas, plus that dated decor that is at everyone's grandparent's house. But just like your gramm gramm's house, you tend to eat all the food because it's just that good. 

No fancy frills, just down home cooking that's definitely not diet friendly, especially with what I decided to eat, The Country Skillet. A heart stopping meal filled with scrambled eggs, sausage, ham, onions, mushrooms and covered in home fries with gravy. I also got the Pot of Bread, which is on the house with a Yelp check-in, free carbs!

The skillet is huge and a very heavy meal that's perfect for sharing or that horrendous hangover that just won't seem to go away. The home fries added a great crunchy texture, which is definitely what this plate of needed with so many soft food items. Gravy, gravy, gravy, it was the perfect addition to the mushrooms and eggs and brought everything together. 

Like I said a free "Pot of Bread" with a Yelp check-in, and they offer three choices; original, cinnamon raisin and a savory flavor that I believe rotates.  I went with the basic "POB" and it was amazing. Soft, pillowy, and all of that melt in your mouth goodness, trust me check-in and be happy. 

Jamms is well, the Jam!
WONDERFUL AS ALWAYS!! I absolutely cannot get over how great this place has been over the years!! Literally our most favorite EVER!!!

This is the cutest little restaurant hidden away. And the waitress, Shirley is just so pleasant. She reminds me of the old school waitresses you see in the 50s dinners. The food was also good as well.

How is this place rated so high?  Meatlovers omelet. .does not come with cheese???  What holds it together??  Nothing!!!  Very bland.  Jamms French Toast is cereal coated bread dipped in egg milk and fried..no flavor at all.  Home Fries were potato mush with peppers and onions. Coffee --no flavor.  The Bacon was the only thing that was enjoyable.  Off The List!
Family and I loved this place. Feels like eating at Grandmothers house. The cranberry potted bread was amazing and warm, hit the spot on that cold morning.

Cute little breakfast spot located in the Albertsons shopping center. Service was fast and our food was really good! I ordered the country benedict and it had one of the best biscuits I've ever tasted in a benny! When you check in on yelp you get a free little bread basket unfortunately we realized when we got home that our waitress accidentally charged us for it and it was too far to go back.

I came here one weekend morning while out and about. The wait was about 10 minutes for 2 people. The place was packed. Wait staff was busy trying to keep up with the demands. Food was pretty average. The jalepeno pot of bread was very tasty. Service was friendly.
 My big gripe was all the yelling that took place during our meal. The ladies at the register trying to seat parties and the wait staff yelling when a table was cleared and clean. It was just not a very relaxing environment. If I wanted to hear all that squawking, I would go to my in-laws. I think there are too many other breakfast places around town that have a more warm, welcoming, and relaxing vibe that I look for.

This place is Awesome! I live in southern California but visit Vegas often and every time we come we have to stop st Jamms for breakfast. We bring our friends and family here too. The food is amazing. The staff is super friendly. This place is a must! And you have to try the stuffed French toast and pot of bread. So so good!
Great food and service was excellent. The pot of bread is definitely a winner and breakfast lovers will enjoy the selection

After reading the reviews, I had to try it.  Overall, a great little diner in amidst a strip mall.  It's quaint, with great diner service and solid good food.  They are well known for their popover bread, and you must get one when you eat there.  

Great mom and pop joint away from the strip, and well worth the drive.  I eat here at least once a week because I love their omelets.

This is my go-to spot for breakfast on the weekends.  Their Irish Skillet is amazing and doesn't have that icky corned beef from a can...it's real.  Their pot of bread is my favorites thing here.  Service is good.  Wait can be long on the weekends but it's worth it.

Fun and good. The reception from the time you walk in the door it's extremely friendly, each of the servers the same delightful approach. Menu is interesting in original and the food is delivered to the table is wonderful.

I absolutely love this place! Every time I'm in town I have to make a trip here. I usually get their California club with the fat fries. Not only is the food amazing, but the service is 100% too! Definitely recommend

I hear the food is good, unfortunately I will never find out.
The "no reservation", only "complete parties" will be seated policy sucks.
Particularly after waiting 40 minutes for a table of 5, the "pitbull" hostess could not wait 30 seconds for my kids to get out of the car and proceeded to skip our turn to seat another party of 5 that had checked in after us.
Not sure if the 2 hostesses on duty on Sunday 02.11.2018 have any vested interest in the operation, but they sure know how to be rude and unwelcoming, did I mention inconsistent / biased in the way they apply the seating policy.
I have read some great reviews about this place and I will make sure that I extensively share my experience so none of my friends / acquaintances ever gets subjected to the embarrassment I had to face.

James is my favorite breakfast spot. The service is always prompt, friendly, and create a family feel. The food is always delicious and they will alter your order to fit your needs... it my not be on the menu but they will try. I love Jamms!

I've been going to jamms since before I can remember, and I mean how can you go wrong with piping hot mini loafs of fluffy perfect carbs rising out of cute little tin pots!

They always have the white and cinnamon pot of breads and monthly they change the third flavor this time we had chocolate chip banana! 

This place is consistently good, and the people are always nice. I Usually have an omelet provencal and joe's omelet are my fave :)
Excellent gem found here in heart of Vegas. This place is your one-stop for great food!
Amazing friendly service! Great food! I have yet to have something I didn't like. So yummy!

Consistently good.  I have never been here when I wasn't greeted like a friend.  Sometimes it is so busy that I don't have enough time to wait.  They try to wait until your entire party is there before they sit you which is annoying if you are trying to save a seat but wonderful if you are a party of two trying to get in.  The food is home cooked and genuine and the Pot of bread is an added bonus.  I had the sausage and egg breakfast with home fries.  The eggs were over easy perfection and the home fries were seared with a crispy lightness that was satisfying.  Today the special pot of bread was creamy peach served with sweet cream cheese frosting on the side.  If this were close to my home I would come here a lot more often.  MMMMM!

Was looking for a great breakfast spot and we heard about Jamm's and decided to stop in. The place was packed! That's always a good sign. Waited no more than the quoted time (5 minutes) for a table. Was greeted right away. The waitress recommended the chipotle mozzarella bun. It's was wildly flavorful! There was a lot to choose from on the menu. I will have to go back and try them all. We were happy with the food and the service.
Excellent food!  You will only need to eat one meal that day.  Pots of bread are delicious!

Since visiting Jamms it is now in my immediate arsenal of go-to breakfast places. The food is just stupid good, even just an omelet is so so tasty  - not to mention they give you the option to make any omelet into a burrito- which I don't know about you - but the only thing that could make breakfast better is wrapping the whole damn thing up in a tortilla. Also their signature pot o' bread - YUMTASTIC. I love this unique element as it really sets their brand as a breakfast place apart from the rest. Sorry Denny's, I'll be at Jamms.

Great place to eat. I have lived in Vegas 14 years without ever even knowing this place existed. My sister and I found ourselves looking for a place to have lunch after my nephew's baseball game. We saw the reviews and that the restaurant was five minutes away, so we stopped in to lunch at Jamms! The place was packed. We waited about 15 minutes for a table, and another 15 for service, but the waiter kept the coffee coming so the wait was not horrible. My favorite sandwich in the world is the Reuben, and can I just say, #yum!  Freakin AWESOMENESS! I will definitely be bringing my husband with me for round numero dos!
Jams is all ways a perfect breakfast place. Pot of bread is fantastic all the employees are very nice, Sandy, Shirley and Jose. They have the best chicken noodle soup lunch

This is hands down my favorite breakfast spot in Las Vegas. The portions are huge and the food is delicious. The Babalama Omelette is my favorite but their breakfast and lunch selections are all fantastic. Get the pot of bread and enjoy a warm, fluffy slice of heaven.

Great place for brunch. The pot of breads was delicious fresh and hot! We got the cinnamon raisin and special of the week: FIG! My favorite. The steak and eggs was very tender, although the meat was a little overcooked for medium. I enjoyed the food nonetheless and would recommend coming here! Thanks for the great service and food! Oh, plus a free pot of bread with yelp check in and 10% off entire bill with a post and a hashtag of the restaurant.
Every time we come to Vegas we make sure to stop in at least once. The food is delicious. Be sure to try the Pot of Bread!!! The service is friendly and efficient. We LOVE this place!

I've been here a couple times. There is usually a small wait, however worth it every time. The staff is friendly and helpful.  Fair prices and great food are a delicious combo. I've had Maddy ' s country Benny and simple sausage and eggs, all of which were hearty meals that left little to no room for the free pot o bread with the Yelp check in.  The salads are top notch as well. You can't go wrong with Jamms.
Love Jamms! One of my favorite breakfast joints in Vegas! The Jamms French toast is amazing! And the omelettes are delish too! The service is friendly and welcoming!
Wow. Awesome breakfast, fresh hot very tasty. I think this place is better then Peppermill or hash go go. The service was outstanding.

The food is good but the presentation is too simple and unappealing. The two thin chicken strips that came with my "Chicken & Waffles" meal were disappointing but tasty. If you're looking for simple home cooking this is place is for you!

Just checked this place out for the first time.  I love going to mom and pop places.  Place was hopping and I sat at the counter.  The coffee  was decent, I ordered the pancake combo with eggs and bacon.  Portion was huge and pumpkin pancakes were fluffy with good flavor.   However, the inferior pancake syrup they used, brought it down a notch for me.  Service was good and friendly.  Menu was extensive.  The omelets looked great co.  Next time I will bring my own syrup and give them 4 stars.
Everything is delicious and the service is great! Friendly neighborhood diner. The variety of pot o breads is to die for!!
Bananas Foster Pancakes were awesome. We make time for breakfast at Jamms every time we are in Vegas. Good food, large portions, and friendly staff.
Delicious food, great prices, great service. I love coming here, always have had an exceptional time. It can get crowded and have a bit of a wait, but it is worth the wait.
Hands down amazing breakfast! Cop friendly and delicious food every time :) A never-disappointing breakfast stop for a weekend with the family OR while at work with co-workers. Love it!

I had seen Jamm's on Instagram and wanted to take my husband out for Father's Day breakfast. We arrived at 7:03 and the place immediately went from three people to nearly full in a few minutes. I was amazed at the menu choices.
My husband ordered chicken fried steak and a biscuit. He liked the crunchiness. Coffee was good. I ordered the chicken waffle BLT which includes the very fresh tomato and lettuce. I liked the concept. The chicken was ok; the waffle was better. Bacon was ok.
Our server, Jasmine, was very helpful and attentive.
I am giving this cafe four stars for Jasmine and the atmosphere of very hard working employees and clean, old school decor.
The food is a solid 3, and it is a pretty good option for breakfast.

Excellent crispy hash browns, but average omelettes and terrible coffee. Staff was efficient. Figured we'd try something new this side of town, but next time will go back to Egg and I. Otherwise an okay place.

Looking for a place to eat breakfast at and stumble upon this hidden gem off the strip.  

The tinted window hides the beauty of the inside.  Once you go inside its bright and modern.  

Greater and was seated immediately and handed a menu.  A guy with coffee pot goes around asking if you want coffee or some other beverages.  The service was fast!!! 

We ordered:

Corn beef hash and eggs with hash brown - it was so tasty and delicious.  Along with a day special of pot of bread - strawberry coconut fluff - it's to die for! 

Ruben eggs Benedict - fiancé said it was yummy and delish!! It's genuine.  

Also ordered French toast sticks-- they were very filling and heavy.  I only ate one stick.  

The food comes in good portions.  Our tummy are full and satisfied!! Oh and when you check in on yelp, you get  pot of bread for free and they have a promo when you show the server that you Instagram your food and tag them, they take 10% off your bill! 

Definitely will come back to try the other favorites on their menu next time I'm in Vegas!! 

By the way, I came in at 8:10 and was driving away at 8:40, that's how fast the service was.
Come to this place all the time. Very delicious, great feeling, and amazing staff. Can't ask for more. My girlfriend loves the breakfast, and I love the lunch. Great place.
Love the pot o bread, and the cali eggs Benedict. Need to buy the place next door and open up more seating, it's always packed, but it's because it's so good.

I eat here mainly out of convenience. The pot of bread is very good. They do offer a wide range of menu items. I can't say anything bad but I can't say a whole lot of good. I'm a flavor person and the food is kinda bland. I don't believe they make their soups from scratch and they tend to be over salty. Good in a quick JAM but not to go out of the way.
This place is great. We go here often, definitely my favorite breakfast place off strip in Las Vegas. Great service, great food. Can't ask for more.
Tasty breakfasts, really good coffee, and a surprise treat that you have to try...pot bread! The staff is very helpful and fun too.

A true hidden gem of Las Vegas. Very thrilled with the flavors I experienced here. The service was great and very fast...we are here on a Sunday and they are still serving us as if they aren't packed.
Very good Friendly good food fair pricing my only negative comment would be the floors need to be replaced the carpet is done for ! All in all that would not keep me from coming back.

This place was referred to is by a local. I wanted really good food and not just the stuff everyone is eating that is commercialized. This place did not disappoint. The service was impeccable and the food was outstanding. I had the corned beef hash (instead of sliced corned beef) Benedict and pot of bread. The bread was delicious except that the condensation in the pan it was served in made the bottom soggy. Oh we'll. the hash browns were crispy and their homemade hash was simply amazing. Coffee was on point as well. Husband had steak and eggs and was happy with portion and taste. I want to come back and have more before we leave. I also have to thank the waiter at another restaurant for the recommendation.

This was wonderful. Only problem that I had that really wasn't, was I should have checked on home hash browns/fries as having bell peppers but that was my error and Ma can't eat the hash browns anyway so it was fabulous. She was to full.

The service is your typical diner experience service. Everyone working is fast, friendly, and efficient. It did take a little while for us to get our orders in, but they were slammed on a rainy Friday morning/afternoon. 

We started off with French toast sticks, and then I had the Florentine eggs Benedict. The spinach tasted frozen and had the freezer after taste to it, so that kind of turned me off a little. My cousin seemed to like her pancakes and eggs breakfast. 

After we were finished, the waitress forgot to drop our check so we awkwardly sat there trying to get her attention until we finally went up to the cashier, and let her know we didn't have a check. I kind of drove out of the way because I was craving a gluttonous breakfast, but I think I'd stick to my Blueberry Hill staple next time I want pancakes and coffee.

Damn, I LOVE Jamms!!!! I am JUST finding out about this place. I am going to keep taking people until I have to go alone! 

PROS: *Jamms Signature Omlet - steak, cheese, fresh mushrooms topped with 
             bernaise sauce. ( I substituted egg whites).
             Hamsteak - sweet and savory
             Pot bread - Party in a tin pan!!!
             Family owned AND operated

After sitting 30 min, our server comes to our table to let us know the kitchen never got our order.  Not once during that time did she come to our to to refill our drinks. Not to mention she didn't think to ask the kitchen why our order wasn't up yet. Will NOT return. Such bad service.

Food was good. They do great mix of breakfast and lunch items. 
Lemonade has to be freash. Prep for a pucker! Haha
Service could have been nicer. Sweet lady but I waited way to long for someone to come to the table. When there was employees standing around talking.
After eating here for more than 10 years I thought I had tried all the breakfast potatoes but the home fries was a real treat.

First time here and the omelet and biscuit I had were delicious. The place was packed on a Saturday morning but we were seated quickly. Service was a little sketchy. We had to ask for our server and again for the check. Not a deterrent at all. I will definitely be back.

Mediocre in nearly every way. The food is bland and unmemorable, the pricing is a little high for what you get. The service is generally pretty good. There are better breakfast options not too far away.

Good place for breakfast.  They have a big menu w/typical breakfast foods presented different ways   Place is small so there is always a wait.  The Pot-Of-bread is good but just bake fresh bread.  U can get a free one if u check-in on Yelp.

Amazing breakfast. Pot of bread, salted caramel and cinnamon raisin were delicious. Omelets were stuffed and fluffy. Sweet potato fries with powdered sugar... Dip them in your left over bread frosting... Just wish there was more cheese on the omelets... We will be back...

Very solid diner spot at the corner of Rainbow and Charleston. We tried their notorious pot of bread a few choice omelettes, and their waffle. Portion size was quite good. Many of the diners here in Vegas either give you a small omelette/skimp on the ingredients or give you an enormous omelette which no normal person can stomach. Jamms gives you a good portion size with quality ingredients for a great price. They also offer tapas plates which is an awesome idea for a brunch to try many breakfast dishes as this meal is by far the hardest to decide in the morning. I very much enjoyed my meal here from the waitstaff to the meal to the 10% yelp check in coupon to the fact that my meal came in at $20 for a solid morning starter. One of the best of its kind in local Las Vegas.

Went here several  times. Food is great and recommended many to come here. Sadly to say I have not returned to eat here after our waitress , who come to find out was the manager, had asked if we were finished while I was finishing up my cup of coffee. She stated people were dying for a booth. Keeping in mind we waited over 30 minutes to be seated. Bad customer service and it coming from the manager made it even worse. Host insisted us to come back and be sat at another servers section. I just don't agree in supporting a business who's manager is a server and gives bad customer service. Many other cafes that don't rush you out that I can go too in this town.

The sweet, creamy goo is the perfect compliment to any warm muffin, but smear it on a fresh pot of Jamm's bread and OMG! It's like a party in your mouth. This fresh little pot of bread is like nothing I've experienced anywhere other than Jamm's. The cream cheese icing is the best. The goodness doesn't stop with the bread and icing, though. We were greeted with a plate of fresh fruit while we browsed the menu and sipped our fresh coffee. This time I opted for the signature omlette and it was awesome. Sliced steak and béarnaise sauce with crispy hash browns and another little loaf of heaven. The service was great, as always. We had a couple of first timers with us and they were both impressed with the service and quality. One of them ordered a bowl of grits, which looked like a meal unto itself. Pretty thick and tasty as well. Ask for a cup of coffee to go and continue to enjoy Jamm's on the way home or back to the office.

What a nice surprise!   I am very picky about my morning break, particularly when it comes to omelette.   I ordered a "build your own" bacon and cheese omelette.  You get 4 items with the BYO so I ordered double bacon and double cheese.  Boy was i surprised.  It  as loaded with bacon and a nice helping of cheese!!!   Very nice.   Hash browns were perfect!   The sourdough toast was perfect!   Probably the best value breakfast in all of Vegas!
So good you have to try the bread it's to die for and the breakfast Omelette Coke with bread and my favorite powder sweet potato fries
Food was decent and adequately priced. I could take it or leave it. The people were very nice but the food took longer than expected.

The French Toast Was Awesome. I will Go Back Just For The Jamms French Toast. Our Server Was Really Nice And The Place Felt Very Homely. Look Forward To Trying New Things Like Their Special Toppings On The French Toast Next Time.

I wish that I have discovered this hidden treasure before! A friend of mine took me to Jamms for breakfast 2 weeks ago and I've been back twice since. The food is excellent, service is friendly and courteous and I can build my own waffle! Anyway I want it!!! Woohoo!

Heard about this place from a friend. Love the service from the front door on in. Coffee in big mugs and delish. Many options and they actually offer substitutions-you don't have to ask. Best egg- white veggie omelet!
Great local breakfast  spot been here for a long time super yummy food great service just an all around great place to eat and yummy coffee

This place made my stomach happy:)
Good service and generous portions.
I will be back for my breakfast fix.
Yum

I'm always looking for great breakfast places.  I came across Jamms on yelp and wanted to try it due to the yelp reviews.  My husband had the cornbeef hash, which was good but def was salty and I had the stuffed French toast which was light and tasted amazing. The coffee was ok and service was friendly.  I wasn't blown away by this place but I would def go back to try other items.

My wife and I ate at Jamms this past weekend for breakfast, and let me tell you, this is somewhere we will be coming back to all the time because it was amazing.  We had one of their pot breads to start (cinnamon raisin), which was awesome and free with yelp checkin! The sweetened butter was fabulous too.  For our mains, I had the breakfast burrito which was a perfectly prepared burrito filled with eggs, onions, and cheese and some delicious hash browns.  It was excellent.  But as good as that was, my wife's Jamms breakfast sandwich was better.  It was easily the best breakfast sandwich I've had.  Ham, cheese, eggs, thick Texas toast.  It was fabulous.  The home fries were delicious as well.

With that said, I also have to comment on the outstanding service provides by the employees at this establishment.  From the moment we came in and the hostess took our name to the end of our meal, service was friendly and outstanding.  We were greated promptly, sat at a perfectly clean table as soon as it was ready (there was a line when we arrived, as the place is deservedly popular), and our drinks (coffee and water) never reached empty.  Orders were taken quickly, food was brought promptly, it was a tour de force of outstanding service. And, to top it all off, this place is a great value.  Prices were extremely reasonable!

Overall I cannot recomment this place enough.  Go here and enjoy.  You will love it!
Great customer service,  food was fresh and amazing, definitely recommend this restaurant,  will come again, was clean and employees were super Friendly

A- OK.
Huge portions of good, well prepared food. I ordered a low calorie breakfast of avocado, egg, and bacon /w cottage cheese and it was good, and when I left
I was not hungry.
The wait staff is friendly and attentive. Most dishes appear to come in at around $10, you won't feel burned.

Excellent breakfast foods with good company. The place was packed so we did some quick shopping nearby. Ate our free pot of gingerbread bread, eggs bene on a waffle, and a straight-up waffle with some powdered sug for the lady. No complaints!

Home of the pot of bread. Well that was good and the food is good but the service is horrible. Had to wait for a table, but that's typical. After waiting for @ 20 min just to have our order taken it was proof then why the wait to sit takes a long time. I think we had more interaction w the bus boy than out waitress. Had to ask for refills which should never happen. Stay on top of your customers please!!! Finally food has been eaten and plates removed and again another long long wait for the check. Over all the service alone will keep us from coming back. No one wants to waste half a day at this. Your staff can be friendly as our waitress was, but when you fail to attend to your customers you fail to get returning ones.
My all time favorite brunch place whenever I'm in Vegas. Love their coffee, sweet potato fries and omelet.

This place is awsome. Great food and great service. Their pot of breads is their specialty and they are delicious. I recomend their breakfast and lunch. We come here every weekend and even though it's a small restaurant the wait is not that long.

We have been coming here for years. Great food, great service and the staff is very accommodating. We have never left hungry, the only thing that would make it better would be a place to sleep off such good food.  KEEP IT UP JAMMS!  We will be back.
Will definitely return. Food was fresh and plenty on the menu to choose from, Service is top rate. The pot-of-bread is great, but not unique to Jamms.
Ever since we shot a promo here for 8 News Now many years ago, I have always remembered the Pot Of Bread. It will certainly keep you coming back!

I love this place, food is always great, pots of bread are amazing, Shirley is always a delight and treats us like family, we've been coming here for years!!! I bring all of our out of town guests here for brunch!!!

The pots of bread are awesome! Plus I had the country style eggs benedict, best eggs benedict ever. After visiting Portland this summer, we were looking for something like that in Vegas and this is it.
LOVE Jamms! They have THE BEST Eggs Benedict! And the fresh baked cup o bread...so good!
Drove out of my way to eat breakfast here based on friend's recommendation. Glad I did. Service was outstanding - fast and extremely friendly and attentive. Great coffee, very good food.

If you eat here, pay cash.

Someone decided after I left that I should be leaving a 40% tip.  Just found the altered charge.

Service was ok, but someone @ Jamms is definitely over valuing themselves at that amount.

I won't be going back.
I love the fact that most of their menu can be put as a small plate option.  Avocado, bacon and cheddar omelet. Delicious
This place was great, my brother brought us there for breakfast and it was excellent!

After visiting Hash House A Go Go, and finding to our dismay, a ridiculous 1 hour wait, we decided to try Jamm's for brunch instead.  

Jamm's is unpretentious, unassuming, honest-to-goodness mom 'n' pop little joint (the complete opposite of Hash House).  Service is fast and friendly and they treat you like family (they were really accommodating to my husband's request for hard boiled eggs).

The food was good solid diner fare.  We ordered the eggs benedict, the chicken fried steak and eggs, and a side of corned beef hash. Everything was good, but we loved loved LOVED the house fries and the corned beef hash (which was perfected seasoned and lightly crisped).  Food was reasonably priced and portions were very generous.

Will return if in the area again!
Great place to eat it I recommend. Especially there pot of bread. Been here forever I worked at Wells Fargo next door 17 years ago and they were good then good now.

I've dined here four times.....

The first time:
I ordered the turkey, swiss and pear wrap........WTF?  Flavor explosions with every bite.  So good, I knew that it could easily become a "go to" item when decisions had to be made on the fly.  Also, on the side, I order their famous bread in a pot.  If you LOVE fresh bread and carbs as much as I, you'll flip for this warm, doughy goodness!  (sigh)

The second time:
I ordered the Jamms breakfast sandwich; scrambled eggs, ham, cheese, Texas toast.............typical flavors for a typical breakfast sandwich.  Yet again, I ordered the bread in the pot and it melted in my mouth!  It is the business!!!

The third time:
I was craving good 'ole steak and eggs so I made my way to the closest breakfast joint.  No, I'm lying, I wanted the bread in the pot!!!  =)  I'm a medium-rare, over medium kinda girl, and when the steak came out chewy and well done and the eggs, over-hard, I was terribly disappointed.  The only thing that was eaten that meal were the hash browns (you can't mess up potatoes, can you?) and the POT OF BREAD (of course)!

On my most recent visit to Jamms, I decided to order my "GO TO" turkey, swiss and pear wrap........decision well made, THANK GOD!  As usual, I ordered the POT OF BREAD, and LOVED every moment of it!
=)

~The service is wish-y wash-y at best.  One time I'll have over the top exceptional attention, and other times I'll be flagging the server down because I've gone 20 minutes (literally) without any sort of look my way.
~The menu is large........nearly 20 omelets alone!
~The POT OF BREAD is what keeps me coming back!!!  I dream about that bread!  Every time I drive past Jamms (which is often) I think about that bread!  UGH...........I want some NOW just writing about it!!!   =)
~I'll continue to give this place a shot......they can thank the POT OF BREAD for that! 
=)

I had a great breakfast here. Many low carb options, which is nice.  Great, friendly service. I had a delicious omelette with tomatoes, cream cheese, mushrooms and green onions.  My only complaint is about their coffee. Oh dear. It does not taste good.  I have been hear years before and had the bread pot and remember liking it. This time, I had to pass.

I love this place! I have been going here for years. My father introduced me to this place. Expect a wait it's that good. Thankfully it is never too long of a wait. The employees are very friendly l. My niece and nephew can get messy sometimes during meals. We order the french toast sticks. This seemed like a good idea cause it's a finger food and they could dip them in syrup. Turned into a sticky mess. The waitresses were helpful and also brought the kids stuff to color. The food is extremely good and reasonably priced.

The cinnamon bread pot is so good! This is a great small restaurant off the strip that we decided to try! We were vary pleased with the customer service and food! I highly recommend for a filling and fair priced breakfast after a long night out lol!
I love this place for breakfast!!!!! I come here with my boyfriend and the food is great and completely affordable. It's great for a Sunday morning breakfast.

This is hands down, the BEST breakfast joint in town!. I love this place. Great customer service. Everytime we come back, it feels as if we're visiting family out of town. Clean, friendly, and delicious!  Definitely a must try if you want something delicious and a great experience.

Decided to stop in and give Jamms a try after a bunch of positive reviews...Carol-Ann has got to be one of the best servers ever, always with a smile, and awesome attitude!

This place was packed with hungry diners and we were lucky to get in quick, as many others were in bigger parties.

As mentioned in other reviews, if you mention Yejp, free pots of bread for you!(Its actually bread baked in a ramekin) we had Original, Cinnamon, and their flavor of the week, Pumpkin Spice.

We also ordered a French Press of Illy Coffee and some OJ...after browsing the menu, wifey settles for the Sandy(?) omelette(according to Carol-Ann, the most popular one) and I go for the Corned Beef Hash with Hash Browns, both extra crispy. we also tried one s'mores pancake, just because:)

Overall, food was pretty good, but Jamm's serves up the best corned beef hash in town!(sorry Du-Pars, you're still king of pancakes though!)
Definitely an item I'd order again! ALOHA!!!

YELP 365 CHALLENGE-(30/365) "Order the Corned Beef Hash!"

This off-the-strip breakfast and lunch place is my absolute favorite. It has a fabulously creative menu and the most delicious coffee. Popular favorites such as chicken and waffles, chicken fried steak and eggs, biscuits and gravy are all items to splurge on. It's definitely worth the trip!
The pancakes and pot muffin are really good.  The bacon was crisp, coffee was margina and the service was decent.

Unlike a lot of other reviews citing huge portions, there was nothing extraordinary and infact, the chicken fried steak was one of the smallest I have had anywhere. So the 'Huge Portions' thing is far from real.
Next, cold eggs and film/skin on top of both gravy and maple syrup is for rookies like Denny's, not the type of place the Food Network personalities film an episode at.

Very sub-par, below average and will most likely be removed from our Las Vegas Best Breakfast website!

In my quest to find a new breakfast spot as I was growing tired of my usual places I found Jamms Restaurant. I wish I could say that I believe Jamms Restaurant is jammin' or had some delicious  and wondrous homemade jam, however I cannot but that is alright just like how the restaurant is alright.

Mostly certainly it was a miscommunication between myself and the name of the restaurant as I thought that perhaps the restaurant would serve some awesome jam, but to my dismay only the pre-packaged Knott's jam is available.. darn.

The menu consist of your typical breakfast items, omelets, sandwiches, corn beef hash, pancakes, but you don't need something extraordinary as long as the ordinary is consistently delicious. Although during my visits I was not particularly impressed by my dishes. Reason being is that I felt that my Jamm's signature omelet which was composed of steak, bearnaise sauce, murshrooms and cheese was somewhat bland and my steak was difficult to chew. I also had a piece of my friend's Jamm's french toast which was battered and covered in corn flakes, my impressions are that I will probably stick with the normal french toast as the specialty is a little mushy for me. 

The service was jammin' though, the waitress were friendly, helpful, and refilled my water often. My dining companions went MIA after ordering but the waitress was very understanding and patient with that, always monitoring when my friends would come back to the table. However I would like to mention that the waitress had no clue what I was talking about when I mentioned the Yelp special nor did the cashier, which made things a little embarrassing for myself as I had to explain their special promo to receive my free pot of bread.. the jammin' stopped there unfortunately.

Maybe in the future when I am tired of my usual breakfast places again I will give Jamms another try or perhaps for lunch I could jam with the California Club
Always a great place to eat ... always busy but the food is good and the portions are large

Ate here on a Monday at lunch...the business was steady, not too busy. The decor is way outdated. The carpet is supposed to be red but is black because it's so old. The portion sizes are good but all of the food lacked seasoning.  I order the country version of eggs Benedict, which consists of a biscuit, sausage, poached egg and gravy with a side of country potatoes. I was so disappointed that the white gravy looked and tasted like it came from an instant mix...definitely not a good quality sausage gravy...it had no flavor. The country potatoes where crispy but again lacked any seasoning. Bottoms line...will never go back
Excellent find. Were looking for a good breakfast place while visiting Las Vegas and found this gem. Very good place for breakfast.

I love Jamms! My mom and I usually split the Irish Skillet. The portions here are super generous so I find half sufficient. It's absolutely delicious! We also share the french press coffee, which is also delicious! I do wish they would bring pots of cream to the table instead of the mini creams, it seems wasteful to me. 

The staff is really friendly and nice, and they are very accommodating. The service tends to be pretty quick as well! Plus they have a Yelp deal if you check in! 10% off your entree with drink purchase!
Food is great service is a little slow but still worth the wait...feels like your grandmother kitchen and just an overall good feel

Jamms is a great breakfast place.  I found them on Yelp a few years ago and now everytime we come to Vegas, we make it a point to have breakfast here.  I love the pot of bread (use Yelp and you can get a free pot) and the french pressed coffee.  I had never had it before, but always will now.  We haven't tried their lunches yet, but will need to do that on our next trip.  Jamms is a great local place.  I get so tired of the chain restaurants and fighting the traffic on the Strip.  Get in your car and take a short drive to Jamms.  You'll be glad you did.

My fiancée and I went there this morning.  Awesome food, ok service.  He got the S'more pancakes I got the meat lovers omelet, it could had more meat for my taste but it was still delicious.  Both times we have been there, there was a wait but always very short.

One of my favorite breakfast spots! The line is intimidating at first but I have never had to wait longer than 10 minutes! Walking in you feel welcomed right away, everyone has a smile on their face which is a plus for me!
