The waiters are fast and friendly, the food is great. I had the steak and eggs and it was perfectly cooked. One of best places to eat forsure!
Love the pot of bread. They have Strawberry coconut fluff pot of bread this week. The service is always excellent & friendly.

My wife and I enjoy finding local places when we travel, especially for a great breakfast.  We found that Jamms easily lived up to its five star rating on Yelp.  The bread in a pot was extraordinary and clicking on Yelp made this complimentary.  The day's special was banana chocolate which was delicious as was the cinnamon raisin. We shared a veggie omelet.  It was fluffy and delicious.  My wife is a connoisseur of breakfast potatoes.  She said the Jamms was among the best she has ever had.  Our waitress told us that she had worked there for 14 years.  That says alot about the quality and management of the restaurant.  One suggestion we offered was to provide real maple syrup at an optional upcharge for the pancakes which were terrific but loss some quality with the imitation syrup offered.

All in all, Jamms is worth the few minutes drive from the Strip for a great a reasonably priced breakfast.

All the yelp, trip adviser and various social media stickers on the door made me feel like I was going to enjoy an amazing breakfast and that was not what I got!  The restaurant is located in a strip mall location and looks like a good find when you search for it.  There was a long line for a wait and the locals told me I would not be disappointed when I questioned the 20 min wait before a flight so I stayed with my friends who are locals.  The wait wasn't too long ..our server took a bit of time getting to us because they were busy ...my fresh cup of coffee (there's a portion on the menu that says that we all deserve it to be fresh) was never refilled ...after I asked for it it came as I was almost done with my meal.  My gauge of a good breakfast is always a Benedict ...I've had multiple variations of it and it's my go to ...must be the sauce ....the menu talked about how you should get turkey if you want it but I guess it only applies to sausage and not bacon ..no beef or pork for me.  I opted for the Benedict with spinach ..egg was ok ..I asked for over medium and it came out over easy ..don't like it when the egg white is still liquid ...the hollandaise was average - nothing extra added to it and the spinach fairly bland.  I did order the bread in a tin and that was decent - I got to sample the plain, raisin and finally red velvet - the cook on each was different and I did finish the bread the only part of my meal that I polished along with the coffee.  I'm pretty limited in some of the things I can eat so when there's an item on the menu that excites me and its executed well I am pleased.  Social media is definitely something this restaurant does well and I think it contributes to their awards and recognition because the food is ok just like any other standard breakfast place out there.

The pot o' bread is a must try especially since they rotate the flavors on a weekly basis. I really enjoyed the pizza flavor but we are going to try the onion ranch today. The staff is friendly and the coffee keeps coming.

This was my first visit.  I went with my son who's been there before.

A slight delay but nothing to ruin the experience.  Plus you have to expect some of that for such a popular restaurant.  

We were seated in a comfortable booth and approached immediately by staff for our drink order.  The coffee was so-so but good.

I ordered Jamm's Signature Omelet and it was very tasty.  Totally forgot to get a pic of it as it looked just like the pic in the menu.  Medium to large omelet and very good tasting.

I also ordered the Pot of Bread and it was very good.

Prices were comparable to IHOP and Denny's but the quality and flavor was way better.
I love this place their friendly. I lovethe fresh coffee and veriety of omlets they have.
Great little place! The food was good and the grits especially were awesome! We also got the chocolate strawberry pot of bread, yummm!
Solid.  It lives up to what it is supposed to be. I like some of their french toast options. Their best quality/commodity is CUSTOMER SERVICE!

Famous for their pot of bread, it resembles a bread in a muffin tin with different flavors. I. Think that it could be more elaborate in looks and taste, like maybe being more browned and crispy on the outside, soft on the inside. Somewhat like a croissant. My friend and I shared the pumpkin cinnamon pot of bread. There is a weekly special. The service was nice, but as soon as I asked for the free pot of bread for my yelp check in, I was told it was for Dine In only. I didn't know, it's not documented anywhere. Anyway, I got a hard time for it. Just sayin.. the lady put it in a to go bag and said I we gonna do it anyway. Thanks. It want that big of a deal! Other wise, the breakfast omelet I had was a big portion and tasted  so so. I'm glad I was able to try this place.
I ordered the chicken waffle Blt - delicious. Great food, great service. Will definitely be back.

Over the past year Jamms has won me over and become one of my favorite breakfast spots here. A big big part of the upgraded rating is because of the staff. Lots of friendly and just nice people, which goes a long way when they're some of the first people you see in the morning. Lots of regulars too that you'll start noticing if you spend more time here. Just kind of a pleasant way to start the morning. The food has been consistently good. The pots of bread have become something I look forward to, especially with the new special flavors every week. And that free stick of gum on the way out. Those details have really paid off over time.

Excellent!  The Pot of Bread was a very nice "reward" for checking in!   The food was fabulous.   Everything was cooked just right.   (Hash browns were crispy on top,  the sweet potato fries were crunchy [and great with syrup!], the omelet was fluffy and full of good stuff.   What a wonderful little place!
A great weekend breakfast or brunch spot! A little pricey, but it's all worth it. Their pot of breads are worth it alone!

I was in the area with friends, so we decided to try it. Got the free cinnamon raisin pot of bread and it was good, just don't expect it to be big. I wanted to try a corned beef dish but as I tried to order, the waitress told me they ran out. Disappointed about that, but I ended up going for the chicken and waffles which turned out to be really good. My friends ordered burgers and said they were good too. 

So the food was pretty good, but the service was slowwww. The restaurant wasn't even half full, but the waitress barely visited us and when she did, her visits were short and she was very quick to leave, like she wanted to be somewhere else all the time. 

All in all, food was yummy, service was bad (lady at the front was nice though), and the price was about $10 each person. I give it a 3/5.

this was my first time here and I ordered the jamms French toast and..OMG!!!. I can't wait to live closer to be here more often. food and service was absolutely amazing. we also tried the chipotle cheddar pot bread..that was also amazing ..ill be back again and again

Very good breakfast. Even though it was Saturday morning, I arrived early enough that I didn't have to wait for a table. The staff was very friendly, attentive and quick. I started with a pot of bread (coconut and pineapple) which was light, fluffy and delicious. Then had the Sandy Omelette which was fantastic. I also loved the rye bread toast.  I just wish it was closer to the strip, which is where I usually end up staying.

This was my first stop at Jamms. The chicken fried steak was very good and the eggs were perfectly cooked over medium. I enjoyed the chipotle cheddar pot of bread too. The service was great and the coffee cups are BIG. Only really need one cup that way. Thanks Jamms for a great breakfast.

I'm a big fan of the breakfast place. I'm especially fond of off-the-beaten-track, magnet for the odd-bird-local breakfast place. This place fits the bill. Not long ago, I was yearnin' for somethin' different than my regular rotation and decided to check out this place. There was a steady stream of people heading in at 9am, which is a smidge earlier than a typical rush - a good sign.
The decor is... well.... Bridges of Madison County meets sponge paint meets truck stop.  Once you get over the momentary shock of that, you know you're at a place that feels like home.
The menu has a lengthy omelette menu which includes the likes of a White Castle omelette. Being from Chicago, I was filled with warm fuzzies.  I settled on the house special omelette, which was steak, onions, sauteed mushrooms and provolone cheese.  The omelettes are done just like I happen to like them, with thin egg wrapped around sauteed yummies in the middle.  The bread in a pot was a nifty surprise as well.  Home baked white bread in a little white ramikin served with softened butter.  
All in all, it was a hit. Go to Jamm's and find yourself in breakfast heaven.

Enjoyed the family diner experience. Our server was very attentive and nice.
I had the house made Corned Beef Hash!! Yummy!!

This place is alright if you're in the mood for a slightly heavy, but nonetheless tasty breakfast. The potted bread is fantastic. Anything with gravy is a bit overwhelming and insanely bad for you. Much of the menu is greasy and pretty strange. Some of it is just plain bad. Some of it is delicious. The menu is massive, which is a personal turn off. Perhaps the reason why the food takes so long to come out every time. However, the staff is friendly and on top of service. Great tips for our waitress each time. 

Small plate options are awesome. Just little samples of anything you want for an inexpensive or reasonable price. They also offer discounts for posting and checking in on social media. It's a pretty nice way to save a couple bucks on your meal. 

Overall, the food can go either way. I've had good experiences as well as awful ones in Jamms. The restaurant is old and outdated (this would usually not bother me, but it does make it look fairly dirty). The staff are great, no doubt. I personally would not eat here again, but my fiancé loves the potted bead enough to come back.

I'm one of these locals you'll see at Jamm's almost weekly!  I love this place.  The people are SO nice here, and the service is great.  The food is EXCELLENT.  Their bacon is perfect (in MY opinion)-I like it thick and crispy, and they deliver on this!  Their eggs are always perfect, and I love their pot of bread.  They have breakfast and lunch, and they have something for everyone.  Best of all, it's not far from my house!  :)

This place was average. I was excited to try the food but my boyfriend and I thought it was somewhat bland. We walked in as first timers and waited for a while before I had to approach the hostess myself that was up front starring at customers/walking around but not asking if she could help them..it was awkward. The pot bread was the only thing worth mentioning but the country skillet and eggs Benedict with sausage was again avg. Gravy wasn't very flavorful neither was the sausage. The waitress forgot our side order but she took it off the bill. At least the food was reasonably priced and we didn't have to wait..meh

Got a free pot of bread through check in.  There is a reason why this place is constantly crowded.  The food is delicious, a service is speedy, and waiters are nice.  I've got nothing to complain about this wonderful establishment.

Came here straight from the airport, and as always, was not disappointed! Great service, great food, huge portions, and the same quality that keeps me coming back every time I'm in town. This is the real Las Vegas, and Jamms has the real breakfast!

I come here every now and again with my dad. It's around the corner from where I live, but rather than just the convenience I come for the food. It's not super fancy, but everything always tastes good and fills you up. The staff is always nice and friendly, and they will continue to refill your coffee or water until you tell them to quit. They seem really helpful with food suggestions too, from what I've overheard. Had Joe's Omelet today, less the mushrooms which the waitress agreed with me was a wise move lol.
Best breakfast spot in Vegas!!! Amazing customer service! Amazing food!
We gave this place a try in place of our regular restaurant for breakfast: Hash House A Go Go. Its a great hole in the wall. Very friendly staff and the food is fantastic.

A diamond in the ruff.. My husband actually found this place on yelp. It's very close to the house so we decided to check it out. I am so glad we did not only does this place have a cute atmosphere but it also has amazing food. The service is impeccable and everyone is so nice and always smiling. When you first walk in you can smell the yummy goodness of the pot of bread cooking and your senses come alive. It's not a very big place and there's usually a line but it moves pretty quick. I suggest if there is a line waiting because you won't be disappointed with the food. Most everything they have is great and I've tried quite a few of their items on the menu. But their signature items are a must try as well. The jamms French toast which is dipped in cornflakes is my absolute favorite. You also have to try the pot of bread!!!  They have the  cinnamon pot of bread With cream cheese icing and they also have seasonal flavors which no matter what you have to try those as well. This has become one of our favorite breakfast places . They're open from 7 AM to 3 PM every day as it's just breakfast and lunch. So if you haven't tried this place you must go by and try the food.
I love the food here however if you don't come with your entire party they would not seat you, they make you wait even if you are dying to have a cup of coffee.

This place is just on the o.k. side, but really nothing special. Far better breakfast places just miles south down Rainbow. The great breakfast places are Baby Stacks, Egg Works, and Cracked Egg. Try these places and you will see the difference.

Good location for quick diner Breakfast. Fast tuen around. Few chairs at the bar for singles. The food is EXPENSIVE for what they serve. The bread bowl is basically a cinnamon roll or bread/biscuit in a muffin cup. If you live here you know where to go. If you don't and are willing to spend 11.00 for eggs go for it.

First time at Jamms and I'll be back for sure. We got there on a busy Sunday and even though it was Father's Day, we only waited for about 15 minutes. He hosts were super nice and both of them were working hard to make sure anybody waiting were seated quickly. We were a party of two and we shared a couple of omelettes. One of the omelettes was the Mediterranean and the other was the mushroom. Both were awesome. We also received a free pot of bread. Our server was super nice and so was the busser. Kudos for running a successful local business and doing a great job making people happy.

Don't let the outside appearance keep you from giving Jamms a try. Very pleasant interior and friendly fast service. The Waffle Benedict was heavy but tasty. Terra worked hard to make sure everything was to our satisfaction!

Been here for lunch many times.  I don't get breakfast anymore because they don't know how to cook eggs.  The sandwiches are ok.  The cuban is edible as is the chicken salad.  The burgers are small and over priced.  The place is always kept way too cold for me and the service can be down right rude sometimes.
Great pork chop and eggs.  We never miss this spot when we come to Vegas.  Best breakfast in town!

Everything here is delicious from there pot of bread, french toast sticks, pancakes, sweet potato fries, COFFEE as you can tell I've been here alot and its good every time, also helps that the staff is friendly... always worth the wait
Here is the place great breakfast joint any day, great service, great people, great place that closer to my house.

A great place to visit for a family feel, great staff and great service... This is I am assuming a Vegas local spot, because when we got there it was packed. The portions are HUGE so come hungry and ready to eat. The ladies that served us were super nice and we also bought their anniversary mugs! :) hopefully when I am back to Vegas I can come back to this spot.

Darlene and I just had great brunch at Jamms

Pumpkin pancakes
Cranberry orange bread bowl
Corned beef Benedict 
Yum -o

Was wanting to try this place for a while. As soon as I walked in, the hostess greeted me and sat us right away. I ordered the egg breakfast with bacon and it came with the Pot O'Bread that they are known for. The blueberry Pot O'Bread was so fluffy and fresh. The coffee was very tasty and the large mug that it was served in kept it warm. Everything was well cooked. Yummy food (and I'm not too big on eggs)

What do three Yelpers do after a double hike at Mount Charleston?  We look for a place to refill our depleted nutritional content.  We first went to a restaurant that had a 35 minute wait.  We opted not to wait and started Yelping on our smart phones to find somewhere else.  On the way to a 2nd suggested place, Warren P. found Jamms and since it was nearby, I piloted the car to Jamms.  What a nice stop for idea #3.

The three of us started out with a free pot of bread, just for mentioning Yelp.  They have plain, cinnamon, and the flavor of the day was green chili and cheese which is what I got.  It comes with a cup of softened butter and was tasty.

I had the S'mores pancake.  That's pancake batter with marshmallow and chocolate chips in the batter.  It's topped with some extra chocolate chips--for good measure-- that soften from the hot pancake.  There is also a drizzle of caramel sauce on the pancake.  I got the single pancale and it was a perfect ending to a great hike.

Service was excellent.  I'll be back here for sure!

I really enjoyed Jamm's! We used a yelp check in offer for some delicious free bread too! Ate a fantastic breakfast after a 15 minute wait on a Saturday morning that left everyone stuffed to the gills, whether was waffles, pancakes or eggs. Portions are enormous and service was friendly and relatively quick!

Jamm's is always perfect. They have the best corned beef hash that I've ever had, the best fresh bread, the best coffee, the best everything. If you're in Vegas you need to go to Jamm's at least once. I come here every chance I get. And it's relatively inexpensive.

Food was great. Server was ok...she was friendly, but it took her awhile to come to our table. I waited tables for years and even though it's busy, "I'll be right with you" is always appreciated. However, the bus boy was on top of everything, including keeping our coffees filled. He deserves recognition for his hard work!

Jamms French toast, veggie omelette, and Ruben Benedict.  I like the fact that they serve real corn beef not the can stuff.  The place is plainly decorated.  Not very busy the Sunday after Thanksgiving which was a shocker.  I enjoy the food, but it didn't wow me.  As a visitor, I probably prefer the Bagle Cafe's selections better. BUT, if you have a sweet tooth, I do like their french toast fried with a corn flake coating.  That was pretty tasty.
Delicious dinner with old school vibes and food made with care. Benedict's were perfect.
Great breakfast. Pot of bread is unique and delicious. As good an omelette as I've ever eaten.

Great comfort food for breakfast or lunch. Jamms restaurant is located on Rainbow and Charleston. I love this mom n' pop restaurant...quaint interior with dated decor that makes you feel at home. 

In terms of service and food, I prefer this place over other breakfast places like Egg & I, Egg Works, Original Pancake House, Cracked Egg, and so forth. It's definitely not a healthy breakfast and can be slightly heavy for some but I still like its tasty home cooking. Service can be hit-or-miss with some servers being very attentive while some completely forgetting your existence. Either way, all servers are super friendly and their uplifting spirit will help you start your day on a bright note. 

My favorite is Jamms signature omelet ($9.99) which comes with sliced steak, onion, mushroom and cheese topped with bearnaise sauce. I have no idea what bearnaise sauce is but based on Google search, it's a sauce made with butter, egg yolk and wine vinegar. I thought it was similar to gravy but it was more fragrant because of herbs. Tip is to ask for sauce on the side because they give you a lot. This omelet is meaty, cheesy and filling, easily my top favorite here. 

French dip ($9.99) is another meaty/filling dish that comes with generous slices of roast beef. These slices of beef are in stack of three to four and comes in a hero roll. Their au jus was little different from what I had expected and almost felt like it was a french onion soup. I was surprised that I actually liked the sandwich without dipping in their au jus. 

Philly cheese steak ($9.79) is nothing special here. I wouldn't order this unless you are craving philly cheese steak. 

Pot of bread is free with Yelp chek-in. You can get the original, cinnamon raisin or special of the week. On my recent visit, I redeemed my check-in offer for their peaches and cream pot of bread. Bread itself was doughy and had small chunks of peaches inside. Cream cheese was provided on the side. 

Inarguably one of the best breakfast joint in town. I hope to keep coming back here for many years ahead.

Best breakfast ever. We eat here every time before the drive back to L.A. 

The chicken BLT green waffles are amazing. 

Coffee is yummy! 

Love this place.

Excellent food, I really loved the corned beef hash. Very well spiced and cooked crispy on the griddle just before serving.  The waitress was friendly and had a folksy attitude which seemed appropriate. 

Coffee was a bit weak, but better than you would expect for a diner.
This place is Amazing!  I love to find great restaurants that are not a chain and this one is awesome!  Over the pot of bread and the breakfast burrito!

No matter how hard I try to behave when I go eat at Jamms, I just can't seem to do it! The biscuits and gravy never fail me! And today I had not one, but two, of the famed pots of bread. I chose to sample the Cinnamon Raisin pot and the Pumpkin pots today. Topping the bread with the scrumptious cream cheese frosting made me weak in the knees. Jamms KNOWS breakfast!!

Jamms reminds me of the small, family run, hole in the wall restaurants that you'd find in the midwest.  There is nothing flashing about the building or decor, but the staff are warm and inviting and the food was simply delicious.  It was packed and busy on a Sunday morning, but we didn't wait too long, maybe ten minutes.  Our drinks were out quickly and the food not long after.  The portion sizes were huge and for three people, it was only around $40.  The food was delicious with fast service.

Pros: Food, Price, People
Cons: Its not closer to my house.

Jamms is one of the first restaurants our family found when we officially moved to Vegas. OMG this place is amazing. Their pot breads are absolutely to die for, and their service is the BEST! They are busy, busy, busy but they can keep up with it; the servers are absolutely on top of it and sweet to boot. Our food has always been fresh and delicious and we have loved everything we've tried. Our two year old loves coming here too; they give her a bucket of crayons and coloring pages and she's set. Great family atmosphere! We love this place!!

This morning's breakfast was a huge disappointment.  It was busy-but Jamm's is ALWAYS busy on the weekend.  I ordered my favorite-The Sandy omelette.  The omlette part was a bit skimpy & it was bursting with bacon (some slightly crispy, some slightly undercooked)-almost too much bacon but the avocados were PERFECTO! Perfectly ripe and huge luscious slices. Sadly my potatoes were undercooked and very greasy 
: (  The Pot O bread was great as usual.  

My hubby ordered the irish skillet.  He said it tasted "fine" but from my view it also looked undercooked in places and I was not even tempted to ask for a bite as I normally do.  

I liked our waitress-we have had her a few times (I don't recall her name).  I asked about the potatoes.  She advised us to order extra crispy but did not offer to take them back... Maybe we could have had a small adjustment?  

This is the closest place to where we live.  I think we will put our other places back in rotation for now.

A great "locals" joint in Vegas.  Awesome breakfast place...plus they have a yelp offer if you check in.  How awesome is that?  Overall great food and great experience.  If you go on the weekend...be prepared for a line!

We came here over spring break. The place was packed with a ten minute wait on a Tuesday morning. We were seated quickly and the server was there right away to get our drink order. There are many interesting options on the menu, but we decided on the classics. I got the pancake special which comes with pancakes, bacon or sausage, and I eggs. When I asked, they had no problem swapping out the eggs for hash browns. The pancakes were very thick and fluffy, easily the best part of the dish. The bacon was decent sized and just the right crispness. I could have used a little more crispiness on the hash browns, but they were pretty good. My boyfriend got the more super sized version which also came with sausage and a ham steak. The ham steak was average sized, cooked nicely. We got a free pot of break with check-in. We got the weekly special which was rainbow sprinkles. It was soft, flaky, and delicious. This is a great spot for breakfast!
Great food! Great Service! Clean! The Potta bread was amazing so we're the waffles! Very nice place!
I love Jams, been coming here since I was a kid. And it's always a good home style breakfast right here in the neighborhood.

I'm a fan of their food, just not a fan of the slow service. When I first moved out here, Jamms was our go to breakfast/brunch because my boss loved this place.  At the time, we loved it too because we knew that our breakfast or brunch would take at least an hour of our work day.  The wait and the service usually takes awhile.  On my last visit, the wait was better and the our food came out faster.  But it still took a while, in my opinion.  

As for their food, there's a big selection of your typical breakfast items.  Price is actually pretty good and taste is not too bad.  

My Past Orders:
-Jamms Signature Omelet:  This is the king of all omelets here.  Steak and mushrooms dominate this omelet.  This is all you need because you are definitely stuffed after eating this one. 

-Chicken Fried Steak & Eggs:  Actually my favorite dish here.  Their chicken fried steak is tender and the batter is not too heavy.  Portions are huge as well. 

-Jamms French Toast:  Their french toast has a different look to them. I always thought that they were over-cooked, but they're not.  The french toast is crispy on the outside and after it's drenched in syrup, soft in the inside.  My second favorite.

-Steak & Eggs:  I had this on my most recent visit and can only say...stick with your favorites.  The steak had no taste and was a bit too dry.  I felt like I was eating cardboard.  But then again, stick with your favorites when you come here.  


Overall, Jamms is just okay.  With all the other breakfast joints in our beautiful city, it's tough to say that Jamms ranks above them all.  But if you're looking for a decent breakfast with a lot of options, Jamms is the way to go. 


YELP PERSONAL CHALLENGE - (056/366)

Delish! First time here and the food was amazing!!! Definitely coming back! Had the Irish Skillet and the Jamms signature omelette! Super yum! The pots of bread where so hot and fresh and melt in your mouth!
Ya, this place Jamms and the food is good. Make sure you get the French press coffee, delicious.

Great breakfast spot just corner of Rainbow and Charleston! Omelets, waffles, pancakes, french toasts, sausages, bacon, you name it! For breakfast I usually order my bacon, eggs, and wheat toasts, but I thought since I'm trying a new breakfast restaurant I should try out something I would not normally get, so I ordered their French Toast Fries with syrup and turkey sausages on the side and they were delicious!  The french toast was fried to perfection, not soggy like the other ones I've had at other places. Great service, friendly staff, and lots of parking. They also serve lunch so I will definitely be back.

This place seems more like your at home!
When checking in on yelp you get a free pot of bread! We tried the cinnamon and raisin, very moist and warm with a cream cheese icing (I think). It's just the perfect amount so you don't just keep eating bread.
My mom ordered eggs and ham Benedict and I ordered a build your burger.
The eggs Benedict came with hash browns and my mom was happy with it, I didn't taste it so not sure- she wished it came with toast.
On the burger you get a choice of 3 buns, 3 meats, cheeses, 3 toppings out of 8, and some sauce. I got provolone cheese, mushrooms, avocado and jalapeño mayo sauce. Tasted better than an average burger and I would come back for another one. I wished the jalapeño mayo was blended. It was literally mayo in a bowl and a chopped jalapeño in it haha I could've done that! Also I got wedge fries with the burger and these are probably the best fries I've ever had! They weren't greasy at all and I loved that they didn't have salt all over them! Soooo gooddd! 
Ps if you post on social media they give you ten percent off your bill, it's on every table so don't miss out!

Oh. My. Gosh. Seriously SO GOOD. I've heard many good things about Jamms, and I work right down the street so I stopped in this morning for a veggie omelet to-go. I don't know if I can ever eat an omelet from anywhere else ever again. Seriously... 5 stars is not enough. I will be back again and again and probably again!

Now I didn't know what a 'pot of bread' even was before I got here. I don't even know if that's a Jamms specialty or not. It's fantastic. The 'pot of bread' is the type of treat that breakfast places offer that I have a particular fondness for. They have a selection of other breakfast type foods that aren't bread and that don't come in pots (or little aluminum cups). 

The corned beef omelette is what I decided on. It was deemed a house favorite and I thought it could be risky. You think corned beef wouldn't be too hard, but I've had my share of salt with a touch of corned beef before. The beef was delicious and this meal all held up pretty well. They do sauerkraut and cheese in the omelette as well as the corned beef. The sauerkraut wasn't wet or overpowering, a nice compliment to the beef. There were hash browns I wish I could tell you more about but I inhaled them. Gone almost as quickly as they arrived. I think you already know my feelings about that soft, supple, raisin 'pot o bread' with the whipped butter that spread like like love on top.

The one touch that really had me was the kindness and the cheer from the staff. Nothing but smiles and friendliness. When we went, it had been raining pretty much all morning. I could hear our waitress tell other tables (and us) when we left to be safe driving out there. You just can't help but smile on that thoughtfulness. Definitely feels like you are eating in your grandma's kitchen and that's an amazing place to be.

Rudest hostesses...ever. Waitress was great, but the food was pretty standard diner fare. We tried one of the pot o' bread, two different benedict dishes and the kiddos split the french toast. Overall disappointing and not at all worth the wait.

I recently stumbled across Jamms and decided to check the reviews before visiting.  The reviews and food pics got me interested.  I'm new to the Vegas area so always on the hunt for a good restaurant.  I had some (southern) family come visit so figured that this would be the perfect time to try it out.  There were 7 of us that arrived around 11 on a Friday morning.  As any great restaurant/dinner should be, they were packed out.  We only had to wait about 5 minutes and the lady at the cash register was super nice.  

Once seated, we were immediately greeted and got our drinks only moments later.  Everyone decided quickly what they were going to eat so we got down to business.  Our choices ranged from breakfast items to kids meals to the crazy awesome french dip sandwich.  Our food didn't take long to arrive and we were all surprised by the amount of food that came out.  Everyone had more than enough to eat and between the 7 of us, we managed to finish off everything.  The pancakes are to die for!  Kids loved the grilled cheese sandwiches, chicken tenders and the chicken nuggets.  And they all loved that the fries came in a "frying basket" for each plate.  The service was great.  Our drinks were never empty and we were checked on several times during our meal to make sure everything was great. 

The menu gives a great variety of choices and we will definitely be back to try something different minus the 4 kids under 7 we were accompanied by originally. Between the 7 meals, 7 sodas/teas and a couple of extra add ons, our meal totaled $68.  Considering the amount of food we consumed, that was a great $68 spent.
Wonderful food and service! Have to try the Pot of Bread with the cream cheese icing!!

I love this place!!! I first got to know about this little piece of breakfast heaven from my co-worker. We had breakfast here before heading to the desert to go off-roading.

So let's start with the location.. It's located on Rainbow and Charleston. It's way off the Strip. But it sure is a local favorite. Finding a parking spot close enough is not always easy but it can only mean one thing.. Jamms is packed! They do get really busy and you might have to wait a few minutes to be seated but I'm telling you it is worth your while.

About the service. Nothing but the most jolly and caring people. It's like coming to breakfast at grandma's or your aunt. The servers always have a big smile on their faces and you are always greeted warmly. Nothing can beat that to start your day!

Then there's the food.. Big generous servings. Since I checked-in on Yelp on our 3rd. visit (this morning) we got a FREE pot of bread.. You can choose either plain, cinnamon & raisin, or the special. I chose the special which for today was Peanut Butter & Spice. It was served with what I believe is a cream cheese butter spread. Oh, it's to die for!!!

We also got half a serving of their biscuits & gravy and OMG! It was delicious. I ordered Chicken Fried Steak and Eggs cooked over-medium (that's how I always have my eggs).  It came with hash browns and another pot of bread. This time I asked for it to be plain. And of course it did not disappoint. I finished my whole plate!!! I was so full.

My fiancé ordered a Panini Bread with a side of Steak Fries and he said on his first bite, "Oh my God! This is a great Panini!" And he doesn't always pay much compliments about sandwiches.. Only the well deserving ones.

All in all, our dining experience at Jamms is great as always! We shall come back again sometime soon.. I strongly recommend them for people looking for a good straight-forward and unpretentious breakfast/brunch for cheap with awesome service.

At first it's deceiving when you drive up but once you get inside it has a small diner feel to it. Expect to wait at least 15 to 20 minutes  for a table then 10 minutes more once you sit down to order because it is that popular and busy.  They have very tasty food and they are humongous portions. We ordered chicken fingers for the kids and the flavoring was really good and they we very crispy.  My husband ordered a bowl of their homemade chicken noodle soup and it was really good and the serving is over 2 cups. I ordered the French dip and it was super yummy, normal size but still yummy. This place has 2 very unique things you can do for a discount and a free item. If you check in on yelp, you can get their pot of bread and if you do get the cinnamon raisin bread, you won't regret it. To score a discount all you have to do is clean your plate. Sounds easy but it can be a challenge because of the huge portions. I highly recommend this place. A must eat in Las Vegas.

This eclectic place is adorable.  It is classic olew...my new paraphrase for old new.  We ordered the pot of bread.  Today's special was cinnamon with cream cheese frosting, you get to put it on your self.  Howard ordered the cereal dipped french toast.  It tasted smashing.  Everything on his plate was gone. I ordered the red plate eggs Benedict.  Shirley the waitress said their Hollandaise sauce was the best she ever had.  I thought it was really good.  They serve what they call red plates.  These are small plates of the favorite dishes people requested.  Great idea for people like me who eat small and like to get a good selection.  I would say run don't walk to have breakfast or lunch here. You will not be dissatisfied!

Love breakfast at this place! The corned beef hash is amazing. The staff is always so friendly and I have yet to eat anything I didn't like off the menu and we've tried lots of thing. And the tapas plates are such a great idea!!

Very good breakfast place to eat. If you come here definitely try the pot of bread comes in 3 different flavors and is fresh daily. The service was excellent from the time you walked in to the time you checked out.

Let me start by saying order the pot bread, it was excellent and definitely fresh baked. The rest of the good was good as well. Good service no wait to get in on the day we went. Only regret I had was not ordering more bread to go

In typical Las Vegas fashion, do not be fooled by a store front.  So often I find that a strip mall with a nondescript doorway will lead to some wonderful experiences.  Point in fact for Jamms Restaurant.  

It was my birthday and I wanted to try something new.  Hubby is always ready to please me and so my Yelp search begins.  After all the nice things posted about Jamms of course we had to visit.

This is a homey kitsch diner.  It is a throw back to years gone by, but do you know what else is a throw back to years gone by?  Their SERVICE.  I found where all good service has gone.  They have come to Jamms.  Warm welcoming smiles are the first thing you notice as you go through the doors and it continues with the wait and service staff.  Just old fashioned goodness.  Then comes the food.  HELLO YUMMY.  The food is old fashioned, homemade, deliciousness.

I ordered the Denver Potato Pancakes, first of all there is no way I could ever finish this dish on my own.  It is massive and not only in size but in flavor.  I could taste EACH AND EVERY ingredient in this dish.  So fresh and made to order.  I would drive miles for this dish.

Hubby and our guests ordered the skillets and only one gentleman was able to finish his meal.  They were big on size and flavors again.  Excellently prepared.  Hubby ordered the homemade bread with his meal.  Today's flavored bread was a Chipotle, Cheddar concoction and it was D E L I S H...  I highly recommend that you order their homemade bread, especially if you are a popover fan.  They are very much more like popovers than a typical bread.

This may have been our first visit here, but will definitely not be our last.

PS I spied a crunchy french toast whizzing past us.  It looked wonderful.

The hostess was not great.  I just needed a table for 2 and my boyfriend was about 10 minutes behind me.  Even though no one was waiting, she made me wait to seat me.  I understand if there was a ton of people waiting and I need a big table but it would have been nice to sit and have a cup of coffee while I waited.  Our waitress was a pleasure.  Recommended stuff and was very quick with service.  The food was just ok.  I ordered the hash because it was listed as a favorite.  I didn't love it.
Super yummy. Excellent portions, fabulous customer service. . Hidden gem, totally amazing!
The food was Not good, I just tasted bland and they are pretty pricey compared to other places great customer service though but if you ask me I much rather eat something good

Thanks to Yelp, I found this little place that has the best brunch. I ordered the eggs Benedict and home fries and it was delicious. My husband ordered the build your own burger. He wasn't very impressed. 

The Yelp app gave me a free pot of bread which was orange cranberry and it was amazing!!
This breakfast and lunch spot is a regular when i'm home in Vegas. The staff is fun and the food is plentiful...if your in the area make the stop and enjoy!
Great food and a very wide selection of items on the menu. Go early they get real busy around 9 am.

I like Jamms. It is a great local joint. It is a lot like the bar Cheers, where everyone knows your name. My dad is a regular and falls into this crowd. I meet up with him from time to time and always enjoy the experience. The food is always good, the portions will fill you up for sure, and the prices are pretty good.

I thought Jamms was a nice restaurant. I would suggest ordering their in house items. I got the pancakes and eggs, they were good, but nothing superb, but my boyfriend ordered the french toast and bacon which was incredibly yummy! The service was quick and friendly and I would definitely recommend it!
The breakfast omelettes are amazing.  I highly suggest to purchase their bread.  Delicious!

We were recommended here and it wasn't a bad choice.  I had the steak and eggs plate.  I got my eggs scrambled with American cheese, and sides of hash browns, coffee pot of bread and a plate of red velvet pancakes.  I also tried the raisin pot of bread and their cabbage soup.  Everything was good.  The eggs were cooked to my liking, the hash browns were crispy on the outside and soft on the inside, and the pancakes were fluffy.  I liked the coffee pot of bread better than the raisin but both were good.  The only thing wrong was the steak that I ordered medium but got well done and burnt.  The service was good and we got 10% off by making a Facebook post.  Can't beat that.

If you are local and live on the west side of Las Vegas you have probably been here.  I have been going here for years.

So long our favorite server (Shirley) knows we order the same thing.   We don't even have to tell her. Rather than spend time with the menu we get to chit chat and get the "above and beyond" personal service.  The kind of service you would expect in a small town where everyone knows each other.

This is a traditional "mom & pop" type place.  Quality and service is always tops.  We try to get there for breakfast right when they open.  There is always a line waiting after that.  

Omelettes are great and you have to try one of their fresh baked "pot-a-breads",

Came out to Vegas on a family vacation for a week and tried several places to eat around town and on the strip. This by far had the best breakfast and great service. A must try is the pot of bread, we got the cinnamon raisin which was excellent. Highly recommend this family run restaurant. Will come back next time we are in town.
Breakfast was average. The pot of bread is just a dinner roll in a tin...people were nice. Comfortable.
This place has a homey feel. Same waitress, same hostess. Great vibe. Must try at least once. Love the sweet potato fries and pot of bread! Can get pretty busy. Lots of regulars.

We split an Irish Skillet. HUGE. Neither of us could finish our half. Really tasty. I enjoyed the melted cheddar. The cinnamon and raisin pot of bread was like a light and fluffy cinnamon roll. A nice addition. The staff was super nice and attentive.
The Pot of Bread was pretty good. My husband and I both had the country skillet and it was just ok. Service was very good though.

The food was good and the staff was wonderful. The place was not to bad on a Saturday morning at 8am. So get here early to get a good seat. After about 9 this place is starting to get busy.
OK the food is good but not great. I probably will not be going back. My omelet was to full of feta cheese and spinach, I get that's what was in it at least chops them both up in smaller pieces. 
I will not tell u to go and I will not tell u it's the best food in town. I would have rather gone to hash house a gogo. Now that food has good taste.
That's it the food did not have a lot of taste maybe it was what I had to eat. I like to taste my food.
One more thing I forgot to tell the waitress that I had a free pot of bread so I told the lady as we were checking out and she was not the nicest. I had told her it was no bid deal but she was not very nice about it. What ever....... And if u post on yelp in another social media place u will get 10% off u need to show the lady when u check out.
I just want to say if u eat here they will put u to sleep for two hours afterwards! Food coma!
We enjoyed a delicious breakfast here.  Loved the fresh-baked cinnamon bread!  Service was great.

Very down-home! Great, perky service! 
Love this place for the food...

Food was delicious. I had a B.L.A.S.T. for breakfast, with homemade chips. The sammich was had so much bacon and avocado, and was simply delicious. The BF had the country fried steak with home fries, and he loved it. We also had the french toast dippers which were nice and crunchy, as expected. I will definitely be back again.
Had a omelet with artichokes, tomatoes, onions and lots of cheese. Place is a very nice place for breakfast. Great potted bread

Was going to try another place but it was not quite open so sad this on Yelp and so glad I stopped it. The Pot of Bread special was a yummy Peach, I devoured it. Also had the Corned Beef Eggs Benedict which was so tasty,  I had to take 1/3 of this dish home since I was so full (rich delicious coffee too) and it was even better the next day.  Very friendly and attentive servers also

By far one of the best places for breakfast in Vegas. If the locas love it it has to be good. Not crowded with tourists, so crazy kids or weird people here. The food is served it very generous portions and I love the olmelt skillets with gravy. The last time I was there they started doing fresh corned beef hash, wow!

By far the best hidden gem close to the strip.

Great place for breakfast. Portions were large and the food was delicious. Coffee was pretty good. Went on a Monday just before noon and there wasn't a wait.

Service was good enough, wasn't overly impressed with friendliness or anything but they weren't rude or unwelcoming.

I'll come back again :) 

PS- For those of you who like S'mores, beware of their S'mores pancake. It includes a ton of Caramel that's kinda overpowering. Tasted like a Caramello candy bar more than smores.
Amazing service, amazing food, no waiting around and everything was so clean. Came from Arizona on vacation and I definitly recommend this place for breakfast and will be back next trip!!!

First and foremost, the staff here is just delightful! They have a regular crowd, everybody knows each others names, it's really welcoming. They're always very friendly, even when busy, and they take care of you as if you were family.

I've been here a handful of times as it's close to campus and I focus better in class when I'm happily stuffed. I've gotten breakfast all but one time in which I ordered the French Onion Soup and a salad and it was a total miss!

The French Onion Soup has a light broth with way too much thyme in it. The bread was a cheap generic white bread, so it got sort of slimy once it soaked up the broth. The onions were a thick slice and were not meltingly soft.
The salad which was Jamms House Salad was a cabbage salad with an "Asian" dressing. By cabbage salad, I mean, chopped green cabbage. That's it. The dressing itself was alright with some sesame oil and rice wine vinegar, but it was too heavy on the sugar.

That being said, the only thing I've eaten here for breakfast is omelets! The reason? Simple: The cheese. Oh my goodness, the cheese!! The omelets here are delicious but they definitely cheat by adding A LOT of cheese, which I'm a total sucker for. I usually eat healthy breakfasts, but the cheesy omelets here do me in every time. So much cheese you have to chew it well. It's glorious!
The Margie is my favorite omelet they have. It comes stuffed with mushrooms, tomatoes and artichoke hearts. Sometimes I add green peppers, sometimes I add spinach, but I always get egg whites which is a slight up charge ($1). They saute the vegetables before putting them in the omelets, so the tomato gets a little cooked which I love. It comes with your choice of potato (fries, hashbrowns, home fries) and bread.

Their bread selection is unique in that they offer a "pot of bread." If you like dinner rolls, you'll love this. Their pots of bread are really soft, pillowy, yeasty white breads. They offer seasonal flavors (I once had a divine raspberry and lemon), white, and cinnamon. Or you can get toast of course. I usually get fruit instead of potatoes and no toast or bread (at an up charge $3). The fruit here is always a medley of melon.

Great service, and amaaaazing gooey cheesy omelets! Coffee is decent.. just decent.

Love this place. I started with the specialty pot of bread, which was red velvet and it was great. I had the corned beef hash and it was the best I ever had, made with real corned beef. My other dining companion had the French toast, egg and sausage combo. Portions are large, service is great. Very busy place, expect to wait, but it is so worth it. Please open another location in the northwest, I will be back.
As always an absolutley wonderful place and staff! We love bringing the family here. The meals are delicious and hearty! Never leave without a full stomach.

Came here with the wife on a Wednesday afternoon about 1 o'clock.  Read some great reviews on Yelp, so we thought we would try it.  We really wanted some breakfast.  

The wife ordered the rueben Benedict.  The hollandaise sauce was okay, fake tasting.  The corned beef was awesome.  You could tell that they made it in house.  They overcooked her eggs and we had to ask for new ones.  The hashbrowns were crispy and good.  I ordered their Jamms omelet.  It was stuffed with thinly sliced roast beef that was crisped on the grill with grilled mushrooms, onions and cheddar cheese.  This was all topped with a homemade bearnaise.  It was fabulous. It all went perfectly together and I loved the crispy beef.  I also ordered their pot of bread.  It had a crunchy outside and a soft inside.  Very good. 

We will return and when I do I will be ordering something with that wonderful corned beef.
The food was amazing the service was great and I would definitely recommend this to anyone who's reading.

I've been to Jamms a while ago, but couldn't remember if it was good or not. My friend has never been before so I decided to try this place again earlier today. 

We arrived @ 10a, and was seated quickly. They got our drink orders right away and the coffee was on point! Another Yelper mentioned the coffee being delicious and I'm a picky coffee person, and this was great! Our server was Sandy, and she was very quick to get our orders and very nice. My friend ordered the steak and eggs and I had the pancake combo. We were both happy with our orders and they came out pretty quickly. Sandy topped off our coffee's a few times which I loved. I'm a sucker for great servers who come around when drinks get half way. 

I will definitely be back to try other items on the menu and to request Sandy again. Highly recommend this place. Get there a bit early as there was a wait when we were paying for our check.

This one was a recommendation from a co-worker at Century 21, yes years ago- we ordered breakfast items several times on a group order. It was very good. I never forgot it and had always wanted to go in person. We were on that side of town and since the Red Apple Grill wasn't open for lunch, this was Plan B. I had never been inside until last saturday, with my husband. It's a small but busy and popular restaurant located at a strip mall next to Albertson's on the corner of Rainbow/Charleston. There was a short wait- I gave my name. It was about five minutes or so. Not bad. My husband said it reminded him of a smaller version of The Cracked Egg. It was decorated for Halloween. We sat in a booth- I was facing their Wall of Fame- numerous "Best of Las Vegas" awards, as well as a travel site award.

The drinks were brought over to us pretty quickly (quick refills too BTW). We ordered from the lunch menu- Reuben & Jamm's Philly (with mushrooms, and onions)- and split it (our usual MO). Your choice of side- fries, sweet potato fries, potato salad. All sandwiches came with lettuce, tomato, and pickles- cut generously. Most items on the lunch side were priced at $8.50 on average. We both got the sweet potato fries- very generous helping (next time, my husband said one of us will get the fries and the other will get something else). Both sandwiches were equally very good. Not super greasy either, which can be the case with both sandwiches. (We saw a sandwich that was going to another table that was super stuffed- wonder what that was, but I don't know how that person could even open his/her mouth- would have to take out an inch of meat from it. It was that big.) My husband liked this place; he recommended it to his mom and step-dad. I'm sure we will be back again. The staff is warm and very friendly- I noticed that there were regulars here (a good sign). 

The bill was $17 and change- pay at the front counter. Free gum at the counter. On a side note, we noticed that there are omelets named after us, our nick names anyway, and they're right next to each other- how funny. Never saw that before in a menu, so we thought it was cute. Good diner on this side of town, reasonable prices, fast/friendly service, cozy atmosphere, only open until 3 pm.

Average at best.

We were "welcomed" in by the hostess whose only words were "For two?" ...yes. Seats us at our table, sets the menus down and walks away. So much for that welcome.

Our server was the best part of our experience. I believe her name was Sandy. She, unlike the hostess, was very welcoming, friendly and answered all of our questions as first time guests. Our food (including gratis Pots of Bread) was brought out promptly, so we appreciated that.

My Waffle Benedict meal was a 3/5.  Pepper flavor of the home fries was a little overpowering. Waffle was light and fluffy, Hollandaise was creamy and flavorful. But the Canadian bacon was way too thick for a Benedict. It was like chewing on a piece of leather. In my humble opinion, Kailyn's Kitchen still wins for best Benny in town.
In addition, I have to add that I was not offered a refill of coffee until our check came. Big deal. They would've scored those points back had they provided a restaurant-style thermos with more coffee at the table, if they're too busy to check up on us...come on, even IHOP does that. Yes, I went there.

We were passed with the check and thanked by Sandy. No message to pay at the register, so we sat awkwardly with our payment for several minutes before having to figure it out ourselves. We get to see the lovely hostess again, who says nothing as we give her our card and check. "Would you like your receipt?" Is this McDonald's? Yes we would. Handed our check without so much as have a nice day.

Perhaps it was an off day for these people. Unfortunately not a great impression was left for us as first timers. Consistency is the key to the success of a small business, and if you can't master that art, you will miss out on a lot of opportunity.
good place to eat breakfast. love the ot bread- freshly baked. portions are huge and tastes delicious.

I've been to this location several times, but only because my friends enjoy going (not sure why when there are so many other breakfast places that offer better food & service).   The food is OK, but nothing spectacular.  I feel rushed every time I'm there, like they just want you to quickly eat and get out so they can seat the next customers that are always standing waiting in the teeny, tiny "lobby".  There is usually a 5-10 minute wait before the server even comes to the table to take our order and multiple requests for coffee refills etc.

I am not easily impressed but if you want brunch in Las Vegas Jamms was 5 stars in every category. We had spinach, avocado, bacon, omelet with crispy potatoes. Order was split in half with complementary pot of bread (we chose pistachio and cream) which was great for no added fee. Place is clean with good portions and well priced. Food came fast even though they were very busy.
Amazing food, fast service, lovely spot. Loved the biscuits and gravy. Amazing coffee as well.

Jamms French Toast was a nice little twist on my favorite breakfast food. A little crunchy, and you can somewhat taste the flakes. The corn beef hash was to die for. A side, however, is a bigger portion than an actual meal order, so prepare for that if you try to order sides as taste testers. Overall, the food was satisfting.
The service was completely alright. Our food took about 20+ minutes to get to our table and there seemed to be confusion every time drinks were discussed. But, they were pretty busy, so I'll blame it on that.
Overall, i liked it. I'll bring people here for some hearty and tasty food. Can't complain too much about the service, especially if they are so busy.
Soooo good. I've had their Rueben Omelet and the Rueben Benny. Both were VERY good.

We decided to come here after dropping my car off across the street, this place is busy like all good breakfast joints. We decided to sit at the bar since the wait was 20 minutes you can't be picky especially if your hungry! The vibe i got seemed to be like that show on cheers where everybody knows your name. At least that was the case for my server she knew the gentlemen sitting at the bar beside us, the staff is always busy but attentive. We ordered a eggs Benedict, the Denver omelette, and the French toast sticks it was sooooo good! Of course get the pot of gold!
Great food and very friendly service.  Our server Staci was very attentive and nice. The food was amazing very flavorful.  Definitely recommend!

Excellent breakfast! We finally found a spot that has a Taylor ham sandwich that we approve of. The only thing that could have been better in our opinion was the roll it came on. But that's more of a preference thing on our part. Service was a tiny bit slow but it looks like it was due to a backup in the kitchen. We got the free pot of bread with the yelp check in and it was great! Will be back soon.

The food was OK, service OK (she never smiled once), prices abit high for the product. Then while paying.....our bill was 44 and change and they wouldn't accept our $50.00 bill. Told us to go break it at the store next store. There was no sign posted either. I'll never go back there when there are so many better places in this city to go.

This is my favorite place for breakfast and all of the staff is pleasant and friendly. Shirley is one of the best waitresses we have had and love her energy and attitude. She makes the place feel like home.

Not very friendly customer service, the food was okay but not great. I could have cooked it better myself at home. Minus the bread, the pot of bread was fantastic. Not worth coming here for a roll though. Never again.

You cannot beat this place for a good  hardy breakfast.  The freh rolls are to die for.   Plan a a little  wait. Usually crowded.  Service slow only because the food is made to ordr fresh. Prices $9- 15 . Most patrons are regulars.
Best breakfast in Las Vegas!! Reasonable prices and great coffee. My son had the s'mores pancakes and they were incredible.

I had heard great things about this place and was excited to try it. I had the chicken fried steak and my girl friend tried the waffles. It was ok...it's hard to screw up breakfast but it's even harder to make a great breakfast. 

This wasn't great my plate seemed a little dry.

So GOOD! first time here in all my life of living in Vegas.."pot of bread" was so delicious service was super friendly. .... reminded me of how Vegas used to be :) Dylan our server was awesome! Can't wait to come back.

I tried the Chicken Fried Steak with Biscuit and Gravy.  I thought this was the best CFS I had in Vegas.  The steak is a deep fried variety.  The batter is thicker than others and has a good crispy crunch while being soaked with gravy.  It's not easy having that last bite still crunchy.  The hash browns were not over cooked or undercooked.  They were golden brown with a nice crisp exterior and nice soft interior.  The biscuit was very soft.  Melts in your mouth.  Coffee was good too.

Had the Bishop Wrap with veggie burger - it was deeeeelish and Sandy is the greatest server. The boyfriend had the Smores french toast and he loved it. Definitely the place to be for breakfast or lunch!
Best breakfast I've ever had in LV.  Large portions of heavenly goodness!   Don't miss the pot of bread...out of this world.

Came over to the area to shop at JC Penney right about lunch time. Not familiar with the area came across a number of places to pick from and decided on Jamm's Restaurant. DELIGHTED! with the choice. Food was excellent, nice family atmosphere with friendly staff. 
Recommended highly.!
First time here and the service was really polite food was awesome, decor was cozy, recommend for anyone who is trying to grab something off the strip

What a great little diner. This place makes you feel at home with the newspaper,and the great waitresses. Reminds me of better days.

There are so many good things on the menu it is always hard to decided. This time I wanted to do lunch and the NJ Sloppy Joe-a triple decker sandwich with pastrami,corned beef,and turkey w/cole slaw & 1000 island sounded good. BUT....

so did the French Dip sandwich with steak fries and au jus.

I got the latter and it was damn huge I knew right away I was at best gonna make it through Half.

The beef was tender & tasty. The Roll was soft and buttery but firm enough to hold up to being dipped.

The fries were seasoned and very tasty.

As expected I barely made it through half but there was no way I was leaving this one behind!

If you like that small town feeling when you go out to eat. THIS IS THE PLACE!
Employes are very friendly, the place was crowded during saturday noon, service is fast, food is very greasy but portions are huge (big), the taste could be improved.

The service is so friendly. Shirley was so wonderful. She knows or seems to know everyone! Her laugh echos throughout the place! The coffee flows and they check on you constantly. 
Food is good and they are known for the Pot of Bread.

First time here, and totally coming back! Thank you to my Yelp flock for never leading me astray! I read your reviews, I heard you loud and clear! 

We came here 10 am on a Sunday morning. The wait turned out to not be bad since a lot of people in line before us had given up. Sad for them, awesome for us!

We were promptly seated, brought menus and coffee, and greeted by our enthusiastic server, Sandy (Hi, Sandy!). I told her I was checking in on Yelp and she was thrilled to tell me that I got a free pot of bread. 

We ordered:
- White Castle omelette
- $5 small plate egg white/no cheese omelette
- Pot of bread - flavor of the week was strawberries and cream

HOLY POT OF BREAD! These are amazing. It's like angels from heaven came down and manifested themselves into a gooey, fluffy, warm pocket of bread. 

$5 egg white omelette was the perfect size! I try to eat a healthy breakfast, but when portions are gigantic, it's impossible. The veggies inside were nicely cooked. It is a great small bite to order.

THEY HAVE SUPER HUMAN BUST BOYS! Twice we watched bust boys catch dropped plates in mid-air. It was really quite impressive. 

I had such a great dining experience here, and will be back!!!!

This breakfast spot is awesome I live in California but visit family frequently and always try to come here . The food is delicious and service is great definitely a family tradition coming here now to put one by me would be great :).

This was a pleasant surprise.  Kind of a drive from the north end of town, but totally worth it if you like a homey family diner kinda place.  Very family-friendly atmosphere.

It was a little while ago, but I remember the food was really good (and inexpensive!!) and in generous portions.  We were there for a weekend breakfast and I think we got a free pot of bread because we mentioned we found them on Yelp.

This is a very homey restaurant! It had its own little charm, for being a restaurant that's been open for over 20 years! The staff were very attentive, and I never had to ask for a refill on my coffee, because they made sure to check around with the tables often! I ordered the chicken waffle breakfast with french fries! For $10, I got a full plate, with room for leftovers of delicious goodness! Be sure to check in, and order their pot of bread for free! I ordered the cinnamon raisin pot of bread, and it was gone in five minutes! This is going to be a new breakfast spot for me for sure!

O-M-G, they had me at the pot of bread.  The pot of bread was three cheese and it was sooooo good.  My friend and I shared a skillet, and my cousin had a breakfast burrito.  I ordered a french press coffee and it was very good and strong.  Food and service was awesome.  If you want to have a great meal, go to Jamms!
Ham steak and eggs was a good choice. Service was very good and very fast. Glad I stopped in.

So, if you have visiting European tourists and want to introduce them to an authentic, tasty, FILLING American breakfast, THIS IS THE PLACE. They're big enough to share. So, if you order the ham and eggs and your friend orders a shortstack it would be plenty. That's not what we did however. We had the corned beef hash and eggs, ham and eggs and a shortstack. The hash was as people claim one of the best restaurant hashes...not as good as my own, though. :P The ONLY thing that was pretty terrible was the coffee....or dishwater.
Good traditional breakfast the baked muffins are excellent and food portions are just right.

Loved this place for breakfast and definitely want to go back and try their lunch. I went with a healthier option omelette but had a few bites of their pancakes and fresh baked bread and they were such a treat. Loved that they gave us a discount for checking In.

Delicious, tasty and filling breakfast served by the nicest people in a warm and friendly environment.  The potted bread is OUTSTANDING and addictive (try the specials). I had the nutella with strawberry swirl and it was like eating a little piece of Heaven right there and then!  Excellent coffee, good country gravy, unique and delicious omelettes, and fresh fruit.  Jamms is one of my favorite spots in Vegas for the "Power Breakfast Meeting" with my cohorts.

Wonderful service!! Food is delicious and quick, the right amount of food. Shirley was outstanding and makes you feel like you are at home. Their hollandaise sauce is wonderful, not too salty. We recommend the French press coffee, prefect size for two cups of coffee. Prices were very reasonable and the servers don't make you feel like a bother if you want substitutions!!! We will be back here again and again!

The fact that Jamms is so close to my house is really just the cherry on top of the cake that is this lovely breakfast joint in Las Vegas. 

We tend to visit here at least twice a month, usually on Sunday mornings (which is kind of a mistake because that's when after church crowd tends to swarm it) so there's always a wait, but believe me it is worth it. 

The omelettes are nice, big and fluffy and the home fries are just right. The orange juice is delicious (I'm not sure if they claim its fresh-squeezed, but I have my doubts). The coffee isn't spectacular, but definitely passable. 

One of the things that set Jamms apart: a rotating variety of "pots o' bread" (Management: If you're reading this, PLEASE make the cheddar jalapeño pot o' bread a permanent menu item!) - ranging from season flavors to standard fare. 

But what I love more than anything is the service. From the hostesses, to the bus people, waitresses and waiters, everyone is friendly and treats you like family. There are seriously staff members who are genuinely happy to see you week after week. 

That's what keeps this place going strong; nothing fancy or fussy, good food and great service.

Great breakfast. Everything tasted pretty good and we all left feeling full. The corned beef hash was noteworthy as it was made from scratch. I would definitely eat here again. You also get a 10% discount if you show them that you did a Yelp review.

One of the many things I love about Vegas is all the little breakfast places they have all around town. It's nice to know that I've got options if I don't want a Grand Slam breakfast from Dennys. 

My husband and I came here for one of our Sunday breakfasts. I'm a fan of Corned Beef Hash so when I read Russ V's review on it I decided to give it a try. I liked this corn beef because it wasn't salty and I knew it was fresh because it didn't have the mushy consistency that canned corned beef has. My order came with scrambled eggs, and house fries with a side of sourdough bread. I'm a little weird when it comes to breakfast I usually will put the eggs and the corned beef hash on the toast. Once the toast runs out I save the rest and take it home. Corned beef on top of white rice is yummy! The portions are huge here so there is enough for like three small meals! I was also very full because before the meal came out we had the free Cinnamon Pot bread. Just mention Yelp and you too can get a free one! It was slightly salty on the top but once you get inside the bread it's nice and soft. It's tastes really good with coffee. 

My husband had the Sandy Omelet that comes with bacon, tomato, avocado, sour cream and cheddar cheese. I sampled the omelet and it was really good too! It reminded me of the Cracked Egg's North Shore Scramble but in a Omelet.
A nice homey place for breakfast with  friendly servers and decent food. The Pot of Bread is tasty and soft.

The girlfriend and I where in vegas for a small vacation, and while we where in town we wanted to get off the strip. So hit up some friends, and they said we had to try Jamms out. And so we did. Well worth it. 

In a strip mall, and perfect size. Also very popular! So recommended times to show up, try around 8:30, after 9 you have a 15 min wait. which is well worth it. The decor is fun and light. The staff is incredibly nice, which was awesome. The menu has a lot to chose from, which can be hard to chose from. LOL.. I got the chicken freid steak, which was delicious, and the girlfriend got the multi grain pancakes, which where awesome, I had a few bites and was hooked. The second time we went there I ordered the jamms french toast, which is french toast covered in con flakes, it was awesome.. The girlfriend loved the multi grain pancakes so much, she got that again. Fresh coffee, and the staff was on top of refilling the cups non stop. Bottom line, its the local spot for breakfast. So if youre looking for a pretty cheap and quick breakfast, hit up Jamms!!!
Absolutely love this place! Not only is the food delicious, the portion are great, and the menue is always updating with something new! Try the pot of bread, especially in the fall!

The food and amazing service was well worth the 15 minute wait this busy morning. I ordered the biscuits and gravy and fell in love. My son enjoyed his BLT waffle sandwich very much.  Vegas is lucky to have this amazing diner.

Great food, price, and service!

FOOD:
Four of us went to Jamm's based on one of the guys recommendation. I'm glad we listened to him. We all thoroughly enjoyed our meals. It was my first time having french press coffee, and it was awesome. We each ordered the Pot of Bread - one guy had the cinnamon raisin, and the rest of us got the special Oreo version. It was so good. The taste and texture of the bread reminded of a soft dinner roll, but the Oreo added a really nice sweetness, and it came with a side of sweet cream frosting/glaze. For our main breakfast dishes we ordered the Cornflake-crusted french toast, and the Irish Scramble, which is corned beef hash with peppers, onion, eggs, topped with cheddar cheese. Sounds yummy, right? Well, it was!

SERVICE:
We went on a Tuesday morning just before 8am. We were seated immediately, and had great service throughout. The waitress and busboy were friendly and attentive.

I'm rarely in Vegas, but next time I visit I will definitely try to come back to Jamm's.

my first time and it won't be my last.  Jamms could become my favorite breakfast place.  Fantastic omelettes.  The bread choices are better than any around bagel, English muffin, toast, or pot of bread no extra charge.  Service is excellent and staff is great.  Try I  did and was not disappointed.

Pretty standard breakfast/brunch/diner spot.
I didn't pay close enough attention to reviews or the menu on the coffee, make sure and order the fresh pressed coffee!!!!!! Otherwise you get a cup of light brown water with a hint of coffee aroma attached. Seriously I could see completely through to the bottom of the cup.
The large orange juice was infact quite large.... a small carafe.
I had the Jamm's Breakfast Sandwich with Ham. It is thin sliced ham, cheese, and scrambled egg on Texas toast. It comes with a side of hash browns or breakfast potatoes. 
This was okay..... not great, not bad. Probably wouldn't order it again.
My hubby had the Mattys Country Benedict. Two poached eggs, sausage patty on a biscuit covered with country gravy. He said his was okay. 
Again, not bad...... but with so many other options, I can't see us coming back anytime soon.

I just tried this place last Sunday with a friend and I loved it! The workers were very pleasant and welcoming, and the food was very good. What I liked the most is that they bake their own bread! I'd definitely come back to this place.

This place is a fantastic breakfast joint. My boyfriend and I usually share the chicken fried steak. It's quite a large portion, and we get the ordered split in the back so you get your money's worth because you get 4 eggs and plenty of homefries. Shirley is a great waitress. She remembers our order and treats us like family. One of the biggest perks of this place is the pots of bread. They have a regular one and then a special one daily.  The blueberry lemon and cinnamon are my favorites.

FYI: stay clear of the biscuits. The gravy is to die for but the biscuits taste like frozen hockey pucks. Lol I asked a waiter if they were homemade and she confirmed they were not.

This was a great breakfast spot. The food was very good the prices are reasonable and the service was great. I will definitely recommend it to friends and family. The portions are decent I had to get a to go container. Don't forget to check in to get pit of bread for free. I highly recommend the cinnamon raisin!!
A+++ for customer service, taste of food, and value. Definitely felt welcome and will return!
My mom had bacon and eggs and I ate  the French toast it was a great dining experience

Just tried out their night menu - they have an awesome selection of unique hamburgers, some other sandwiches and wraps, a few salads and a short list of appetizers.  The choices of sides are many - seasoned fries, skinny fries, sweet potato fries, potato salad, coleslaw, cabbage salad and a regular side salad.  The drink selection left something to be desired, but they do carry the essentials. (Coke products for sodas)  While the items are definitely not standard, it *is* a smaller overall menu than most places.

A recent addition (I don't remember seeing it on their lunch menu) is "The Jamminator" - a whopping 24 oz burger with your choice of toppings.  If you take the challenge and can eat it all in one sitting, they give you a free t-shirt.  After seeing how big their regular burgers are... that thing has to be monstrous.

I had the Egg Salad Burger.  (Yup - a 10 oz burger with a scoop of egg salad on top, plus the normal fixins.)  It was fantastic, but super big.  Definitely something to cut in half and take part home for later.  For my side I chose the sweet potato fries; they came spinkled with powdered sugar.  I think I could've just eaten a plate of those by itself and been satisfied.  Super delicious, and a nice sweet change-up from normal fries.

The waitstaff is super friendly, almost to a fault.  Great group of people, though.

Comparing what you get for the money you spend, this is easily one of my favorite diner-style restaurants in town.  Expect to spend about $15-$20 per person if you go all out with drinks and dessert.  It's definitely worth it.

I've been coming here ever since I was a little kid. They treat you like family here and if you are unpleased with your meal or experience they try their best to make it up to you. We always left satisfied and wanting more the next morning.

The three of us are 4 pots of bread. Why? Because it was delicious! We had the cherry, cinnamon raisin and plain. In addition we tried three different omelets. The portions are generous and everything is fresh. Really enjoyed breakfast here and will plan to return the next time we are in Vegas and need a solid breakfast without breaking the bank.

Also, service was perfect! Super fast and my coffee was always full. I gave it five stars because Jamms does classic diner food really well.

Fantastic meal and the free pot bread for checking in on yelp is awesome. Will definitely be back to eat here soon. So many thing on the menu looked great. Today I had the biscuits and gravy with bacon. Everything was great!

I'm going to say one thing to you yelpers pot of Bread.  yes you read it right pot of bread. They always have cinnamon raisin and they have a daily special when I went it was chocolate caramel now I have to tell you that was a little over-the-top for me you could only taste the chocolate not even the caramel but the cinnamon raisin... amazing and the pot of bread is just what it sounds like.  don't be fooled by the butter on the side no no no no it's not just  butter it's actually cream cheese icing. That's right cream cheese icing on the side of your pot of bread. I don't think I need to say anything else. I do remember ordering other things but I don't remember them not like I remember the pot of bread

Jamms is family friendly, with great food and better service. Everything comes out hot. This visit we wanted chili cheese fries & my mom is diabetic so she asked if she could have them on sweet potatoes instead, they told her sure. They tasted great.

I really wanted to like this place!

Walked in and was immediately transported back to Woodbury, New Jersey!  Smells exactly like a NJ diner!  Made me smile & homesick all at once!  Hostess greeted/seated us with a warm greeting! 
Place was fairly full, but we were seated right away.  It's a good sign for a Wednesday morning!

Pot-o-bread - Was expecting a typical fresh, doughy bread like you'd get at dinner. However, it was a like a light, moist pastry type "bread", which was a perfect side for breakfast.  Don't hesitate to try it for fear of filling up before the main course!
