Belgium Waffle & fruit & coffee - I got the half order.  My honest opinion is that I've had better Belgium waffles.  This one had good flavor, but it was unusually thin for a Belgium and surprisingly  "tough" to cut with a fork.

Signature omelet w/well done hash browns, ice water- the husband got this for breakfast. He specifically requested "well done" hash browns.  What he got, tho, were actually lightly browned & under cooked.  He was not happy.  He scraped off the sauce on top of the omelette as he said it has way too much tarragon and the consistency was "gelatinous".  He said the actual omelette had little flavor and he had to douse it in hot sauce.

The bill was under $20.  Fair for the amount of food.

I love the Mediterranean omelette, here, which comes with spinach and feta cheese. Very simple. Portions are big here and just that is pretty filling. It's home to the pot of bread. Options are great, and they have a special one for the each week. French press coffee is also offered.

I've been coming here for 10 years now. I'm not the biggest fan of breakfast but Jamms is the place to be. They always have  great service and great food. They are small and always have a line but it goes by fast and it's worth the wait !
The servers are always so nice and welcoming and the food is awesome! I recommend the corned beef hash as it is the best I have ever had and the Sandy omelet makes my grandmother very happy!

This is the best brunch spot on Charleston. I'm very happy to have found this place and will definitely be back. The place is constantly busy. If you want breakfast on the weekend, you better get here early. This place rocks. If you have the opportunity, stop by Jamm's because it's pretty sweet

Jamms has won the RJ readers poll for the best breakfast in Vegas basically every year since the beginning of time, but then again, the RJ readers voted Taco Bell as the best Mexican food in town last year, so screw those people.  The Fat Man knows what he's talking about when it comes to food.

You want the skinny on this place from the Fat Man?  I live off of Boulder Hwy in Henderson.  This place is at Rainbow and Charleston.  (About 35 minutes from my house.)  I don't do mornings, and I'm not generally a breakfast eater...But at least once a month, my wife and I get up early and trek across town just to eat at Jamms.  

Over the years I've had a few things on their lunch menu, and I'll be honest...I'm not a fan.  But their breakfast....oh baby, their breakfast.  Their omelets are light and fluffy and PACKED with toppings.  They have about 30 omelets to choose from, so you have plenty of options (The White Castle is by far my favorite.)  Their corn flake french toast is AMAZING.  I have often wished for their signature pina colada french toast as a dessert after dinner at night.  (When I start thinking about that is usually when we go to Jamms the next morning)       

Their fresh baked pot-o-bread is some of the best bread I've ever had.  It's like a poofy dinner roll baked like a muffin, only airier and fluffier and full of wonderousness. (And yes, that's a word.  I just made it up.) I usually get the original, but they also offer cinnamon raisin and the "flavor of the day".

Ladies and Gents, as I said before, I don't do mornings.  As I often say, "they call it mourning for a reason".  Anything that can make me EXCITED about getting up early is something special.  Jamms is one of those rare things. 

The only thing better than the food at Jamms is the atmosphere.  The staff is friendly, helpful, and courteous.  They are always smiling and chatting with the customers.  They are excellent about refilling drinks and making sure you are enjoying your meal, but they also find that perfect line between being helpful and not hovering.  Ronnie (the owner) has great taste in employees, and has almost no turnover.  Almost all of the wait staff has been there since I started going there nearly 10 years ago.  

My only caution about this place is to be careful.  Once you have eaten here a few times, it can become an addiction.  I'm pretty sure they put crack in their food to make you crave it more.  :)
This place was cool but service was a little slow. Fun atmosphere like a ma and pa place but the bacon was fatty. Food was great.

Coffee is very weak. Dirty water type.
Servers are so busy cause they also are tasked with making toast, english muffins, etc. They never have a free moment to check back with customers. Poor gals. You get one touch only. 
Kitchen staff is extremely fast and efficient turning out food at amazing pace.
Note, the bus 'persons' (red shirt) takes your drink order, but not your food order. You need to flag down a server (black shirt) for that.
Waffle is soft not crispy.
Hash brown is the thick kind, little crispy surface and lots of soft center.
Servers were too busy for me to contemplate ordering the 'pot o bread' as an afterthought. 
Pay at front when you leave.

I don't even know where to start!! Portions? Amazingly huge!  Customer service? Impressive! Food quality? Top notch! Pot o' Bread? OUT IF THIS WORLD! 

Although it is a tiny location in a strip mall on Rainbow, the wait time was less than fifteen minutes on a Sunday morning. Waiters and waitresses were super attentive and the choice of music for the place was awesome (a lot of Katy Perry, Adele and Ed Sheeran) even though the place was jam packed, you were still able to hear the person sitting across from you and no one was bumping you or your booth. 

What did I order? The most amazing skillet ever. It included,  sausage, bacon, the best potatoes possible, eggs, cheese, peppers, onions, all covered in white gravy. Seasoned to perfection and piping hot. Came with a side of perfectly toasted toast (ha, perfectly toasted toast), and I ordered a strawberry covered waffle on the side. 

I should not have ordered anything extra because the portions were out of this world. 

My boyfriend ordered an omelet which came with sausage, bacon, peppers and a pot o' bread. 

That bread...  My god that bread. When they offered it, I should've taken it instead of substituting the toast. My boyfriend inhaled it in a matter of seconds. I was barely able to get a tiny piece. It was just that effing good. No clue what they put in it or how they prepare it, but not only was it toasted and flaky, but when you bit into it, it was rich with flavors I can only describe as heavenly and the feeling in my mouth was simply orgasmic in nature. 

GO EAT ALL YOUR MEALS HERE.

Good food and pretty good service. 

I was in Las Vegas for vacation and came to Yelp to find a non-touristy breakfast location. This seemed to be the best choice. We made the 8 mile trek from the strip and found Jams.

The first visit I had the Steak and Eggs. The steak was nothing fancy, just a typical cheap diner steak. It was cooked well but it was just okay. The "breadpot" was pretty damn tasty. I had cinnamon raisin and added lots of whipped butter. VERY tasty =D

The second visit (not my idea.... families idea...) I had the Texas Chili Omelet. This visit proved to be much tastier! The chili was meaty and flavorful. They were more than willing to add onions and jalapenos, per my request. I had the pumpkin and marshmallow breadpot with sweeeeet sugary frosting =D. 

Overall it's a great local place. The staff was quick and friendly. Refills were pretty quick. 

Only thing that bothers be is the gramatically incorrect wording on the front page of the menu.
The best mom & pop breakfast& lunch spot in town. I don't even want to review because it's my favorite little secret.

A really good, of the strip place for breakfast.  I've found there's not a lot of places to grab breakfast on the strip, unless you're talking a buffet. Too many people still asleep I guess. But if you stay off the strip and are looking for a non-cookie cutter restaurant Jamms is it.

I had the eggs Benedict, which was perfect, and my girlfriend had the steak and eggs. We split a strawberries  and cream pot of bread which is really a must if you go here. 

Service was friendly and fast. Prices were reasonable. We'll definitely come back on our next Vegas trip. Highly recommended.

Wow- so good! The service is wonderful. The menu has EVERYTHING for everyone - even a sample menu for those who want it all. The fresh corned beef hash is the best I ever tasted. Light and filled with meat and flavor. The biscuit and breads are fresh light. My friends omelets were "yummy and perfect". Oh And the coffee is great!!The Price is Right - Jamms is JAMMIN!!

Jamms is my jam, for sure. I'll tell you one good reason why: diner type food, with big ol' booths you can enjoy it in. I love a good diner with booths. It's not a diner without booths, honestly.

I was intrigued by the variety of burritos on display, so went for the White Castle (I'm white trash like that). It was what you would expect (and as described): ground beef, onions, cheese, and they serve it with ranch on the side. I've never put ranch on a burrito before, but when in Jamms, I just went with it. Truth be told, it completed the experience.

Great service, nice people. Ample parking. This is a go-to for brekkies and brunch.
Food was ok but was a bit too pricey Denny's is better you get more for your money and much tastier  also we ordered a side of pancakes which the waitress forgot to bring :(

I love this place!! The servers are always on the fly and they've never messed up my order. The sandwich selection is phenomenal, anything you want, they'll get it made.  The food is so awesome, I end up there at least once a week, if not for any other reason than to try the weekly pot of bread.

Awesome little breakfast place. My boyfriend and I decided to give this place a go on a Wednesday morning. 
I got an omelet with bacon, cheese and avocado with a side of hollandaise sauce. 
Reminds me a of cute little diner.

This is a LONG time family favorite of ours. My mom has been going here for 15+ years. My best friend and I take our kids in now, at least once a month.

The service is outstanding! It's always the same group of ladies, and they remember everything. Kids names, drink orders, our regular menu choices. It's impressive to say the least!

The menu is vast to say the least. My all time favorite is the Sandy omlette. Think BLT with avocado wrapped in fluffy eggs, melted cheese and sour cream. You have your choice of bread side- but I would recommend the pot of bread. It's always slightly under baked, which we have grown to love.

Make Jamm's you family favorite, and let me know what you think!

We wanted to try places where the locals go, someplace off the strip, where you don't literally get beat over the head when the check comes.  Found this place and we're very glad we went!  While they didn't have a gluten free menu they were very accommodating.  I had an omelette and hash browns and they gave me some sliced tomatoes in place of the pot of bread.  Hubby was lucky enough to have the french toast sandwich which was totally not what he expected.  It was french toast, made from their pot of bread and had cooked apples on top.  When I say his eyes rolled around in his head while he was eating it's an understatement.  He said it was probably one of, if not the best breakfasts he's ever had!! Service was great.  We would definitely go back!

Service was excellent. Food was great. The omelets were so big that the wife and MIL wished they had shared.

I got the Jamms breakfast sandwich. Wonderful and very filling. The wide had the Tomato and Avacado Omelet, which she absolutely raved about.

Wish I had this place in Dallas.

Great food, great staff, great atmosphere.  The cornedbeef hash and eggs was great, loved the pot of bread, especially since it was free.  I could probably give this place 5 starts, but I'm going to have to eat there a few more times to make sure it's earned.  The staff seem to know and love there regulars which is kind of a nice change.

Great food and packed but they know how to turn tables quick. Great food, great service but much need of gluten free option for people who can't have it. Will be coming soon. Hope one day I can try at least of the items on the menu.

This is a gem in the Vegas locals breakfast/brunch circuit. I've been meaning to try it out and when I did, I could easily see why. The staff is very attentive and friendly, you have that family friendly diner atmosphere and the coffee is just eye opening, literally!

I enjoyed a tasty breakfast burrito with their homemade salsa. It definitely didn't disappoint and I'll be sure to return to try some more of their other items in their very extensive menu.
I'm in love with this place for all things breakfast related. The service is outstanding and the food is soooo yummy

Loved the little Pot of Bread!  We tried the Cinnamon Raison and the Plain.  Both were delicious!!  Husband had the Hash, ordered an extra egg and I have him two of mine, then it was perfect (he likes lots of egg cut up in it)  I had the Chicken Fried Steak and it was very tender, not enough gravy and the gravy needed flavor.  Will most likely go back, there are a few other menu items we want to try!

Great breakfast spot! 

Excellent pot-o-bread, yumm. The flavor of the week was Oreo and it was devine. 

Great pricing for fresh and hearty egg dishes. 

Would definitely go to Jamms again and reccomend it to friends and fam.
Amazing!!! Food is great, they were busy but food came out fast and was delicious!!! Donna was our server she was amazing!!! So helpful and always checking on us drinks were never empty!
The pot bread reminds me of Grandma's homemade sweet rolls.  You can tell they are made from scratch.  The rest of my breakfast kept up with the amazing roll.

I love the comfort food, illy coffee, servers, & my fave- Shirley's unique laugh across the room!

I more come to hear SHIRLEY's uplifting laugh.  I am not laughing at her, I love how she loves her job!

My husband and I came in this morning around 11 am for breakfast. We sat at the bar so we didn't have to wait. Our server had the greatest laugh! She was personable and funny. A real "at home" feel. He had the corned beef hash meal and I had the stuffed French toast meal... They were both SO GOOD! I never finish my plate but I did today. His was massive! Even took home a small box! The home fries are excellent. Similar to cowboy potatoes. We live no where near here and drove quit a distance. Totally worth it!

A favorite go to for breakfast and lunch!! Amazing omlettes and the signature french toast is to die for!! Of and if you love a great ruben sandwich...this is the place. Server, SHIRLEY is such a sweetheart and always has a smile on her face!!

This place was great. Food was delicious, pot of bread was very cool concept. I liked the cinnamon raisin plus the strawberry lemonade bread. I would for sure go here again to eat. Loved the atmosphere and the waiter was super nice too.

I love Jamms! Great service.  Great food. Great breakfast spot. It is our place on the weekend to go when we don't want to hassle with breakfast at home. Great prices.  The staff cares about its guests and the weekly Pot O Breads are delicious

Great down-home diner. We stopped by here before our car ride back to LA. I had the Sandy (?) omelette which had a avocado in it. Very tasty. I think the sweet part of breakfast was also really really good. Service was friendly and the wait was not very long.
This is my second time here and I love this place. There was a 10 minute wait, but worth it. Shirley, our waitress, was very nice and had an infectious laugh!
Service was good, food was nothing like I expected. Yet again the great reviews on Yelp failed me. Not worth going back to.
My favorite breakfast place in town! We love the huge menu and the pot of bread! We go here every month. Kid friendly!

Went here for breakfast.  I had to find out what a pot o bread was.  Took a very expensive Uber from the strip to this place.  Reminds of you of any greasy spoon diner that you find across this country.  The Pot O Bread was very good and you should try it, if you go.
Jamms is my favorite place for breakfast/brunch in Las Vegas.  The wait staff is friendly, the food is great, and the service is great.
Hungry Lion is the best!  Happy 20th anniversary Jamms!!!  They have 20th anniversary coffee mugs on sale for 3.25, be sure to grab one!  The staff here is always so wonderful and helpful too!

I finally experienced the big build up of Jamm's, but Ronnie wasn't there!! I ordered the White Castle Burrito, against my cardiologists advice, of which I could only eat half of it, while my sister ordered a very large, very delicious Garbage(?) salad. I later had the burrito for a snack. A big menu of breakfast and lunch choices anyone would appreciate. Certainly worth the ride from The Strip, if you're visiting.

Well, back again at Jamm's that never fails to satisfy with its great variety of food. Definitely is a good place to go for delicious breakfast food.
I am currently trying their specialty omelet: the bearnaide sauce is what makes this item special. Try their Pot of Bread - always a good accompaniment.

We went here for breakfast. It is a Mom and Pop place. It is a ways off the strip, but the food is worth it. It has good food and the service is quick here. Got a omelet that had a lot of bacon and cheese. My husband got a scramble and it really filled him up. Everyone is very friendly and recommend great things to try. We will be back here again.

Service was great- food was great - wife got the corn flake french toast & is probably the best i've ever had- I got the steak omelet & it was good as well- the icing for the bread bowl was great not to sweet - We will be back

Just dropped in after reading the reviews. This place didn't disappoint.  My hubby and I shared a build your own omelet and it tasted great. Their French toast is nice and crunchy. Their raising in a pot is very tasty. Will come here again.

I would go back.

Reminds me of a mom n pop stop.  People were friendly, service was pretty good.  The food wasn't anything to write home about but I did enjoy my meal.  I liked the casual setting and it's in a convenient complex with plenty of parking.

I am not sure why this restaurant has such raving reviews.  Maybe because there aren't that many breakfast joints in this neighborhood, but I definitely did not enjoy my visit here.  And I definitely came here with an open mind and ready to love this restaurant since it is so close to my office. 

Visited on a Saturday morning and it was busy but we didn't have to wait long for a table.  It took a while for our drink order to be taken and then a while longer for our server to take our food order, but it wasn't that big of a deal.  

We had the seasonal pumpkin roll, the no-longer-on-the-menu french toast sandwich and the pancakes combo.  Nothing was spectacular or worthy of writing home about.  The only thing I enjoyed there was my coffee, which was better than average.  

Our server did not check up on us once except when she took our order and when she gave us our check.  However, we noticed she checked on all the other tables around us.  Again, it's not that big of a deal since we are relatively low maintenance, but it was an interesting observation.  

Maybe the other Jamms-goers know something we don't know, but unfortunately I won't be returning to this establishment.
This is a place I'd recommend to anyone.  They are friendly, polite, and best of all make you feel welcome. The food is great. The specialty items make the experience, definitely worth the trip!!

Came here before but I forgot to review. Second time back and it's so delicious! This restaurant never fails me and will definitely be one of my favorite breakfast spots. The first time I came here I ordered chicken noodle soup with blue berry pot of bread, and it was sooooo delicious.

Today I ordered corned beef hash and it was amazing. It was very filling so I shared my food with my brother. Next time I come I will order the steak and eggs because it looks really good too. The service is great and so is the food. Will definitely be back! 

*Order cinnamon or blueberry pot of bread!!! Pot of bread will have you hooked!!!

Visited this place during a recent stay at Vegas. We wanted to try something off the strip and found Jamms. The menu has alot of choices and everything looks good. I got waffle benedict which was excellent. Also tried the bread in pot which was awesome.
Deliciously friendly food! Strong coffee and large amount of food! Will definitely be back THIS WEEK!
Fabulous, everything we have ordered has been great. Friendly staff. The pot of bread fabulous

Omg so full! The food was amazing and still had food to take home! Then lastly u want to check in and show then that u post to social media and they give u a 
discount!

if this place didnt close at 3pm everyday i would come more often. i've had the sausage breakfast and its consistently delicious! i've tried their buffalo chicken strips and fries.. sweet potato fries!!! so tasty. i like their buffalo strips cuz they're flat and juicy. not super drenched in sauce so they're not soggy! so.. 1 star off for closing so damn early and another for... slow service. ppl at work usually call in their order so they dont have to wait around. service has always been friendly here.. shoot.. i would be too if i got off at 3 everyday! its right around the corner from my work so i always see ppl from work with leftovers from jamm's and everyone drools. hmm.. i think i shall stop by before work tmrw cuz this review is making me hungry!

So good! My friend and I both got the Bamalama omelette. His was traditional, and I substituted tomato for the bacon. Both were winners. Even better, the pot of bread! He tried the cinnamon raisin, and I went for the cranberry coconut. Absolutely wonderful alone, but add the cream cheese spread for pure heaven.

My husband and I look for a few things when we go out: friendly service , drinks refilled and nicely portioned great tasting food. 
We definitely found all of these at Jamms! My Jamm's steak omelet was very tasty with fluffy eggs and the home fries were seasoned well and didn't skimp on the portion. My husband's chicken fried steak, home fries and 3 eggs over easy were equally as delicious.  The cinnamon raisin pot of bread was tasty and tender. His ice tea and my coffee were never empty.
Our wait time was nil as we were seated as soon as we arrived at 10:30 on a Wed. We will definitely be going back as there are many more dishes we want to try.

Had a great lunch at Jamms and the rest of the family all enjoyed their meals. The menu is diverse for both lunch and breakfast..so plenty of options depending on your taste for the day. I had the Arthur sandwich and ate every last bite (highly suggest). My only knock on the place is slow service and booth space is quite uncomfortable.

In the summerlin area and was tired of all the stuff we tried before.  We frequent bagel cafe, egg works, cracked egg, and the alike, so we wanted to try something different.  We found Jamms on yelp, so wet gave it a shot. Firstly this place has a great "breakfast" feel, friendly staff, and the traditional specials dry erase board.  My gf had the jamms breakfast sandwich w home fries, and I had the corned beef hash, and we shared their special cinnamon "pot bread", everything was flavorful (not too seasoned) and most importantly fresh. Everything you would want in a breakfast spot. We will def be coming back.

We found this restaurant on Google Maps when shopping on rainbow.  We were so hungry and a Pot of Bread sounded perfect.  We were not disappointed. The serving sizes were perfect and the prices are reasonable.  The pot of bread is great. This will be somewhere we visit again.

Pot thingies...yummy and free if u mention yelp...but I have to say as someone that is not really a breakfast person the egg salad club is the best egg salad other than mine I have EVER had....I mean insanely good...and the Irish scramble...omg...the corned beef soooo soft.  The hostess barks at you but eh...it's Vegas right?  Lol.  YUM!

The food is great but not friendly service.  These ladies are on a mission....and you better know what the outcome want the second they ask or they yell I"'l'll be back!"  Ten minutes later!  They actually told us we needed to hurry eating.....people were waiting and they needed our table!"  They close at 3 p.m and at 2:45 pm they tell you to pay the bill!   These ladies want the hell out of there!  Good great!  Service....desperately need waitresses with friendlier better attitudes!
Good basic breakfast joint.  I ordered "tapas" style breakfast.   I had a classic egg Benedict and the Babalama omlette.  Great concept

After yesterdays encounter we wanted to revisit a friendly place that we know we can get a nice meal and great service.  Jamms once again provided us with top notch service, very generous portion sizes.  We joined them early in the morning for breakfast to which we were promptly seated and drink orders were taken immediately and brought out right away.  Other than my wife getting a bagel instead of an english muffin, which she didn't mind getting, it was great!  My drink never dropped below half full.  Great staff and great food.  Waiters and waitresses in Vegas could learn something from a small ma & pop place like this about customer service and attitude.
Food is delicious and service is Fabulous!! The cinnamon raisin pot bread is amazing! If you're ever in vegas be sure to find this place...it's definitely worth the trip! !

The cinnamon raisin pot of bread is enough of an excuse to go to Jamms.  But then there 
Is the rest of the food.  Made in-house corned beef hash, delicious, eggs Benedict, and oh so many other wonderful selections.  I luv Jamms.

Hello! First time to Vegas and I find this place! What a gem! They have huge portions and very reasonable prices. In the 4 days I was in Vegas I went there twice. That's how good it was. And the waitress remembered us. That's how a diner should be. Their French toast is deep fried and covered in corn flakes!!! Not to mention they have what is called pot'o bread. Brilliant! I got the special for that morning which was strawberry s'mores. Yes that's right. STRAWBERRY S'MORES! Together in perfect harmony. Why haven't we combined these favors years ago?!? I could never live in Vegas but if I had to, Jamms would make it a little less unbearable.

Was pretty skeptical about eating here but was I wrong. The food was so delicious and the portions are so fair it's incredible. The service makes you feel so at home and the wait is never bad. I would recommend this place to everyone for breakfast. Do yourself a favor and visit Jamms!

Went in to this place today for a late lunch with family members. It was super busy but that doesn't stop us from being seated promptly. It also didn't impact the service! We were treated kindly, respectfully, and promptly.

As a vegetarian Jamms let me subsitute vegetables for meat ingredients at no extra charge.

We all ordered different types of food. I ordered breakfast and some of my family members ordered lunch entrees. The portions were enormous!!! I noted that I would take a to go box for my omelette I would be able to eat off of for the next couple of days :-)

All servers and workers make patrons feel as though they are " regular" customers.

They also give a small discount if you post on social media which shows they are in touch with the social media aspect of our culture.

If you are looking for a casual, cool place to eat that has a down home feeling , I would highly recommend this place! Definitely will return.
Loved their classic breakfast!! The old school hash brown and their cinnamon raisin pot of bread got me!

Would have been 5 again, but we wanted to start eating, and instead have to stand around.
 Star loss.
The Pot of Braad was a vivacious disappointment. Kind of Pillsbury Rolls with a sprinkle of brown sugar, no Peanut Butter flavor at all. They waited to bring it WITH our French Toast. Huh?
Jamms restored my faith in finding a breakfast spot which feels like home.

Great food, great service! Loved the bread. Had to order more to take with me. Haha 
The whole staff were serving anyone that needed anything, no Gidding in the corner pretending to not notice you. Very friendly people with wonderful smiles.

Thank you, Yelp, for introducing me to this fantastic breakfast spot.

Great coffee, refilled frequently. Provencal omelet (tomatoes, provolone, fresh! spinach), delicious. Pot of cinnamon raisin bread, light, fluffy, and perfectly addictive.

Cannot believe Jamms has been right there all along and we never noticed it. Now that we've found it, though, I expect we'll happily become regulars.

Had the corned beef hash and eggs over medium.  Eggs were cooked perfectly and were delicious.  No complaints there.  
But the corned beef hash wasn't flavorful.  Just salted heavily but none of the delicious flavor you expect from a good corned beef.  Just tasted like salt.
Had the pot of bread...I like that it's hot and such but it wasn't very flavorful either.  Just seemed like plain white bread.  Didn't get the yeasty flavor other people liked.
Service was great and the staff super friendly.
Omg this place is Bomb.com you definitely have to try it when in vegasand out waitress Shirley is awesome

Had breakfast here during our latest venture into town.  What lead us here was reading about their pot of bread, which I had to try out.

The resto is a typical family diner, but not quite that of a greasy spoon.  Menu offerings were fairly standard as they had a nice variety of omelets, skillets, eggs and such, french toast, waffles and pancakes.  I ordered their Corned Beef Hash and Eggs, which was definitely none of that can stuff, it was housemade and cooked to perfection!  It was one of the better offerings of CBH I've ever had; you can trust me on that, I've been eating CBH since I was a kid.  The pot of bread it came with was served piping hot and was yummy.  I added butter and jelly and it was a nice treat.  Definitely skip the toast and go for the good stuff!

Service was very friendly, they kept our glasses full and most importantly my coffee cup filled with hot caffeine goodness.  Which by the way, their coffee was pretty good!

Overall, Jamms is a nice spot for breakfast, we'd come back again!
Best breakfast I've had in forever! Had an omelet with a side of biscuit and home made potato chips that were amazing  also customer service was great!
The food is delicious ! I had steak and eggs and they were perfectly cooked . Red velvet pancakes are huge . Great service and price .

The bread, oh the bread. You have to get their bread. It tastes like the rolls my grandma use to make, so light and fluffy and rich. The food was good quality and what I expected, but I would go again and again for the bread. The bread comes in little muffin tins and they have different flavors with little sauces. They also have this option where you can try more than one thing by getting smaller plates, perfect for someone who can't make up their mind. But the bread is divine.
This is a great breakfast or lunch place. Good selection of favorite foods,  good coffee and the pot of bread is always fab. Break it open and let the fresh-baked aroma make you happy.

We came on a rare Sunday we were actually awake. The place had a steady queue, a sign of good food. There isnt much in waiting area and I hate creating a clusterfuck in front of the hostess booth where people are trying to ojt their name and check out. it was too cold to hang outside so we left our number with them to sit in the car instead.

We decided to share

Rueben Benedict -I was expecting more like chunky pieces of corned beef but they use deli cut for this but guess that makes sense too. Overall solid Benedict as the Hollandaise was perfectly done.  We got their home froed potatoes which was pretty good flavor with peppers and onions. Only I might ask to get a bit of it crisped up next time.  

Jamms Signature Omelette - this isn't the fluffiest of omeletttes and is stiffer but still good. This has onions, mushrooms, peppers, steak and cheese in it topped with bernaise. It wasn't plentiful on the thin sliced steak (think like philly cheese or gyro), but all the components were decent. We also got home fried potatoes with this and this comes with a bread choice.  

Seeing as they are famous for potted bread we chose that.  They always have plain or cinnamon and rotate a flavor of the week. Vanilla caramel was this weeks which soinds like everything we liked. It is similar to brioche crisp on the top and fluffy inside and theu fave us a whipped butter frosting like spread.  Yeah,  Im a fan of the bread.  

Service was always friendly, and definitely on top of things. They are quite speedy here, our food was out in no time and drinks refilled stat. 

I can see why people like this place.  Its solid, no frills American hearty portioned breakfast with good service. I'll be back if I ever wake up early enough again.

"WHERE'S THE MEAT"  I hope my pic's posted!
We went in late, they close at 3:00 we got there about 2:15!  We got a seat right away.  I love the booths, there roomy.  Our waitress was Lorena, she was very professional, she greeted us with a smile.  She took our drink order, and as I was checking in when she came back, I showed her my yelp check in offer.  They have some bread for free.  So I choose the lemon and blueberry!  I have no idea what it is.  It came in this tin thingy, it was really a 1 person serving.  My husband got into it before I could take a picture.  But OMG, it was yummy!  The bread almost felt like it was not done, but it was so freaking good!
So I got the pastrami!  Ok, most places that serve pastrami, it's piled on the bread!  This looked like 3 strips of bacon between 2 pieces of bread!  for $10.00  Not worth it!  The skinny fries were good though.  My husband ordered french toast, eggs and sausage.  He loved every bit of it.
Next time I will stick with breakfast!

I just had the best omelet! It was a mushroom, brocolli and cream cheese omelet...cooked to a PERFECT fluffy consistency. It wasn't gooey like some other omelets that I typically get. They used chopped mushrooms (not canned) and yummy chunks of fresh brocolli. It also came with hashbrowns and their famous "Cup of Bread." The bread was flaky and buttery--delicious on its own or with jam. My friend ordered their Philly Cheese Steak, and she loved it too! Service was great...really friendly team.

Wow. this breakfast based restaurant is by far my favorite in the whole valley. Luckily it's right by where I go to school, so I come in here for a quick bite in between classes often. 

While this place is practically always packed, it's worth the wait. Usually the staff is working very proficiently and the wait isn't even that long. The breakfast food is very good, and they have a few vegetarian options. 

The pumpkin pancakes were my favorite when they were in season, but there's plenty other crazy combinations to choose from. The eggs benedict is usually what I get and the sauce is awesome. Yeah, awesome sauce.
Good place to eat, food is delicious, staff is amazing, will definitely comeback again

Jamms was a great breakfast spot! We discovered this place on Yelp and decided to give it a try when we arrived at the city. 

The service is friendly, quick, and efficient. I have to say that the service was truly good and based on that alone I would go back. You can tell that they care a lot about their customers and it really stood out to me that they knew their regulars' names and usual orders. I loved seeing that. You can tell that they go the extra mile and really try to get to know their customers. 

The food was also tasty.The portions are generous and the food leaves you feeling full afterwards. I ordered the Sandy Omelet (I was pretty hungry I forgot to take a picture of it) and my husband ordered the California Benedict. The omelet was really, really good and my husband enjoyed his meal as well. 

Everything was tasty, fresh, and filling. I highly recommend coming to Jamms.

The Denver potato pancakes are magnificent. I am so happy to have found this breakfast place thanks to all the rave reviews on Yelp! The service is a lot better too...although it seems a bit busy and every server and busser walks hastily through the small diner. The pot of bread was interesting. It lacked flavor, but I'm not much on sweets so it was decent for me - just expected sweetness and it was shocking to taste that it wasn't. We got today's special pot of bread: creamy strawberry (?) and it looked really weird because of all the sprinkles they decided to put on it. They could do without the sprinkles and maybe add a piece of strawberry on top? My boyfriend declined tasting the pot of bread until I told him to look past the child-like mess that sprinkles have painted on them and he actually finished it. I definitely want to try the cinnamon one next time though! 

Also, their home fries. Delicious. They are potato masters for sure! I can't wait to go back. I really am inclined to try different items, but I keep dreaming about their potato pancakes... Wish I could eat this everyday!
Delicious breakfast. Great Service. Amazing place to bring the kids and family when visiting Las Vegas.

We were here with family.  Great service.  The food was okay,  average = 3 stars.  I had the Canadian bacon, eggs, and home fries.  I was hungry so I ate it.  Nothing that I'd need to pass up a Dennys or an Ihop to  try again.

I am amazed that this place has won the Best of Las Vegas multiple times and is currently ranked as one of the best breakfast spots in Vegas...

The service just met my expectations, not bad but nothing special. 

The ambiance reminded me of an old fashioned diner. The decor was very dated and to be honest the place felt dirty to me.

My husband and I both ordered omelets, the Jamm's specialty omelet and the Ruben omelet both notated as favorite items on the menu. Maybe we just ordered the wrong meals as both left a lot to be desired. The home potatoes were inedible. It's a shame I was given such a large portion. The meals do however come with a "pot o' bread'. You can choose cinnamon raisin or white bread. These reminded me of bread my grandmother used to make at Thanksgiving, just plain ol yeasty bread. This trip down memory lane gave Jamm's the extra star. 

To be a good breakfast spot, the coffee needs to be spot on. This was another failing aspect of Jamm's. They use Illy coffee which I find to lack the robustness I love about coffee, almost watered down. I know many people love Illy though so this might just be a matter of preference.

Overall, I will probably never return to Jamm's. I typically give places two chances to win me over but on a good day Jamm's could probably only muster one additional star out of me.

I've been to Jamm's twice and both times I was impressed. I found out on the second occasion that I could check in and get a free pot of bread. Not feeling adventurous I chose the white bread over the orange creamsicle flavor of the day. The bread was super fresh, tasty and hot out of the oven. I loved it.

As for breakfast the three of us ordered biscuits and gravy, an order of the French toast sticks and a New York strip with eggs. All of the items were cooked perfectly including the medium rare strip steak. I will remember not to attempt to eat an entire order of biscuits and gravy again. The portion was huge. 

I find their coffee mugs sizable and the staff is always available for a quick refill. This is a great spot for breakfast without a huge wait time. We hit them on Mother's Day weekend and the place was packed but there wasn't a line out the door or anything so we were promptly seated.
Babalama omelette had huge pieces of avocado and lots of bacon (too much?) well worth the price. French press was great as well. Definitely suggest it.

I lived in Vegas for 6+ years but actually had never been to Jamm's so was excited to try it while visiting after reading all the positive reviews. Nice place, comfortable setting, good service but very average food at best. The free bread was the best thing they served my friend and I but it was really nothing that special. The eggs, hash browns and pancakes were very blah and average taste wise. I must say I was surprised by the lackluster flavor and experience after reading the plethora of complimentary reviews. It's definitely a head scratcher.

Jamms is a hidden gem when it comes to LV breakfast diners. Starting with the staff - everyone is incredibly nice and pleasant to deal with. I've both called in orders and dined in (many times) and have yet to come a cross a  poor attitude or rude remark. The food is fantastic all around, but where it's really at is the breakfast burritos. It's without a doubt a tough job to find a good breakfast burrito in LV. I'm talkin good ratios of egg/meat/cheese, crispy and well seasoned potatoes (but not overdone), and a quality tortilla. Oh yeah, Jamms nails it. Plus, you can make any of their omelets into a breakfast burrito. I recommend the Denver with crispy bacon instead of ham. God I want one now.
My favorite place for breakfast when I'm in Vegas. Love the pot of breads. The service is great and our waitress was real friendly.

The Little Foodie and me were finally up early enough to eat Breakfast!  

When we arrived, I figured I would go with the tried and true breakfast classics, but I was told about the brand new Chicken & Waffles!  Seriously, the day I went I was told they were added to the menu...so how could I pass that up??

Well I should have done that...passed them up.

Chicken and Waffles ($10). This was very disappointing! The waffle was good, but nothing out of the ordinary. There were only two pieces of what seemed like frozen chicken fingers, overcooked and bland. Pass! 

Yes, I know they aren't a Soul Food kind of place, so my expectations weren't too high, but looking at all the other positive reviews, as well as all the personal recommendations (the reason I was there in the first place), I was underwhelmed.

I'm sure I will be back to try the traditional breakfast items, and I foresee a much more positive visit than the last.
I have been missing out! The pot of bread is reason enough to keep coming back. My omelet & home fries were delicious! Service was quick and the waitresses were friendly. I'll definitely be back!

Exceptional service and well made food. I came here for the signature pot of bread so the food I ordered was secondary and really the stuff you see made generically at every restaurant (chicken noodle soup and salad). It was all made fast, it was still very delicious, and the pot of bread was wonderful and totally worth it. there was a hiccup early on; my coffee cup had lipstick on it. The servers handled it with speed and humor that I appreciated and the rest of the service was fantastic.
The food here is delicious and the service is on point! They are very attentive and make you know exactly what you're getting! This place is definitely well worth the visit!
Had the Denver omelette and it was very tasty! Coffee was great, service was good, overall good experience.

I read up about this breakfast place online and decided to take a break from the very busy Las Vegas Strip for breakfast. We had a great experience here. The service was good, the food was tasty and there was a line out the door when we got there. That was a sign that the locals like going there as it was so off the beaten track. We would go there again, nice family owned and operated restaurant.
The service is always great, the food is very good. Eat here atleast once a week. I highly recommend Jamms.
Great service! Great food! Had the pot of bread, sweet potato fries, and an amazing omelet!!! Recommend for brunch!!! Worth it

I've eaten here many time, but have only tried 1 menu item. I get the 
N.J. Sloppy Joe every time I go. It has three layers of rye bread filled with roast beef, turkey, corned beef, coleslaw and 1000 island dressing. Awesome!

Second visit and I am amazed by the over the top service. I had the opportunity to meet with Ronnie, the owner, and really enjoyed the pleasant conversation. I enjoy patronizing establishments with great service, who also take good care of their staff. I can tell that with long time staff, this place is extremely well run with the positive customer experience being foremost of importance. Thank you Ronnie and crew!

Repeat Jamms, and I think the secret is in the pot of bread. However, I did not get a pot of bread because we've been sticking to wheat. The highlight is the "everybody knows your name" service. The place is packed with regulars, and everyone knows everyone, which is super charming. For the food, my omelet was filled generously, but the overall flavor and stiffness factor weren't my ideal. I think I need to try something other than an omelet next time. Note: They serve Illy coffee, and you can even have it in a French press.

But, what I really wanted to let you know is that on Fridays they have fish and chips, and my husband went googley-eyed and inhaled the giant pieces of fish filet with boyish delight. Our waitress said they usually sell out before the end of the day, so get there early!
Wonderful breakfast, on this beautiful fall Saturday.  Great food, great server, Shirley was very friendly informative and welcoming.  Enjoyed the morning.

Updating....my last review was not very good but since then they have totally redeemed themselves.  I have been there many more times since then and am glad I did not give up o them.  The service has improved and I have not been disappointed again.  My favorite right now is the eggs benedict (minus meat) and is a great place to stop in on the weekends when out doing errands.  It is usually very busy as it seems to be one of the last Mom and Pop style restaurants in town.  


However, now the gum at the register is gone.  :(

1st time here with friends. The service was good, i ordered the chicken and waffle sandwich. Hubby ordered the corn beef hash. He liked it alot, mine was so so. Chicken was dry but waffle had good flavor. May try & come back and try lunch.

I've been coming here for breakfast for almost 20 years. An old local told me about this spot and it's been my go to. I live in CA, and my best friend and I have driven to
Las Vegas for breakfast. Lol. I know, sounds insane. But it's so good. Now I get to have it a few times a year and it's great. Not much has changed over the years, the food is always consistent and service is great. Thank you for being my favorite breakfast place ever.
Came here for the 2nd time today. Still impressed with the service and food. Generous portions and lovely waitresses too. Nutella pancakes with banana are a must!

The sweet potato fries at Jamms are probably the best I've ever had! I wanted to come back the next day and the next day and the next day just to get an order of those delicious fries. The cheeseburger was just as good. I began to describe this place as old-fashioned until Shirley (long time waitress) quickly corrected me and said "Please don't say OLD, just say it was your parents favorite spot and their parents as well." It's a breakfast and/or lunch place so they close early. Definitely coming back!

Horrible service if your a minority I recommend you don't go they won't treat you the way they treat privileged white people . The whole time I ate didn't give us napkins also didn't even offer a soda refill horrible service . there food isn't even as good as everyone makes it seem

Items ordered:

Coffee
Nutella Almond Pot of Bread
Red Velvet Pancake
S'mores Pancake
McBeth - French Toast, Ham, Turkey, Swiss
Grits

Another long-term fixture of the local food scene, and one I'd unknowingly been driving by twice daily every Thursday and Friday since relocating to Las Vegas, Jamms Restaurant quickly earned a spot on the 'to-visit' list when my server at Mary's Hash House mentioned the quaint local eatery as another "great place" serving up home-style breakfasts at a fair price - a 7am opening perfect for another Saturday of dining.  Nondescript from the exterior but cozy and kitsch inside as a friendly staff bounced between tables with endless refills of coffee from Illy at a mere $2.75 it was to a diverse menu and a hot, yeasty 'pot of bread' slathered with Nutella and toasted almonds that I arrived and after perusing the menu at length an order was placed, a server named Shirley warning me that it would be "a lot of food," but failing to inform me of noted upcharges of $2 for a single Red Velvet Pancake and $1.25 for grits in place of potatoes.  Jovial in spirit with tunes ranging from Sinatra to Madonna playing overhead it was perhaps a ten minute wait after the bread that the rest of my meal arrived and with each item larger than expected in size it was indeed a substantial breakfast with only the cocoa-less Red Velvet failing to impress...the flavor merely that of a decent buttermilk pancake gussied up with $2 in dye.  Speaking to the rest, suffice it to say that it would be hard to mess up something as decadent as the signature "S'Mores" with ample chocolate chips and chocolate syrup finding balance in bold buttermilk, marshmallows, plus a dollop of whipped cream and yet as good as the pancake was, the un-fried riff on the Monte Cristo easily stole the show as golden Texas Toast dipped in custard housed Ham, Turkey, and Swiss of good quality and quantity, all just waiting for a sweet gilding of maple syrup to make flavors pop.  Never one to quibble prices but a firm believer that upcharges should always be disclosed Jamms strikes me as a good-enough place in a city with plenty of similar options; a bit better than some and a bit worse than others...the sort of place I'm sure to revisit at some point for the Waffle Sundae or the Stuffed French Toast, but not before investigating other family owned spots or before second visits to Blueberry Hill, Hash House, Egg & I, or Baby Stacks.

My second time here, my husband's umteenth time (used to live in Vegas for 2 years) & it's still the same delicious food as when he took me here 8 years ago.  The bread in a cup is a MUST, especially when they have the different flavors.  LOVE the small plates choices also.  Staff is super friendly & the place is extremely clean.  Be prepared for a wait if you go on a weekend later in the morning tho!  But, the wait is well worth it!!

I went here for the first time today and the food was incredible. Had a Denver omelet with hash browns and home made cinnimon roll. It was a little pricey but the food was worth it to me. I would definitely go again and try the flavored pancakes, they looked amazing
OMG - this place is hands down one of the best breakfast places.  They have chiliqueles on the menu, not something offered just anywhere.  The bene's are fantastic!  100% worth the wait!

This is the last last time I will be coming to this restaurant owner prohibits employees from speaking Spanish! Racist racist will never be here again and I will make sure I will pass this along to my family members who also frequent this restaurant weekly!

Food was good- didn't like the pot bread... service was fast but buser was pushing us to leave...
When I got to the register I was trying to find my free pot bread coupon here on Yelp and the cashier just ignored me and ran my credit card through anyway I guess you must have to know the people to get the actual friendly service... instead of come in and sit eat give me your money and get out now

Been going to Jamms for almost a year now, and I love it more every time we go.
Friendly staff, great service even when they're packed. Food is really good.
Omelets are gigantic and tasty, and Eggs-florentine is really good.
I love, love their pots of bread. They always have regular and cinnamon-raisin and they feature a different 3rd option weekly, today was lemon-lime. Last week was orange-cream. Delicious. And they always have a consistently great cup of coffee.
It's a comfortable, family-feeling environment, great people and great food.

Was on vegas for a mini vacation from los angeles but wanted to try a breakfast out of the strip... So i decided to give jamms a try... I can honestly say it was worth the drive... I can honestly say the have the best corn beef breakfast... Yummy.. I recommend this place

Me love breakfast.  Me like Jamms.

Jamms is an okay at best breakfast/lunch spot in Spring Valley. Tucked in strip mall. Jamms is packed on the weekend. I think the reason this little place is so popular is their Pot O' Bread. What is Pot O' Bread, let me assist you. It's fresh bread dough, placed in a little ceramic ramekin, then baked, then delivered to your table. Recently they've added flavors of the week (recent flavors: chocolate peanut butter cup, cherry cheese cake, cinnamon raisin).

Jamms has a wide variety of options found at any dinner. Jamms' food isn't all that special. It's on par with Denny's and IHOP. 

The service is friendly, warm, and prompt. Coffee mugs, water glasses, and iced teas are never left empty. The restaurant is clean and loud. There are scattered tables and booths. On the weekends (Sat and Sun), there is looooong wait, so get here early.

On the way out, be sure to pick up a free piece of gum to get the sausage, egg, and whatever else is on your tastes buds.

Just realised I've never left a review for my fav corned beef hash spot! 
I go to Jamms at the very least a couple times a month. 
I loooooove their pot of bread. It's so adorable and warm and delicious. We usually get all three flavours when we go. 
They have some of the best egg beni's in town. And I usually get mine with corned beef hash on top. Which by the way is freaking ridiculously good. 
I don't think I'll ever stop coming here.

My favorite place to eat breakfast has ALWAYS been BLUEBERRY HILL. I don't like anyone else's french toast. I ordered a omelet here and was really surprised by the size of the omelet, the amount of vegetables, and best of all the perfect amount of cheese. The omelet was fluffy and didn't have a overcooked patch of burnt on it at all. It was very beautiful. I was there at 8:30 am on Monday and I was so happy that there weren't loud mulitple crowds. It was consistently busy but not overwhelming and annoying. My friend and I sat there for quite a while catching up and best of all the server didn't harrass constantly. They let us talk for quite awhile without interrupting. 
The only bad thing I had to say was the hashbrowns were TOO crispy for me. They were overcooked and crunchy and had that burnt potato flavor. Other than that---this is one of my new favorite spots for breakfast.

I love this place for simple but honest home style American fare. The food is not extravagant but good. It's just simple and delicious. 

The staff here are the best around kind, courteous and genuine. Good food great staff is always a good way to get me coming back, even from green valley.

If you are looking for good food to excite your taste buds, this NOT it! This is edible food you can find anywhere. I'm not saying the food is bad, just ordinary. I wouldn't make any special trips to go back.

We went for breakfast. I got the pancakes, eggs, and sausage, which were something that would served in the sample isles of Walmart (nothing special). With enough butter and syrup, you could make it workable. The eggs were just ordinary (but hot) and the sausage was kinda tasty.

My wife's french toast was bland (where the **** is the cinnamon?) Then,  the hashbrowns lacked the seasoning that makes a good shredded potato! 

Having said that, the place is in a "conditioned" part of Vegas. I wouldn't say it's ghetto, but in a middle-of-the-road type area. Now, the service was amazing, the servers and managers were very attentive and nice! I love good people working together. The 3 stars are for the service...0 stars for the "cooks".

AJ

Let me start this review by stating that the service at Jamms gets a 5+ rating.  Never was my glass empty or my table dirty.  They were attentive and did an awesome job at making sure we had everything we needed.  This rating is based on my meal.  I had a French toast combo and decided to go with the Jamms French Toast.  It was very tasteless and needed something sweet to give it a wake up call.  Had the chef done that, I would be giving this a 5 star.  Otherwise, the rest of our breakfast was good and my wife really enjoyed the pot of bread!!  I just recommend asking them to sweeten up the Jamms French Toast because I lost my appetite after eating it.

Big breakfast for inexpensive prices is the drawing point of this restaurant in a non gross way. Unlike other places that give you a heaping plate of heart clogging ridiculousness, Jamms has more healthy options. I had ordered the veggie omelet with egg whites and no cheese. That was the health nut in me speaking and then the glutton in me decided that sweet potato fries and a cinnamon raisin pot o bread should accompany with it ($10).  

Looking around there were seasoned customers and I knew this place was a winner. When you can get a bunch of older locals into a restaurant and have them enjoy a meal, it must be good. 

The omelet was massive, filled with tomatoes, onions, mushrooms, and big chunks of broccoli. The sweet potato fries were plentiful and I made sure to eat them all. The pot o bread was nice and fluffy. I just wished with a name like Jamms, they would have homemade jam. Just nitpicking now. 

The staff was nice, split checks were not an issue, and our server was quick with refills.
Great as usual. That's why we keep coming back. Food is excellent. Home style cooking. Reminds me of breakfast when growing up.  So comfortable in this place
We waited a long time to get a table, food was good, service was good and the people were nice.  Overall it was a average breakfast place.  We will go back.
I love Jamms! Their potted breads are so tasty! The fiance and I love going here on Sundays when we want a break from cooking. :)

This place is great! I was here for breakfast about one month ago. I like it because it is no nonsense. First of all, do not expect fancy because you're not going to get that. So what should you expect: you may have a little wait because it is that busy. You can expect good service in a diner like setting. The best part: you can expect an awesome breakfast. The menu is vast with all kinds of choices, from healthy to sinful. Everything is delicious and they will prepare to your liking. The prices are incredibly reasonable which never hurts.
I ordered an egg white omelette with feta cheese and spinach that came with house potatoes. My friend ordered the farmers omelette with the hashbrowns. Someone else at the table ordered French toast fries which are incredible and served with an incredible maple syrup sauce. I can go on... anything you want for breakfast... They have! Highly recommended.

I apologize to my friends @ Egg, but Jamms has the best breakfest in town! Today I had butterscotch pot of bread & the signature omlet. It brought tears of joy to my eyes. The waitress, Carol Ann, my friend, had to pry the plate out of my clenched fists. I had already licked the top clean, but she had a point, no need to lick the bottom. BTW, Carol Ann is an atrocious spellern

I just don't have anything to rave about or to recommend. The food was below average, it is just a locals regular breakfast spot. The advertised pot of bread was under-cooked and tasteless. The veggie omelette was watery. The coffee was bitter and watered down. Not what I had in mind after reading the reviews.

The waitress was very sweet but her service did not continue to the front of the restaurant. The cashier was not polite. She refused to give me a receipt that showed paid for my cash transaction. I do not think this is standard practice of restaurant sales. Why would she not be able to give me a receipt showing paid in cash? Is there a reason why this specific restaurant cannot provide a customer with a paid receipt? I was not content with their overall experience.

For the price and the reviews ... I expected more.

Will not return nor recommend.

Worse than the 1st time! This time service was even more terrible and the food was Bleh. They really don't have a kids menu worth ordering from. We stopped at black bears and baby cakes and both had long waits so we ended up here.....crap! We ordered corn beef hash,
Lumber jacks kids meals and the biscuits and gravy. Came with the pot of bread which was under done :(
Waitress was not nice and patient she just rushed us and seemed to like chit chatting with the other customers leaving us to feel really like we were a bother to her. We will not be returning.  This place seems to cater to certain kinds of clientele (if you know what I mean).  Again--baby cakes is preferred but be prepared to wait long.

The food amazing the coffee even better this place is absolutely the best. Saw it on tv and it's close to the house been there about 4 times tries something new every time and everything is great. Get there early cuz most the time is a wait but it is worth it

I love breakfast food!  This place is amazing and looks to have been around for a long time!  I think it's a hidden jem!  Took family here to eat breakfast once and now everytime they visit, we have to go to Jamm's at least once...even their friends came here on a recommendation!  

The omelettes are huge and so the the pancakes.  They both taste great also!  They are even able to do egg subsitute upon request!  They offer sides with the main breakfast items and I recommend the "pot-of-Bread".  It's soooooo good!  They always have cinnamon raisin and plain...but they also have their "special" which ranges from jalapeno chedder to s'mores!  All of it is great!


Price is reasonable, wait is reasonable, wait staff and hostess are always happy and helpful!

Give it a try if you're ever on that side of town!

The food was just as amazing as the first time, so that's not why this rating dropped. The rating dropped because during us dining in, a waitress (?) came up to me and my boyfriend and put her arms around us. She told me to quit using the "f bomb" because it was a "family friendly" restaurant. I was in such shock that I didn't say anything (I also cannot stand to be touched by anyone that I do not know). It was so uncomfortable. 

First of all, that's assault. You had NO RIGHT to touch us. The fact you even did is reprehensible. It was uncomfortable, unprofessional, and I have mental issues that could make it where I'll have a panic attack and freak out. That isn't very family friendly, now is it?

Second of all, my right to free speech trumps everyone else's feelings, and if you have an issue with that, go fuck yourself. Not to mention it was so loud in there the only people who could hear me were right next to me!

Thirdly, this is Vegas. If you're going to tell me that none of those parents curse in front of their children, you're stupid. What makes a stranger saying it any different? Get off your high horse.
Great place Great food. Shirley our server was the best! Will definitely recommend and come back

Thankfully there are still some old school breakfast houses still left that are not chains. Jamms is one of these, and is my favorite place to get breakfast in between class or whenever I have a craving for a pot of bread.

They have a great menu, and decent prices (averaging 20$ for two people). It can get busy depending on the times, and it does close early for Vegas time. I have never had slow service or a bad server, in fact, they get me in and out very quickly so I never worry. 

They have a great selection of omelettes and pancakes (Smores are the best) and they have a special Pot of Bread every now and then. So far I have tried the Pumpkin with cream cheese and the chocolate brownie with marshmallow, both were amazing but the brownie one was the best.
Having Awesome Food with Mom at Jamms (my new favorite Breakfast place) Chicken and Waffle BLT. Sooooo Good!!! and the service Rocks SHAY went above and beyond

This pace is the bomb for breakfast. We eat here every time we come to Vegas. The homemade corned beef hash is so freaking good I could eat a couple pounds of it. Omelets are huge and the pot of bread is also very good. Wait staff is superb, watch for Shirley - she's a hoot.

Excellent food. Good size portions. Friendly staff. Gotta love it! They remember my husband and I each time we come in and always know just how to help us make the difficult decision of what to eat each time cause everything is so good.

Bacon was crisped perfectly.  Pancakes were delish.  Corn beef hash was made from scratch - I love it!   Great cup of Joe.  Glad my wife and I came to have a great breakfast here.  Definitely a must if you wanna have a good ole breakfast without the hustle and bustle of the Strip.
Really good breakfast. I ordered the Hungry Lion breakfast and everything looked great. Service was great and our server was very friendly. Good atmosphere too.
Lovely food. Fast service. Great price. Very home style feel. Good portion size. Not too loud. If ur craving breakfast/brunch, this is THE Spot to go
Awesome.food, good staff, good service, enjoyed the meal, the wait for a table wasnt the best, but other than tnat not too bad
This place has the best breakfast and friendliest wait staff in Vegas. Do try to include this as one of your restaurants when in the area.

Jamms is definitely one of my favorite breakfast places.  I love the menu's variety.  There's always something that catches my attention, even when I'm not really hungry.  My go to item is the "Denver potato pancakes".  They're less like pancakes, and more like shredded hash browns mixed with diced ham, and vegetables, but they are absolutely amazing.  The portions here are huge, too.  You can get two meals out of most of the entrées here.
I'm not in love with the country kitsch grandma's kitchen decor, but considering the fact that a lot of their customers ARE grandmas, I can't complain too much.  Especially when the food is that good.

Don't be afraid of the wait.  This place turns tables fast.  

Hash and eggs are homemade.  Don't forget the freshly made pot of bread.  Always great food.

My family and I have been going to this restaurant since I was 12, that is currently 11 years. There are 3 people who I see everytime I go that have been there since before we first went there and they always greet me with and extra big smile. I recently took my wife and her parents and our nephew and there was not one complaint about the whole meal. I was suprised that my super picky fatherin law who is also an amazing cook did not say 1 bad thing about the meal and that was a shocker, he always complains. This restaurant is wonderful, the pot of bread is to die for (if it's fresh) and they are aware of the Yelp, free bread deal, and the waitresses are always so very nice. It is definitely 1 of my favorite places to eat in Vegas.

This is a great little breakfast joint. I haven't been here for lunch or dinner, but I assume it's good as well. 

First off, they serve illy coffee which is a big plus for me. Warm and friendly, the staff is super nice and attentive. The food is good. Like home cooking. To me it is not out of this world but is better than the major chains like IHOP or Denny's.

Service is decent but definitely show up early because this place gets packed pretty fast.

Love this place! We have been there a few times now when we head to Vegas. It might even beat our previous favorite breakfast spot in Hash House. The portions are more reasonable than Hash House delivers, which we appreciate and the price tag is less than hash house too. This mom and pop place has more of a truck stop feel and the fair is unique and special. Things you won't experience anywhere else. I love the little bread bowls with fun flavors of the week to choose from. The bread melts in your mouth. The hot chocolate is wonderful. And I haven't had a bad breakfast item yet. They have some really nice variations on how eggs are done. The flavors are homemade and wonderful. I haven't tried lunch or dinner here yet but breakfast is always the bomb! We will be back again and again!

Breakfast past noon? YUP! I had it here. 
Good service, friendly staff. I had the eggs and hashbrowns. The hashbrown was nice and crunch on the outside, just the way I like it. The toast was very buttery but my bad for forgetting to ask for dry. Prices are comparable to other average breakfast places. Would go back again.

First time here and I loved it. Service was awesome. Our waitress, Sandy was the best. The food was very good. Jamms French Toast was crunchy and fluffy at the same time. Loved it. Homemade Corned Beef Hash was pretty good too. We'll definitely come back.
Awesome coffee and breakfast omelet. Pot of bread to die for. Definitely a go to for breakfast or lunch.

Both times I have been here have been great experiences! The staff is friendly,  pleasant,  and quick! The food is delicious and so are the pots of bread! I have had the chicken and waffle blt and the reubon omelet. They were both so good! 

The atmosphere is fine and welcoming. It always seems like they are buzzing with happy customers!

Delicious all American breakfast diner.  That sums up Jamms in a nutshell.  First time eating here and we felt like we were treated like regulars.  We had the French toast, pancakes and bacon & eggs and everything came out fast and hot.  We've been to a couple of different breakfast/brunch places around the valley and immediately this place stands out as a gem.  We will surely come back and bring friends to try this place!

I LOVE JAMMS!!! This place is absolutely delicious. You will NOT be disappointed. Large American sized portions, friendly staff, and a nice bright atmosphere. I love coming to JAMMS for breakfast. I had the chicken fried steak with country gravy, hashbrowns, and a special sprinkle pot of bread. My tummy feels warm and full and wonderful.

I almost gave this Place 4 stars because the service is outstanding, I believe we had "Sherie" a talented server with a very unique voice and from what we witnessed she is well liked because many customers were coming to her and giving her a hug. We were at Treasure Island And a Guest recommended this place as the best breakfast in the area. The service is outstanding the Pot Of Bread we liked , but that was about it, I had the Chicken and Waffles, I wanted to be blown away, left half on the plate, Wish the Chicken was homemade. The French Toast Fries are a great a idea and not bad,My wife enjoyed the Hollandaise sauce on her benedict , My daughter  did not finish her Reuben Sandwich, Overall Jamms is a fun place with Great Service, I will ask some friends that live in the area to check it out, just in case we got them in a bad day
Wow what can i say. This place is very good and service from Shirley was great she did a wonderful job. We will definitely be back here again. Thanks Jamms

I walked in and the place was packed!

The decor reminded me of an episode of the Golden Girls...  it was charming.

The service was excellent.  

I had a Rueben for lunch.  The sandwich was pretty tasty. The pastrami was good, but they were real skimpy with the pastrami.  They had a total of 4 slices of pastrami...  When I was served the sandwich I had to lift the top piece of bread to see the pastrami.  

When I eat a rueben I want layers of pastarmi, kraut and dressing slopping out the back of the sandwich when I eat it.  

I like the place and I will probably end up there eating breakfast sometime...

If you are anywhere close to Jamms, stop what you're doing and go! Go now and get the Jamminator! It is beyond awesome!

The restaurant was packed, the service was great, and the food was amazing!

Great find on family vacation!
My husband and I love this place for breakfast! Definitely a gem in the desert. Highly recommend. Rainbow and Charleston.

Great price, good food. A little off the strip but well worth the drive if you have a car. Its a local place. Only problem is many people know how good it is so it stays pretty busy. Our wait wasn't that long though for me and my three kids.

A last second choice on our way to Red Rock Canyon, Jamms was a great surprise. Everything was great- the atmosphere, the menu options, the workers (even dealing with my indecisive wife who wanted first available, then a booth, then first available, then switched to a booth). 

We checked in with yelp and both got a free "bread pot" which was freshly baked and delicious. I ordered an omelet with ham, cheddar and broccoli. There was so much meat and cheese in it I was full until dinner (and needed two rolaids).

We also split a fruit plate which was freshly cut and good even though some of it wasn't in season. 

All things considered, probably one of the best breakfast diners we've been to in a while, that's even with the fact it wasn't exactly cheap. Money well spent.

The corned beef hash with egg whites and the pot o' bread are my go-to selections at Jamms.  A neighborhood breakfast/lunch eatery, the staff is always friendly, albeit a little slow on the service at times.  I think I've only been here on Fridays, so it's not too crazy busy and we've rarely had to wait for a table.  The pot o' bread is Jamms signature, basically a big yeasty dinner roll that comes with most of the breakfast platters, as well as getting a free one with your Yelp check-in.  Customers can choose the standard plain, cinnamon raisin, or the pot o'bread of the week; today's choice was triple chocolate brownie.  I had that pot o' bread plus the cinnamon raisin one that came with my corned beef hash breakfast--carb loading indeed!  If you haven't been here and love bread and breakfast like I do, give Jamms a try.
Great food! Cuban panini was great. French toast is amazing!! Cannot wait to come back next weekend and try more!
I tried speaking Spanish and some random guy named "Andy" said I wasn't able to speak Spanish. I finally ended up dying of starvation. RIP
Great food!! Great service by Sandy!! Our first time at Jamms! We will definitely be back!!!

Steak and eggs disaster! 

Eggs were undercooked and steak was very overcooked.  The cut of steak was meager peace of flat steak, not best choice for the dish.  Would rather have a better steak and pay more, seriously Albertsons is next door.  Gave the opportunity to correct the steak, got it back rare with no seasoning/salt.

Sausage Gravy (for biscuits and gravy)

Very smooth due to the absence of sausage.  It was a strange yellow color.  (Side note:  should be able to order with pot of bread if you so choose)

Omelet and breakfast potatoes 

Large and stuffed nicely.  Potatoes well cooked and not mushy.

Coffee wasn't refilled as promised twice, then presented with a $5 coupon for next time... there won't be a next time.




Pot of Bread was excellent!

***Local Vegas Breakfast Spot***

#LocalFlavor

There is a basket of Juicy Fruit and Big Red Stick gums at the hostess counter to sweeten up your taste buds before or after breakfast because guess what? I did pick up a stick or two to chew on while waiting about 20 minutes before and another stick after an awesome meal.

I've ordered their Irish Skillet which consist of corn beef hash, bell peppers, onions, potatoes scrambled with eggs and melted cheddar cheese, it didn't disappoint! I know a good skillet meal when I try one when it all just melts in my mouth, but hey the potatoes on these were not dry but almost light as butter, the scramble mesh well the all the toppings that made it a hearty meal for me. 

Addition to the experience my wife's Ruben Benedict was delicious! English muffin topped with corned beef, two poached eggs covered with hollandaise sauce? whats in that sauce?! it was creamy and it added some flavor, the corned beef was sizzlin'! and I love corned beef!

No coffee this time! but I've ordered the specialty Mexican Cinnamon Hot Chocolate/no whip cream which was good it's almost a horchata, just not as sweet. On the side, I recommend giving their Bacon Ranch Pot of Bread a try! It's a small bread with bacon bits pouched inside with butter spread, very tasty along with the softness core to bite in.

The ambience inside is like one of those old school diners with spacious booth seating and of course awesome service. Our server reminds me of some lady in the Simpsons because she had that friendly lovely voice.

I highly recommend this spot to do away classy Vegas eats for breakfast time.
Very good food great service. Love it here. Coming back for the 2nd time. Yummy food. Brought my mom and she loves it also.

We found Jamms on a fluke and absolutely love this little restaurant... It has a family feel to it and while not fancy- the food is amazing! I recommend the signature omelet- unlike many breakfast food chains, it delivers on not only the steak, but the mushrooms as well! I've also tried other items on the menu and they never fail to impress!

This place is sooooooo good, it's pretty small but totally worth the wait (it's usually super busy & packed) my friend took me here Friday morning & boy was I impressed, service was top notch & even tho it was so busy the waitress and waiter were extremely attentive. Our food came out quick & was so delicious. I will definitely be recommending this place to my friends & I'll definitely be back! Such a lovely big breakfast menu I have to try it all !!!!
Decent food but nothing special. The corn flake crusted french toast was OK but again, nothing special. I had the Irish skillet and was underwhelmed.

A locals restaurant, for sure, but super friendly to non regulars and THE FOOD!!!! The best french toast I've ever tasted, hands down. Amazing omelets, chewy super cheesy (the way I personally like them) The bread pots are like risen pots of yeast heroin. If I think too much about the bread pot I'll be right back there tomorrow morning consuming my entire day's  calorie consumption on multiple bread pots with the addictive cream cheese topping. They keep the coffee filled and the food out fast. Been coming here for over a year while out monthly for work and has been consistently excellent!

I keep forgetting to come here and enjoy the restaurant.  Portion are huge and everybody seems to know everyone.
Great experience

Jamms will be my go to place next time I'm in Las Vegas. The Illy coffee they served was delicious. Loved the pot o bread, I had the cinnamon raisin type, my breakfast was the chicken and waffle. The servers were attentive, friendly and quick. The decor is classic diner/coffeehouse, casual. My kind of place.
Great breakfast spot. Diner style with great options and great service. The potted bread is a must have.

Gr8 omelettes and other breakfast items.  Pancakes and waffles are good.   Lunch is less impressive.   Bread seems smothered in butter so ask for dry.  Service is efficient and friendly.  Gr8 coffee.  Good specials.
My daughter and I found this little gem on our way out of town.  Outstanding service, great food & a true local atmosphere.  We will be back!

The decor could definitely use some upgrades. However, I enjoyed my Mushroom omelette, home fries and cinnamon raisin pot bread. Although, there is nothing special here, I would still more than likely return.
