This restaurant has been a family favorite since Jamms first opened. I grew up as a child right behind Jamms!

*military discount in uniform only*
*free pot o' bread with yelp check-in* 
Went on Saturday 11-28-15 at 10am and there was a bit of a wait.  This restaurant is located on Rainbow in the same shopping center as Home Depot and Strip N' Dip Chicken Strips. 
$28.77 got us a pancake combo, a white castle omelet, and grits. 
The white castle omelet has ground beef, cheese, and onions inside and comes with home fries, which are sliced potatoes cooked with onions and peppers.  I thought it tasted a lot like a white castle. 
The pancake combo comes with your choice of sausage or bacon and then eggs cooked however you like them.  The pancakes were ridiculously fluffy-they had to have been an inch thick!  They were so tasty and the eggs and sausage were perfect.  They brought out two containers of butter without me asking, which I really appreciated.  There's nothing worse than getting big pancakes and they hand you one packet of butter.  
The grits were cooked well but lacked salt.  I liked that they brought butter with the grits without asking. Paula Deen would be proud of my obsession with butter today.

First time here. Driving down Rainbow, hungry, checked yelp breakfast. Decided to give it a chance. Glad I did!!

French toast combo was excellent
Free pot of bread with check in: today's special flavor Chipotle Cheddar (to go)

Efficient friendly service

Pretty good for breakfast! The pot o breads is what I mostly came for and they are pretty darn good! Service is very good and they also have healthy options .. They have a pumpkin marshmallow pot o bread sometimes as well!!
Not good at all.  I was excited about the pot of bread because of the reviews, but it was plain and dry.

Unfortunately this is one of the very few good diners in town. They nail the temperature on the eggs pretty much every time. I love the cinnamon raisin potted bread. It's my favorite. Very good coffee.
Really good service and food. One of my favorite breakfast spots. You must try their famous pot of breads. Cinnamon raisin is my favorite.
I enjoy this little place.  I think a lot of other people are too!! Packed this morning.
What's not to like about a pot of warm bread with soft butter. Add to that an awesome selection of omelettes , benedicts, waffles.....and it's all good!

We ate here in February and we all enjoyed our food. We all ordered omelets this time and were disappointed. The egg was fully cooked with the ingredients stuck in the middle and the Denver omelette had more cheese than egg! Too much.
My favorite breakfast place. Great coffee, awesome pancakes, great service. Have been coming here for years and it's consistently good.
The hot coco is the greatest hot coco ever!! The French toast fries are amazing as well.
Amazing food and amazing service. We will be coming back. The atmosphere is very very family friendly. Thank you Jamms.

Decided to stop here for breakfast about 1pm on Saturday. Place was fairly busy, but easy for a single like me to get seated. Menu looked like it had some interesting fair and some variety on old favorites. I decided to go with a Waffle Benedict for $9.99. $2.75 for an ice tea is a bit high, all the drinks were priced in this range. No offer for refill while I ate. 

Service was quick, and my meal was served inside 10 minutes of ordering. Crispy hash browns were cooked to my liking. The hollandaise sauce didn't have much to it, no taste of lemon or anything. Pretty bland. I ended up squeezing left over lemon from my ice tea on it to get a little bit of taste. The waffle was good, the eggs poached right and the canadian bacon a little small. Nothing that would make me want to come back for but I will try another meal here of something different.

What we noticed was from the moment that we entered the door, everyone was very nice and courteous to us. We're tourists from out of town and they most definitely made us feel comfortable there. It was as if this place was in our own hometown just by the hospitality. We never felt rushed to finish eating. 

I had the Jamms French Toast, which was very good. I could not decide if I wanted that or the corned beef hash. I'll have to try that on a next visit. There are so many choices that look very good, we will just have to keep going back to try them all. 

My wife had the mushroom omelet and she said that it was very good as well. She had mentioned that she has never had an omelet that good before. And she surely does eat a lot of mushroom omelet so I believe her! 

Jamms should be on everyone's list to try out!
Great food great service been coming for years they never let us down love you guys!!!!  Pot of bread forever

Service: Friendly and efficient (nothing spectacular but good none the less)

Food: Near perfect breakfast (perfectly browned and crispy hash browns and not too oily, Rueben Benedict was my breakfast of choice, hollandaise was creamy although i do prefer just a touch more tang, eggs poached to perfection in all its yolky splendor, tender corned beef atop a golden English muffin that was not soggy. Winner winner chicken dinner! The famed potted bread was a bit dry probably not the freshest, but it was now noon so I'm not mad at it)

Prices: standard ($24 after tax and 10% discount for 2 and a coffee with standard American breakfast portions aka BIG)
**10% OFF when you post their food on some form of social media! (; 

All in all great experience. Thanks for breakfast Jamms!

Side note: they serve Illy coffee so that is a gold star in my book

My wife asked me, "Do you think you can adequately describe the nirvana you just reached?"

The short answer? No. 

I ordered a liberally cheesed dish called the Irish Skillet. I've been to Ireland, but I don't remember having anything this good. 

The pot full of bread is an awesome idea and the Cinnamon Raisin is very good. 

Service is incredible and though the atmosphere is a little lacking (what do you expect for a homey feel?), the sum of all parts more than makes up for it.

Short story - go here. Home cookin' never tasted this good.

Great breakfast place. Eggs cooked to perfection, good coffee, and a special delight...a pot of hot bread! The bread comes in assorted flavors...we ordered the red, white, and blue...delicious! Service is excellent. Meals can be ordered "mini" size. I had the cheese and veggie omelet, mini, and it was still a decent size breakast..only $5.00!!
They charged me for my supposed" free pot of bread" that you get by checking in on yelp.
Jamms is like a trip to grandmas house. Yelping never tasted so good. I'm going with the corn beef hash and free pot of bread for every yelped eat it up yum!
This is probably the best place for brunch in Vegas. Let bed the French press coffee and the toot toot omelet was over the top.
Great locals place. The service is outstanding. The food is great. I had the biscuits and gravy, wow... The best I have had in a while. French Toast was just as good.

Arrived on a Sunday morning at around 8:30 am and it was already crowded. Waited about 15 minutes for a party of 6. This place is good. It's no wonder why they've won Trip Advisor Best of LV for four years in a row. If you're looking for an affordable brunch in LV, it's a must try.

Coffee - good. 

Pot of Bread - lots of hype, but all air - literally. If you must try it, do so. If you don't, you're not missing much.

Breakfast Burrito - delicious especially with all that cheese and potatoes. Lots of going in this burrito, but you won't be disappointed. 

Fried Chicken Waffle Sandwich - the star in this dish is the waffle. The fried chicken was crispy as was the waffle. The waffle had a sweet and cajun-like seasoning. Yummy. The tomatoes and lettuce tricked your mind thinking this sandwich was actually healthy. Regardless, it's good.

Corned Beef Hash - Different, but good. It's homemade with ample bits of cured ham. It could have been more "hashy", so it worked more like a skillet. The potatoes were good, but wasn't integrated well into the ham. Again, different, but tasted good.

French Toast - tried the the traditional french toast as well as the french toast sticks. This was my favorite dish. The french toast was made with thick toast and battered and fried to a nice crispy outer texture. The inside of the french toast was fluffy and moist. The french toast sticks were fun and easy to eat. Again, crispy outer and moist inner. 

Service was courteous and prompt. You get 10% off with Yelp check-in.
Excellent food and friendly staff. Check in on yelp and get a free Pot of Bread, which is amazing!

Ok so today was the day to check out what all the fuss was about! 

Went for breakfast this morning, this "greasy spoon" restaurant is comfortable and casual with booths. 

I ordered a Denver omelette and the country potatoes, of course the raisin cinnamon cup of bread. 

Yikes I was not aware they loaded their omelette's with cheese, was a bit overwhelming to say the least. They saute the Denver ingredients to oblivion, onions, ham and which should be green bell pepper as for a "traditional" Denver omelette, they used red. I like my Denver omelette with a bit more crunch of the onion and bell pepper. Way too much cheese about 1/2 pound it seemed, was basically a cheese omelette with some ingredients. It was insane the amount of cheese.

Anyhow, I will be sweating cheese for the next week, eek. 

The country potatoes and cup of bread was awesome, and the coffee is also good with plenty of refills. 

I will give them another shot and order something different next time, perhaps the french toast.

I have to say the service was awesome! We had a waitress that was sweet, charming and on top of things! She is one of those that calls you sweetie, honey, etc. I love that and eat it up, she got a hefty tip! lol

The wait is crazy, 20-30 minutes (went on a Sunday). I was on Yelp looking at breakfast places and this is one place we were excited to try. 

It was worth the wait, I'll tell you that.
Great customer service and the food was great! 
Don't want to leave a full review because I know I'm going to be coming back here. 

Will return whenever I'm in town.

Yummy! The pot of cinnamon and raisin bread was a perfect way to start the beginning of fall. The Ruben is one of the best I've had in town. It's a great sign when they ask your preference of corned beef or pastrami.  The portions are very generous and the prices very reasonable. Be prepared to wait for 10 to 15 minutes to be seated but it sooo worth it the wait.

Taste: 3
Creativity/Authenticity: 3
Atmosphere: 2.5
Service: 2.5
Bang for your buck: 3

Whats with all the hype, maybe because it was on the TV, but i dont really get how people can give it such good ratings. First its packed so be prepared to wait. The interior of this place looks like one of those diners you would find in the middle of nowhere, very run down and dinghy. Our waitress was an old lady who seemed to be somewhere else, just doing her 9-5 so you can imaging the service. I got the country fried steak and eggs with hash browns and a biscuit; my gf got steak and eggs with home fries and a side of biscuits and gravy and we got the free bread bowl with our check in on yelp. First the bread bowl had been sitting on the counter with all the other bread bowls because it was very hard on top and cold so that was horrible, my gf steak looked like it had been cooked in a mirco wave, very dry and chewy (medium rare). On the other hand my country fried steak was great, deep fried perfectly great taste however my eggs were mediocre just your basic mass amount of pre made eggs sitting in the back so again cold and flavorless. The biscuits and gravy weren't too bad, good flavor to the gravy and the biscuits were soft and flakey. Overall nothing special about this place dont see where the hype is, back to Mr Mamas better breakfast

Came here to meet with friends from NY while they were in town, apparently they had been here several times because the food was excellent and we had to get the pot of bread (this was said over and over) and we did, SERIOUSLY, NO REGRETS. It was amazing!! Food was fantastic and we were a table of 4 adults, 3 kids (6, 4 and 1) and a baby and the kids were seriously happy and ate everything put in front of them (parents will know this is seriously a rare occasion when every child not just eats but finishes their food without an act of Congress.) Awesome find for us locals and a place to take friends and family to in the future, a welcome find by our friends from out of town; sometimes that's what it takes to find greatness right in front of you.

Small little restaurant tucked away in the Albertsons shopping center. Portions were good and the service was great. They are always very attentive. They make their own bread there which is kind of cool.

The only reason they could not get 5 stars it was because the waitress that was serving us could not give us a clear answer on what was good. Has a first-time customer partner and I I asked her how was a particular item and the answer to each item was fantastic. If everything is fantastic I will not know what you decide so I got what she recommended was the best omelet in the house. I'm going to have to argue that it was kind of bland. I was expecting fantastic.
Great little place! Stopped by here on our way to the Natural History museum. Had medium rare steak & eggs, very yummy and great price. Waitress was friendly and attentive. Great place to stop :)

The first time it was here it was awesome. I had Jamms French toast and shared a side of chicken fried steak. It was good, the service was friendly and fast.
The second time I went here, there was an estimated wait of 20 minutes. If you're going here for breakfast, make sure you have at least two hours. The staff was friendly, and we were seated in 20 minutes. After we were seated, however, it took probably another 20 minutes for us to have our order taken. This time I got one of their specialty French toasts-- a word of advice, don't bother with the specialty French toasts. Just go with Jamms French Toast. I made the mistake of coming here with only an hour and a half before I had to go to work, and I got my food about two minutes before I had to leave. Immediately I asked for a to go box and left. The food was still good, friendly staff but it took too long. Don't come here during the breakfast rush. It will take an hour and a half to get your food.
The pot of bread is delicious, so is the chicken fried steak and Jamms French Toast. It's fried in corn flakes. Classic soul food.

I've been coming here for over 15 years. This place is Ahhh-mazing diner food! I usually get one of their scrumptious omelettes even when I come for lunch. Seriously, that's how good it is. And I Love the staff!!! They are always so welcoming and hardworking. This place can't be beat.

It's either Jamm's or I-Hop or Denny's.  Until recently Jamm's was the choice.  I haven't had a bad meal there in at least a dozen visits for breakfast.

If only I'm lucky enough to visit when that cackling waitress has the day off. She's a great gal, don't get me wrong, but wow that laugh is tough to take early in the morning.

One time I had a "fluffy" omelet.  Well, it wasn't fluffy.  It was a regular omelet like any other.  I mentioned it to the lady at the cash register when I paid.  "I don't think that was a fluffy omelet," I said.  Just a harmless comment, not a complaint.

Of course she got huffy.  I think she was the owner.  She looked at me like, Who are you the galloping gourmet?  "All of our omelets are fluffy," she insisted in a crabby tone.  

OK fine, calm down.  It left me with such a negative feeling I haven't been back. It's not that I'm holding a grudge but an experience like that cuts my enthusiasm for a place.  I don't feel welcome there anymore. Now I go to Red Rock casino or Denny's. Jamm's is so busy that one customer more or less is no big deal. They won't have that annoying fluffy omelet guy to deal with anymore.  

Good for kids:  Don't encourage people with "good for kids" votes.  Let 'em invade Denny's or I-Hop with their screaming whining little hellions. This is a small restaurant.  A tantrum will disrupt the whole place.

My second visit to Jamms and I might be hooked! As an east coast girl, I grew up on diner breakfast and have been scouring the country for that homestyle familiarity. The LAST place on earth I thought I'd find it is Vegas. 

Bringing my visiting PA native parents here at an off peak time (very important to avoid a long wait at this popular spot) we were seated immediately by friendly staff. Our waitress came over promptly and took our drink order. Consummate coffee drinkers, my family complimented Jamms regular brew. I've had their French press prior, and that was just as delicious. 

Mom and Pop took forever to decide but two words on the menu immediately decided for me: taylor ham. This Jersey breakfast staple is impossible to find outside of the Mid-Atlantic!! The Taylor Ham breakfast sandwich with (gasp!) REAL griddled potatoes was my choice. One bite and I was transported back to college and better days. Listen, I'm not an asshole that waxes poetic about food for no reason, but I'm not kidding--the sandwich was bomb. 

Mom got the 2 egg breakfast with bacon and hashbrowns because she's boring and a picky eater. It was as good as it gets with eggs over medium cooked perfectly. Dad got Joes omelet which was big enough to make him think twice about finishing the whole thing (he did though, because he is a machine). 

The pot o bread--a fluffy roll baked in a muffin tin--was phenomenal. Do yourself a favor and get the flavored ones. Cinnamon raisin is a delicious choice!!

Our food was served almost immediately after ordering, and server Jasmine was perfectly attentive without being overbearing--a hard balance to master. This place is popular for a reason so be prepared to wait but trust me, it's worth it.
Best breakfast and lunch spot. I recommend you come in and try it for your self.  Try the chicken and waffles or the steak n eggs.

Good traditional breakfast.  Fast service and good coffee.  Cornbeef was tasty but a little too salty.  Hubby's french toast was good. 

We'll be back...

I've been coming here since 2012 and the food is not consistent. I expect some great food for the price but that doesn't happen!

Oh and depending on what waitress you get will depend on the price you pay.

Temperature of restaurant is always freezing.
Love this place when visiting. Great service and bread pots are amazing! Big menu. Everything is good

This place is Jammin!! (Haha) My friends and I were craving some good, chill atmosphere, breakfast food that didn't cost $36 a person like on the strip! This is the place, a little hole in the wall with wonderful, friendly staff! It's a bit of a drive from the strip, but well worth it and affordable!

It's just so darn hard to find really great breakfast food. 

I was actually really happy with my order. I had the Sandy Omelet with sweet potato fries and it was pretty good. I was interested in ordering the pot of bread, but I forgot and ordered toast the first time around, but got it on my second visit. I don't really see what the hype is all about, I preferred the toast, actually.

The price was right, but the service was spotty. Hit or miss on my two trips here. Sometimes hard to get the servers attention and often would have to remind them two, three or even four times to get me a refill.

All in all, I'll probably be back, but I'm still on my quest to find the best breakfast in town.

Decent food is served here at affordable prices.  We came during the middle of the week for breakfast after reading so many positive reviews.  Was looking forward to trying one of their pots of bread that we read so much about.

We came at a good time because we had no wait at all.  The restaurant was about half full.  Our server was terrific, friendly, attentive, and fast.  

There are many choices on the menu.  We were getting confused because everything sounded so good.  I finally decided on Jamm's French Toast.  My wife ordered an omelet.

So, what did I think of the food?  Overall, it was okay.  Maybe, we did not order the best food off the menu.  Would I come here again?  Probably not.  There are so many breakfast places yet for us to try in Las Vegas.

I wanted to love here, I really did . Upon entering we were greeted by the woman standing at the counter. We didn't see my boyfriends family that we were meeting and we weren't sure if his little brother would make it, so we asked for a table of 4 to 5. She told us she couldn't seat us unless our whole party was there. I understand places that have this policy, but usually they tend to explain it nicer than they did here. The woman's tone was very unfriendly. We asked if it was possible just to put us at a table for 5 just incase the little brother snuck in a little late, not even order and her response was "well it depends if I seat you at a table for 4 or 5" ... Ok so please make it 5? Thankfully right then the little brother walked in and we didn't have to deal with her anymore. We were seated and quickly taken care of by a really spunky and nice waitress, she was seriously great. Big personality! 
I ordered the small plate omelet and their pot bread (cinnamon raisin). The omelet was average, I really wasn't blown away by it. The saving grace of the meal was the pot bread which was warm and delicious! 
Food was ok, front desk customer service was bad, and waitress was great! Probably won't go out of my way to eat here again when I visit Vegas.

4.5 stars.  The extra .5 is just for our waitress, Shirley, who is awesome with her contagious laugh! (If they served freshly squeezed OJ, then this would be 5 star status). 

I am so excited that we finally found a local breakfast/ brunch location that we can be proud to call our breakfast home.  We must have come at the right time for Sunday brunch because we were seated with no problem.  But, after a few minutes- the waiting area was filled to the brim with hungry patrons.  

I ordered the Eggs Florentine and after a number of misses with the hollandaise sauce at other breakfast joints- I finally found one that was perfect.  Of course, I mentioned yelp- and even got a free pot of freshly baked bread- and I selected the flavor of the day: apricot.  Yummo! My husband ordered his usual- chicken fried steak with a side of country potatoes and devoured it.  My cousin ordered an omelet and another ordered a sandwich with steak fries which were so delicious.  We also shared a plate of peach french toast and not a crumb was left.  Yes- we were quite the hungry bunch. 

Awesome service, awesome food and I love the fact that it is family owned.  We even left with some "Jamms coffee mugs" because we are such fans.  As their motto says, we did "enter as strangers, left as friends".  See you soon, new friend!
los french toast. estan buenos lo recomiendo con fresas los huevos baacon salsicha están bien el lugar esta agradable tranquilo
